title: homemade salsa
directions: Clean your vegetables and chop up. Bring all ingredients to a boil in saucepot.
Reduce to medium heat for 10 minutes.
In a water bath kettle, process for 30 minutes.
Take out to cool.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Spread pretzels, 2 tablespoons sugar and butter in a 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake
for
7 minutes at 400°.	Soften and blend cream cheese, sugar
and	Cool
Whip
and
spread
over cooled pretzels. Dissolve
jello,
add
strawberries and chill until slightly thickened. Spread over cheese mixture.
Refrigerate.

title: chicken supreme
directions: Spray nonstick skillet with Pam.
Brown chicken in margarine and dressing mix in pan.
Remove chicken and place in ovenproof casserole dish.
Add wine to skillet and stir to mix with dressing mix.
Bring to boil, then let cool.
Mix soup and cream cheese in bowl.
Add to wine and dressing mixture.
Mix well and pour over chicken.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
Serves 4.

title: reese's cup candy
directions: Mix confectioners sugar, melted margarine and peanut butter. Pack in greased 9 x 13-inch Pyrex.
Melt wax and chocolate chips. Pour over first mixture.
Let cool.
Cut into squares.

title: snappy spinach dip
directions: In bowl, blend Campbell's dry vegetable or onion soup and recipe mix, sour cream, plain yogurt, chopped green onions and frozen, chopped spinach, thawed and well drained.
Cover; refrigerate at least 2 hours.
Makes 2 3/4 cups.

title: green tomato pickles
directions: Mix pickling lime and water well, letting any lime that does not dissolve settle
to
bottom.
Select,
wash,
dry and slice tomatoes.
Pour off
lime
water and add sliced tomatoes to it. Do
not
use
aluminumware.
Soak
24 hours, then wash each piece well
under
running water and dry.
Mix sugar and vinegar and pour
over
tomatoes.
Soak 12 hours.
Add spices and bring to boil.
Cook at that point for 30 minutes.
Place in churn
or glass
jars.
Yields approximately 8 pints.
Old South recipe.

title: barbecue beef
directions: Brown the beef in butter and mix.
Simmer all ingredients 30 to 45 minutes.
Serve on toasted buns.

title: spiced tea
directions: Steep tea and cloves in boiling water for 5 minutes and then strain.
Dissolve sugar in hot spiced tea and add lemon juice. Serve hot.

title: hawaiian nut bread
directions: Beat eggs and sugar together; add shortening.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Add dry ingredients to first mixture and blend.
Add nuts and pineapple.
Stir just enough to combine.
Pour batter into a greased 4 x 8-inch loaf pan.
Bake in oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: bread and butter pickles
directions: In large bowl, combine cucumbers (cut in 1/4-inch slices) and bell pepper (cut in 1/4-inch julienne strips) with salt and cold water to cover. Let stand, covered, stirring occasionally, 2 hours. Drain well. In large kettle, combine vinegar, sugar, turmeric, mustard and celery seed. Bring to a boil. Add cucumbers and bell peppers. Cook, stirring 2 to 3 minutes. Can in 6 pint jars. Sterilize. Store in cool dark place.

title: icebox cheese wafers
directions: Cream butter and cheese.
Add salt, pepper, flour and nuts. Roll into 6 rolls wrapped in wax paper.
Refrigerate at least 24 hours.
When ready to bake, slice into wafers.
Cook on greased cookie sheet at 325 degrees until lightly brown.

title: hot cheese bread
directions: Toast bread.
Mix all ingredients and spread on toast.
Place in broiler until bubbly.
Remove and cut into fourths.

title: chicken salad
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients. Add whipped cream to salad dressing and then add this to the meat and vegetable mixture. Chill. Serve salad on lettuce or in cream puffs.

title: scalloped corn
directions: Mix ingredients together, except butter, in casserole dish. Top with the butter.
Bake, covered or uncovered, for 30 minutes at 350°, then for 40 to 45 minutes at 325°.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix eggs, sugar, flour, Karo, butter, water and flavoring (mix in this order). Add nuts. Pour into a 9-inch deep dish pie crust (uncooked). Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: lemonade pie
directions: Combine together and pour into baked pie shell.
Refrigerate 2 hours before serving.
Quick and very good.

title: meringue for cream pies that does not weep
directions: Mix the cornstarch and water. Add to boiling water. Cook until clear. Add the sugar and vanilla.
Mix into egg whites that are beaten stiff.

title: japanese fruit pie
directions: Blend all ingredients and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 300° for 40 minutes.

title: icebox rolls("a favorite from the '76 cookbook.")
directions: Place dough on board and knead.
Place in greased bowl.
Brush top with melted butter.
Cover lightly.
Store in refrigerator until ready for use.
(Can keep for weeks.) When ready to use, shape into about the size of an egg or walnut.
Brush top with butter.
Place on greased baking sheet.
Bake in 350° oven for 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes about 4 dozen rolls.

title: apple cake
directions: Beat oil and sugar until creamy.
Add eggs, salt, vanilla, baking soda and cinnamon.
Mix well.
Add flour and nuts; mix. Add apples.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread crescent rolls out on a baking sheet, pinching seams together to make 1 large pan of bread and bake as directed.

title: stewed potatoes with onions and tomatoes(dish for potato lovers.)
directions: Saute onions in olive oil in large skillet until light gold. Add green pepper. Add the cut up tomatoes with juice and salt and pepper.
Cook at slow intermittent bubble 15 minutes or so. Add potatoes.
Turn heat down very low.
Cover skillet. Cook until potatoes are done.

title: lasagna noodle bake
directions: Brown ground meat, onion and garlic.
Add tomato sauce.
Cook egg noodles and drain.
Layer in large or 2 medium bowls (greased), noodles, sauce, sour cream, cottage cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 325° for 30 to 45 minutes or until bubbles.
Serves 10 to 12.

title: dancing moth balls
directions: Mix water and vinegar, then add baking soda.
Mix all in a large container because it will bubble up.
Add a few drops of food coloring.
May be used on dinner table as a holiday centerpiece.
One-half cup moth balls added as desired.
Do not eat!

title: yeast rolls
directions: Mix the ingredients in the rotation given, such as a plastic bowl with a lid on it.
Refrigerate overnight.
About 3 or 4 hours before serving, roll out the dough and shape into the shape desired.
Let rise.
Bake in a 375° oven about 12 minutes or until golden brown.

title: cocktail meatballs
directions: Combine first 9 ingredients in a large bowl.
Mix well. To form
meatballs,
use
tablespoonful of meat mixture and roll into
balls.
Heat	shortening in large skillet on medium heat. Cook
meatball
until
brown on the outside and done on the inside.
You
can
also broil meatballs until done.
Drain meatballs well
and
put to the side.
In a medium saucepan on low heat,
heat jelly until it is a liquid, stirring constantly.
Then add chile sauce.
Continue stirring until hot.
Pour over meatballs.	Serve
very warm.
Makes 10 servings.
Can be made ahead, freezes well.
Sauce tastes better if made ahead.

title: fresh peach cobbler
directions: Peel and halve peaches.
Toss in sugar; set aside until juice forms.
If frozen peaches are used, juice will have formed already.
Melt butter in 9 x 13 x 2-inch Pyrex dish, with peaches, cut side up.
Pour juice in peaches.
Mix flour, milk and sugar. Pour over.
Bake at 350° for approximately 50 minutes or until top browns.

title: coconut cake
directions: Mix cake as directed on box.
When done poke holes with toothpick.
Mix Eagle Brand and coconut milk; pour over cake and let soak in.
Top with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Very moist!

title: chinese beets
directions: In a large pan, dump in sugar and cornstarch.
Mix well.
Add vinegar, cloves, catsup, oil and vanilla.
Stir well again.
Add beat juice. Cut beets into bite size pieces and add to fluid. Cook over medium heat until mixture thickens.
Cool and refrigerate.

title: caramel corn
directions: Mix sugar, syrup, margarine, cream of tartar and salt.
Boil mixture for 5 minutes on medium-high.
Remove from heat; add soda. Mix well.
Grease bowl.
Add popcorn and pour mixture over popcorn.
Pour on cookie sheet.
Bake at 250° for 30 minutes, stirring every few minutes.
Cool.
Store in metal or plastic container.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Brown meat and drain.
In a large skillet, add onion and simmer about 3 minutes.
Add chili powder, chopped jalapenos and cream of mushroom soup; set aside.
Then mix first six ingredients and set aside.
In baking dish or large iron skillet sprayed well with nonstick spray, put one layer cornbread mixture, then a layer of meat mixture; repeat cornbread and meat mixture.
Put grated cheese on last layer.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes or until done.

title: pineapple cookies
directions: Cream Crisco and sugar.
Add egg, pineapple and vanilla.
Sift flour, soda, baking powder and salt together.
Add to pineapple mixture.
Add nuts.
Drop teaspoonful on greased cookie sheet. Bake at 400° for 10 minutes.

title: frosted pumpkin bars
directions: Combine all ingredients and pour into greased and floured 17 x 12 x 1 pan. Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes. Frost.

title: ziti and broccoli
directions: Steam broccoli about 10 minutes; set aside. Mince garlic and brown in a lot of olive oil. Cook ziti; drain. Add butter to coat. Cover with salt, pepper and Parmesan cheese. Add broccoli to garlic; add more olive oil if needed, then add ziti and toss together and serve.

title: mom's favorite jelly roll
directions: Whip egg whites stiff, add yolks and whip again.
Add baking powder and a little salt, beat again.
Add sugar and flour; beat and add vanilla.

title: pecan pie
directions: Place shell in pie plate.
Line with pecans.
Beat eggs.
Add sugar, syrup, salt, vanilla and butter.
Pour over lined crust. Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.
Nuts will rise to form a crusted layer.
Refrigerate when cool.

title: 5-cup fruit salad
directions: Mix together and keep in refrigerator until ready to serve.

title: double-deck potatoes and carrots
directions: Place potatoes in boiling water in heavy covered saucepan. Place carrots on top of potatoes; sprinkle with salt.
Cover and cook over medium heat for about 5 minutes.
When potatoes and carrots are tender, drain.
Place cheese on top.
Replace cover; turn off heat and allow cheese to melt.

title: pineapple glazed chicken
directions: Sprinkle chicken very lightly with salt and pepper.
Brown in butter over medium heat.
Add remaining ingredients; cook, uncovered, turning breasts occasionally until liquid has mostly evaporated and chicken is glazed, about 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with scallions.
Serves 4.

title: zucchini tostito spread
directions: Fry first 5 ingredients until the zucchini is tender.
Drain thoroughly.
Stir in sour cream. Serve on Tostitos.
Cover with grated cheese and diced tomatoes.

title: california walnut bread
directions: Into mixing bowl, sift flour with sugar, baking powder and salt.
Cut in shortening.
Stir in 1 1/4 cups of walnuts.
Add egg, milk and vanilla; mix until ingredients are blended.
Turn into greased and floured 9 x 5-inch loaf pan.
Sprinkle remaining 1/4 cup walnuts over top.
Bake at 350° for 60 to 70 minutes, or until loaf tests done.
Let stand in pan 10 minutes.
Turn out onto wire rack to cool.
Makes 1 loaf.

title: fruit slush
directions: Boil sugar and water. Cool.
Add other ingredients and freeze. Put scoop in glass and fill with 7-Up.

title: cranberry raspberry salad
directions: Mix Jell-O, water, pineapple juice, and cloves.
When partially set, add rest of ingredients.

title: strawberry pie
directions: Wash and drain strawberries and place in a cooked shell.
Cook other ingredients in a double boiler on high temperature until thick (approximately 8 minutes), stirring constantly.
Pour over strawberries and cool.
Top with Cool Whip or whipped cream. Yields 1 pie.

title: gerry's simple blackberry cobbler
directions: Mix 1 cup sugar and cornstarch in a saucepan.
Slowly add hot water.
Boil until thick and clear.
Cool slightly.
Add blackberries.
Pour into 9 x 12-inch pan or larger.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Mix margarine and sugar.
Add the eggs, one at a time.
Then add the bananas on slow speed.
Stir in the egg mixture.
Add dry ingredients, then nuts.
Bake in a loaf pan at 350° for 40 minutes or until done.

title: bacon and onion muffins
directions: Fry bacon until crisp in skillet.
Remove with slotted spoon and drain on paper towels.
Saute onion in 1 tablespoon bacon drippings until tender (do not brown).
Set aside to cool.

title: easy chicken
directions: Put tin foil in a casserole dish; place chicken skin side down.
Sprinkle onion soup over chicken.
Place about 4 to 5 pats of butter on top of chicken.
Pour 1/2 cup water over chicken. Seal and cook in oven at 350° for 1 hour.
Turn over, reseal and cook for additional 20 minutes.

title: 7-up salad
directions: Combine all ingredients and let jell.

title: polish crullers
directions: Cream shortening until fluffy; add remaining ingredients and enough flour to make a soft dough.
Roll and cut.
Fry in hot oil until brown.

title: blueberry dump cake
directions: Put drained blueberries (fresh or frozen) in a baking dish. Sprinkle with sugar.
Add dry cake mix, scatter nuts over top. Add 1 large can sweetened pineapple, crushed with juice, over cake mix.
Melt margarine over mixture.
Bake at 350° for an hour or until done.

title: pasties(makes 4)
directions: Cut flour and shortening together.
Add enough water to hold together.
Roll out 4 plate size circles.

title: fried chocolate pies
directions: In a small bowl, mix sugar and cocoa together; taste.
You may need to add a little more sugar or cocoa, so it's not bitter.

title: baked crab meat spread
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 9-inch pie pan.
Melt margarine in skillet over medium heat.
Add bell pepper, green onions and garlic.
Cook and stir 2 to 3 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Stir in flour and pepper; cook 1 minute.
Gradually add milk.
Cook until mixture boils, stirring constantly.
Stir in Parmesan cheese.
Remove from heat.
Fold in crab meat.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries in food chopper or blender.
Place sugar, salt and lemon juice over cranberries.
Let stand for 2 hours.
Mix gelatin with boiling water.
Add cold water and stir until dissolved.
When gelatin is syrupy, add cranberry mixture, celery, nuts and pineapple.
Place in refrigerator until firm.
Place in refrigerator to store.
This salad can also be frozen.
Yields 12 to 16 servings.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Measure oil and water in same cup.
Pour over cream cheese, butter and sugar to melt.
Add 1 box butter cake mix and 4 eggs; beat about 4 minutes and bake at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes in a Bundt pan.

title: hungarian beef soup
directions: Place ribs in 6-quart pot.
Cover with water.
Bring to a boil and skim.
Tie parsley and celery with string to hold together and add to pot.
Add remaining ingredients.
Simmer gently and skim occasionally for about an hour.
Simmer for 3 hours.
Serve with noodles.

title: yeast rolls
directions: Soften the yeast in warm water and set aside.
Combine milk, sugar, shortening and salt.
Cool to lukewarm.
Add 1 1/2 cups of flour; beat well.
Beat in yeast and egg.
Gradually add remaining flour to form soft dough, beating well.
Place in greased bowl, turning once to grease surface.
Cover and let rise until double (1 1/2 hours).
Turn out onto lightly floured surface and shape as desired.
Cover and let raise until doubled, 30 to 45 minutes. Bake at 400° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Makes 1 dozen to 2 dozen.

title: baked corn
directions: Stir together flour and sugar in a bowl.
Break in two eggs and mix well.
Add milk, corn, melted butter and dash of salt. Pour into baking dish and bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: rocky road candy
directions: Melt morsels in microwave on medium; stir in peanuts and marshmallows.
Layer a brownie pan with wax paper.
Spread mixture in pan.
Chill in refrigerator until it hardens, at least an hour (in freezer if in a rush).

title: chew bread
directions: Mix and bake at
300° for 30 to 40 minutes in a greased and floured pan 12 x 18-inches.
Cut into squares while warm.

title: slush fruit
directions: Mix well
to dissolve the sugar.
Add crushed pineapple and juice.
Add bananas, grapes, cherries and blueberries.

title: homemade sangria
directions: Cut outer peel from orange into a long spiral strip without membrane.
Place in 2-quart container.
Squeeze orange and 1 lemon.
Add to peel.
Slice other unpeeled lemon into thin cartwheels.
Add to juice.
Add 2 quart bottles of wine.
Add sugar and brandy.
Stir to dissolve sugar.
Chill.
Pour into a punch bowl or 2 pitchers.
Add 1 quart chilled sparkling water. Optional:
May add cinnamon sticks, limes, cloves, etc.
Enjoy! Makes 2 quarts.

title: pineapple filling
directions: Mix sour cream and pineapple (juice and all) until well blended.
Add dry vanilla pudding.
Juice from pineapple will thicken it.
Pour into baked pie shell.
Chill!!

title: easy rice dish
directions: In 13 x 9 Pyrex, melt butter. Add other ingredients. Cover and bake 45 to 50 minutes at 350°. It's great with or without the chicken or mushrooms!

title: apple cake
directions: Sift together in a large bowl, flour, sugar, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Then add eggs, salad oil, apples and vanilla.
Mix together and then add walnuts.
Bake in a 9 x 13-inch pan at 325° for 30 minutes.

title: pickled peppers
directions: Pack peppers (which are cut in strips), parsley and garlic into pint jars.
Boil vinegar, water, sugar, salt and olive oil and pour over peppers.
Seal.
Can be cold packed.
Just bring to a boil.

title: lattice top chicken
directions: Combine soup, milk, seasoned salt, chicken, vegies, 1/2 cup cheese and 1/2 can onions.
Place in 8 x 12-inch baking dish. Bake, covered, at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: turkey burger deluxe(lo-cal)
directions: Prepare grill or preheat broiler.
Spray with nonstick cooking spray.
In a bowl, combine turkey, ketchup, garlic, green onions, basil, oregano and pepper.
Shape into four equal patties. Grill or broil 4 inches from the heat, turning once, for 8 minutes, or done to taste.
Place half a slice of cheese on each burger for 30 seconds until cheese melts. Top with lettuce, tomato slices and pickles.

title: peach pickles
directions: Peel and half peaches.
Bring sugar, spices and vinegar to a boil.
Add peaches and boil 10 minutes.
Pack in jars and let seal.

title: cathedral windows
directions: Melt chips and butter in top of a double boiler.
Add the beaten egg and let cool.
Fold in marshmallows and nuts.
Turn out on waxed paper covered with the coconut.
Form into 12 x 2 1/2-inch roll.
Wrap roll in waxed paper or foil and freeze. Slice to serve.

title: angel food cake
directions: Place egg whites in large mixing bowl with salt and extracts. Sift cream of tartar over the top.
Beat until the whites have no air bubbles, but are still moist.
Add 1 1/4 cups only of the sifted sugar, 1 tablespoon at a time, beating until the dry sugar disappears.
When sugar is all in, mixture stands in soft peaks whose tips bend slightly.
Sift flour with remaining 1/4 cup of sugar and fold sugar flour mixture into meringue, 1 tablespoon at a time.
Mix only until no flour can be seen.
Turn mixture into a 10-inch ungreased tube pan.
Release air bubbles by zig-zagging spatula through mixture.

title: weight watchers tropical spaghetti squash
directions: In medium bowl, combine all ingredients, mixing well.
Serve immediately or cover and refrigerate until chilled.
Makes 2 servings.
Each serving provided 1 1/2 vegetable exchange, 1/2 fat exchange, 1/2 fruit exchange.
Per serving contains 83 calories, 1 g protein, 2 g fat, 16 g carbohydrate, 29 mg calcium, 326 mg sodium and 0 mg cholesterol.

title: spanish rice
directions: In electric skillet at 375°, cook onion and pepper in a little bit of water.
Remove from skillet. Brown the ground beef, then add the onion and pepper. Add the tomato paste with 1 1/4 cups water and add the envelope of Sloppy Joe mix.
Stir together. Turn heat down and simmer for about 10 minutes. Add Minute rice and let simmer until rice is cooked.
Add more water if mixture looks dry.
Serve. Good with blueberry Jiffy muffin mix.

title: mini pizzas
directions: Will also need aluminum foil and hot pads.

title: hershey bar pie
directions: Melt candy and marshmallows in milk.
Let cool.
Whip cream and pour in chocolate mixture.
Pour in a pie crust and chill.

title: italian spaghetti
directions: Brown ground beef; add chopped onions and minced garlic.
Add other ingredients and simmer slowly for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
This makes a large amount and freezes wonderfully!

title: crumb-topped apple pie
directions: Mix ingredients together and bake in unbaked pie crust at 425° for 40-50 minutes.
Place foil around edges of pie crust and place pie on cookie sheet.

title: mrs. david e. rainey's pecan pie
directions: Mix together flour, sugar and butter.
Add eggs slightly beaten, then Karo and pecans and vanilla.
Cook in unbaked pie shell 15 minutes at 400° and then reduce oven to 350° and continue baking 45 minutes.

title: cherry salad
directions: Mix milk and Cool Whip, then add other ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch greased dish and chill. To garnish, sprinkle chopped nuts on top.

title: zucchini relish
directions: Mix first three ingredients together in large bowl and let stand overnight.
Drain and rinse in cold water and drain again.

title: wafer no bake cookies
directions: Melt chocolate in top of double boiler over hot water.
Remove from heat and stir in sugar, syrup and juice.

title: carrot cake
directions: Beat together the sugar, oil, eggs and carrots.
Sift dry ingredients together; add to first mixture.
Blend thoroughly. Pour into greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan or a Bundt pan.
Bake at 300° for 55 minutes, then bake at 325° for 10 minutes more.

title: minestrone
directions: Peel and cube potatoes.
Scrape and thickly slice carrots. Slice zucchini.
If using fresh tomatoes, peel and chop, or chop canned tomatoes.

title: fruit cocktail ice cream
directions: Put all ingredients into a 4-quart ice cream freezer.
Mix well, then fill to "fill" line with homogenized milk.
Freeze.

title: mike's famous spaghetti sauce
directions: Cut links into bite-sized pieces.
Fry by itself until brown. Then put in pot with other ingredients.
In large skillet fry sirloin, 1 onion, 2 cloves of garlic and 1 bell pepper until almost done.
Then add into pot with other ingredients.
Combine all ingredients and simmer for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Add mushrooms 1 hour before sauce is done.

title: pork chop creole
directions: Heat shortening in large electric skillet.
Add pork chops and saute until brown.
Add all other ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown ground beef; drain off grease and stir in onion powder, salt and pepper.
In large casserole, combine pork and beans, ground beef mixture and remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Bake at 325° for 1 1/4 hours, stirring occasionally.

title: bean soup
directions: Put all ingredients, except sausage, in 8 to 10 quart pot and fill with water.
Add a lot of black and red pepper, but no salt yet, as the ham may be salty enough.
Add salt after it has cooked an hour or two if needed.
Cook about 8 hours.
Sometime during the day, slice a link of smoked sausage in rounds and fry to remove grease.
Add to soup.
This freezes well but will need more pepper after thawing.

title: chili
directions: Brown ground beef and put in a big pot.
Add all ingredients and simmer 7 hours.

title: angel biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm water.
Sift flour, soda, baking powder, sugar and salt into bowl.
Cut in shortening.
Add buttermilk, then yeast mixture.
Stir until all flour is dampened. Knead on floured board for 1 or 2 minutes.
Roll out to desired thickness.
Cut with biscuit cutter.
Bake at 400° for about 12 to 15 minutes.

title: strawberry orange shakes
directions: In a blender, combine orange juice, milk, strawberries and sugar.
Cover and process until smooth.
Add ice cubes and process until mixture reaches desired consistency.
Pour into glasses and garnish.
Serves 4.

title: pork broccoli stir-fry
directions: In a large skillet stir-fry pork, until no longer pink. Remove pork from skillet, and keep in warm place.
In the same skillet, stir-fry broccoli about 2 to 3 minutes.
Add green pepper and garlic, cook for 2 minutes.
Stir in the mushrooms, cook 2 minutes longer.
In a small bowl combine cornstarch, chicken broth and soy sauce, until smooth, and stir into skillet.
Bring to a boil, cook and stir constantly until thickened.
Return pork to the skillet, heat through.
Serve over rice or noodles.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Boil chicken.
(Put in a slow cooker in the evening.) Bone the chicken and save the broth.
This can be used for many recipes.

title: scripture cake
directions: Beat butter, sugar and honey to cream. Add eggs, one at a time, still beating. Add almonds, raisins and figs. Beat again. Add almonds, flour, spices and baking powder having already mixed them and then add milk. Bake in slow oven for 1 1/2 hours.

title: orange juice cake
directions: Beat sugar, shortening and buttermilk.
Beat alternately milk and dry ingredients.
Add grated orange rind and ground raisins. Bake at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: yorkshire pudding
directions: Beat eggs at low speed.
Add milk.
Beat 1 minute.
Add flour and salt.
Beat 2 minutes.
Pour batter into drippings.
Bake in 400° oven for 40 minutes.
Cut into squares; serve immediately.

title: pecan pie
directions: Mix all ingredients together and pour in unbaked pie shell. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes, then turn to 350° and bake 20 minutes more.

title: double clam chowder
directions: In a 2-quart saucepan over medium heat, combine all ingredients except parsley.
Heat through, stirring occasionally. Do not boil.
Garnish with parsley.
Makes about 5 1/2 cups or 5 servings.

title: chicken pot pie
directions: Cook chicken.
Stir together Veg-All, soup, broth and chicken. Pour into casserole dish.
Mix together margarine, milk and flour until smooth.
Pour on top of chicken mixture.
Don't stir.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.
tags: cream of celery soup or cream of chicken

title: cherry-glazed pork roast
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a small saucepan.
Bring to a boil.
Reduce heat and simmer for 2 minutes.
Add almonds and sprinkle roast with salt and pepper.

title: caesar salad with capers
directions: Rub salad bowl with crushed garlic; set aside.
In separate bowl, combine remaining garlic with the olive oil.
Allow to stand for at least 1 hour before using.
Toss 1 tablespoon of the garlic oil with the toasted croutons; set aside.
Tear the lettuce into large pieces; place in the garlic rubbed salad bowl.
Sprinkle with salt.
Grind a generous amount of pepper over the lettuce.
Have remaining ingredients available at table if you wish to toss the salad in front of your guests.
Crack the egg into the lettuce; toss.
Sprinkle with the lemon juice, green onions, capers and the remaining olive oil.
Toss well.
Add the anchovy fillets and Parmesan cheese.
Sprinkle with the croutons, or serve alongside. Toss gently.
Garnish with whole romaine leaves and serve immediately.
Serves 4.

title: microwave peanut brittle
directions: Place sugar and corn syrup in a 2-quart microwave-safe bowl. Cook on High for 3 1/2 minutes.
Stir in peanuts.
Cook on High for 3 1/2 minutes.
Add margarine and vanilla.
Cook on High for 1 1/2 minutes.
Add baking soda and stir gently, until mixture is light and foamy.
Pour onto nonstick cookie sheet and spread evenly.
Let cool for one hour.
When hard, break into bite size pieces.
Makes 1 pound.

title: carrot salad
directions: Marinate overnight or at least 6 hours.

title: zucchini casserole
directions: Melt butter; mix with dressing mix.
Line bottom of casserole with 1/2 this mixture.
Cube zucchini and saute with onion. Combine soup, sour cream and shredded carrots; add to zucchini and onion.
Put into baking dish.
Sprinkle top with balance of dressing mix.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: grilled italian roast
directions: Marinate roast in Italian dressing 6 to 8 hours or overnight. Grill over medium coals approximately 20 minutes per pound, turning occasionally.
Brush with marinade occasionally.
Carve into slices.

title: zucchini pickles
directions: Combine the first 6 ingredients in saucepan; bring to boil. Pour over zucchini and onions; let stand 1 hour (minimum).
Stir occasionally.
In large saucepan, bring mixture to a boil; simmer for 3 minutes.
Continue simmering while filling sterilized jars. Fill jars to 1/2 inch of top, making sure fluid covers vegetables. Seal jars at once.
Ready to eat after 2 days.
Recipe may be halved.

title: cracklin corn bread
directions: Mix corn meal and flour; mix buttermilk, oil and eggs.
Add to meal and flour.
Mix well.
Add cracklins.
Pour into greased iron skillet.
Place into preheated 450° oven for about 35 to 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: yankee noodle dandee
directions: Melt butterscotch bits in large heavy saucepan over low heat. Stir in chow mein noodles and peanuts until well coated. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto waxed paper. Allow to cool.

title: vegetable salad
directions: Drain all vegetables well.

title: banana bread
directions: Mix soda in with bananas.
Combine all ingredients.
Bake in slow oven 45 minutes.

title: crock-pot baked potatoes
directions: Wash potatoes.
Drain but do not dry.
Place damp potatoes in crock-pot.
Cover.
Cook on low for 6 to 8 hours or until tender.

title: corny cheese browns casserole
directions: Mix and pour into 9 x 13-inch greased pan.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: pumpkin roll
directions: Beat eggs 5 minutes, gradually adding pumpkin and sugar.
Add flour, baking powder, and spice.
Grease pan.
Cover with waxed paper and grease again.
Pour mixture onto cookie sheet and sprinkle with nuts.
Bake at 375° for 15 minutes.
Dump out onto towel covered generously with powdered sugar (nut side down).
Roll short side to short side.
Let cool for 2 hours rolled in towel. Take out, slice and serve.

title: chili con queso dip
directions: Saute onion well in margarine.
Add tomatoes, chilies, salt and pepper.
Simmer for 15 minutes.
Add cream cheese and when melted, add the cream and heat.
Serve with tortilla chips.

title: good ole banana pudding
directions: Place a layer of wafers and then bananas.
Repeat.
Mix sour cream, Cool Whip and instant pudding together.
Pour over bananas and wafers.
Stir a little bit.
Let set overnight or two nights, then serve.

title: stuffed mushrooms
directions: Clean mushrooms, chopped stems and put in mixture.
Stuff. Bake for 10 minutes at 325°.

title: potato gratin with peppers, onions and tomatoes
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
In a 2-quart baking dish, spread 1 tablespoon olive oil in bottom.
Scatter 1/4 of the minced garlic. Layer vegetables, starting with potatoes, then peppers and finishing with tomatoes and onion.
Sprinkle salt, pepper, garlic and oregano between each layer.
Pour remaining olive oil over surface.
Bake for 1 1/2 hours or until fork-tender.

title: cranberry apple pie with soft gingersnap crust(makes one (8-inch) pie, 8 servings)
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Place gingersnaps and margarine in food processor.
Process until gingersnaps are finely ground. Press gingersnap mixture onto bottom and up side of 8-inch pie plate.
Bake 5 to 8 minutes and cool.

title: apple harvest cake
directions: Mix apples and sugar.
Let stand for 1 hour.
Beat eggs, oil and
nuts;
add cinnamon and nutmeg to taste.
Sift flour, salt and soda.
Mix well with mixture and add vanilla.
Bake at 325° for 55 minutes in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch loaf pan.

title: citrus cream cheese icing
directions: In a small bowl, combine all ingredients and beat until smooth.

title: puppy chow
directions: Melt first 3 ingredients.
Fold in cereal.
Pour in powdered sugar.
Mix well.
Don't smash.
Let it cool, if you can, otherwise, dig in!

title: sausage and egg casserole(for brunch or breakfast)
directions: Cook sausage and drain thoroughly on paper towel.
Butter bread, top side up.
Place in casserole dish.
Spread 1/2 of cheese and 1/2 of sausage over slices.
Beat milk and eggs and pour over the mixture.
Place remaining buttered bread, sausage and cheese on top.
Press down gently, making sure all of the bread is wet. Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Bake, uncovered, at 325° for 1 hour.
Great for holiday breakfast.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Mix sugar, spices and salt. Add pumpkin.
Mix well. Add eggs. Blend thoroughly. Add evaporated milk gradually. Mix well.
Pour into pie shells. Bake in preheated 400° oven for 50 to 55 minutes or until set.
Cut each pie into sixths. Serve.
Makes 8 (9-inch) pies.

title: meat and mushroom sauce
directions: Brown meat.
Take out and drain on paper towels.
Brown onion. Drain grease in pan.
Add tomatoes and paste; cook 15 minutes. Add meat, mushrooms with liquid, salt, pepper, basil, oregano, garlic powder and wine.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.
Cook 1 hour more without cover.
Serve over cooked pasta.
Serves 8.

title: strawberry squares
directions: Grease baking pan with some butter or margarine (9 x 9 x 2-inch).
Heat margarine, marshmallows, dry milk and strawberry milk mix in saucepan over low heat until smooth, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat.
Stir in 4 cups of cereal and coconut until coated.
Empty into buttered pan.
Pat mixture evenly into the pan.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: really good bar cookies
directions: Cream together butter, sugar and egg.
Add bananas.
Sift together flour, soda, salt and nutmeg.
Mix.
Stir in oats and nuts.
Pour in a sheet pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
While warm, glaze with powdered sugar.

title: quick rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in lukewarm buttermilk.
Add soda, sugar, salt and oil.
Add flour, a little at a time.
Mix well in bowl. Knead on floured board until stiff.
Cut into rolls.
Oil tops and bottoms and let rise for 30 minutes.
Bake at 400° until done.

title: cheese balls
directions: Grind sharp cheese and pecans together.
Add Worcestershire sauce and garlic powder to taste.
Combine pimento cheese and cream cheese with this mixture.
Make into balls and roll in paprika.
Good served with crackers.

title: cool rise bread
directions: Dissolve yeast in water in a large warm bowl. Add milk, sugar, salt and margarine.
Stir in 2 cups unsifted flour.
Beat with rotary beater until smooth, about 1 minute. Add 1
cup flour and beat until mixed.
Gradually stir in enough additional flour (3 cups or more) to make a soft dough.
Turn onto lightly floured board and knead until smooth and elastic.
Cover dough with towel and let rest 20 minutes.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Melt butter; add onion, garlic and mushrooms.
Cook until onion is transparent.
Remove.
Fry round steak in same pan until brown. Remove meat.
Make sauce in pan of salt and flour.
Add bouillon and sour cream.
Stir until thick.
Add Worcestershire sauce and Kitchen Bouquet.
Then put meat, onion and mushroom in slow cooker, then pour sauce and slow cook for 5 to 6 hours.
Serve on a bed of egg noodles.

title: black-eyed peas with okra
directions: Shell and wash peas in a heavy pot.
Cover with water and add salt pork and salt.
Bring to boil, cook on low until tender.
Wash okra and place on top of peas.
Cook for 5 minutes and turn off, leaving okra to steam until fork-tender.
Do not overcook okra as okra will become slimy.

title: oriental shrimp salad
directions: Combine first six ingredients in a bowl.
Mix together remaining ingredients and combine with shrimp mixture.
Chill and serve.

title: soft molasses cookies
directions: Sift flour once.
Add baking soda and spices, then sift again. Cream the shortening. Add sugar gradually. Cream together until light and fluffy. Add egg and beat well.
Add molasses.
Add flour and milk alternately, mixing well after each addition.
Drop by rounded teaspoonfuls on lightly greased cookie sheet about 2-inches apart.
Bake 10 minutes at 400°.

title: gourmet baked salmon
directions: Saute onions, garlic and celery in olive oil for 10 minutes. Add remaining ingredients, except the salmon.
Place salmon in large casserole.
Pour mixture over salmon.
Bake, covered, in 375° oven for 20 to 30 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: hot mexican cheese dip
directions: Combine cheese and chilies in a 1 1/2-quart microwave-proof casserole.
Cover and cook on 80 (Reheat) for 5 minutes.
Mix thoroughly with portable mixer until smooth.
Keep hot on a heated tray or candle warmer and serve with corn chips or potato chips or with crisp raw vegetables.

title: chicken tarragon
directions: Heat oil and butter in a large frying pan.
Saute chicken until lightly browned and remove to a warming platter.
Add green onion to drippings and saute about 5 minutes.
Return chicken to the pan and add brandy, wine, tarragon and pepper.
Cover and simmer 20 minutes.

title: fried biscuits
directions: Add yeast to warm water.
Add all ingredients; let dough rise.
Cut into biscuits.
Drop into hot fat and fry.
Delicious with apple butter.

title: crescent roll salad
directions: Unroll crescent rolls; place over bottom of 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Press together to form crust.
Bake according to package directions (do not overbake).
Mix cream cheese, mayonnaise and Ranch dressing mix; spread over cooled crust.
Top with fresh vegetables, such as cauliflower, broccoli, green pepper, onion and tomato.
Top generously with shredded cheese.
Refrigerate.
Let set 4 to 5 hours.
Serve at room temperature.

title: linguini salad
directions: Cook linguini until tender.
Drain and rinse in cold water. Mix linguini, vegetables and dressing in large bowl.
Chill for 2 to 3 hours.

title: blueberry cream cheese squares
directions: Combine cornstarch, sugar (1/2 cup), water and blueberries. Cook, while stirring, over medium heat until sauce bubbles and thickens.
Cool.
Combine cracker crumbs and butter.
Press 3/4 of mixture into the bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mash cream cheese until soft.
Gradually beat in sugar (1 1/2 cups) and vanilla. Fold in Cool Whip.
Spread 1/2 of mixture carefully over the crumbs.
Spread blueberry filling evenly over cheese.
Spread remaining cheese mixture (drop by spoonfuls, then spread to spread evenly).
Sprinkle with remaining crumbs.
Chill overnight.

title: sinful potatoes
directions: Mix all together.
Sprinkle with crumbled, crisp bacon.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: icy melon freeze
directions: Combine puree and sugar until sugar dissolves.
Add juice and stir.
Place in a freezer container and freeze until partially frozen.

title: quick and easy dessert
directions: Mix cheese and dry jello together.
Add Kool Whip and blend all.
Add drained fruit, mix and refrigerate.
Makes a large amount.

title: mary jo reeves' fruit punch
directions: Combine water and sugar; bring to a boil.
Cool mixture.
Add orange juice, pineapple juice, crushed pineapple, bananas, lemon juice and cherries.
Mix and freeze.
To serve, remove from freezer one hour before serving.
Add 3 quarts of ginger ale. Yields 50 servings.

title: water chestnut hors d'oeuvres
directions: Wrap chestnuts with 1/2 slice of bacon; fasten with a toothpick.
Place in rows in 9 x 6 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° until bacon is almost done but not crisp.
Remove from oven; pour off grease.
Combine catsup and sugar.
Pour around but not over chestnuts.
Bake 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.
Serve immediately. Yield:
15 to 18 servings.

title: garlic cheese grits
directions: Cook the grits in the salted water. When cooked, add the butter, garlic cheese, sharp cheese and Worcestershire sauce. Stir until the butter and cheese have melted.
Put in greased casserole and sprinkle with paprika.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Serves 8 to 10.

title: potato casserole(serves 12 to 14)
directions: Blend soups gradually with cream cheese.
Add the sour cream, green pepper, onion and seasonings.
Pour over potatoes and mix well.
Place in a well-greased 9 x 13-inch pan or Corning Ware dish.
Top with grated Cheddar cheese.
Bake at 300° uncovered for 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
May be made ahead and held in the refrigerator until baking.
Adjust baking time if chilled.
Also freezes well after baking.

title: chocolate-chocolate chip pound cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together for 2 minutes. Add 6 ounces chocolate chips. Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: mock enchiladas
directions: Layer ingredients in 2-quart casserole dish. Cover and bake in a 350° oven until bubbly. Serves 4.
(May also be microwaved.)

title: golden ember barbecue sauce(student favorite)
directions: Shake together in batter and stand for several hours or overnight.
Cover bottom of baking dish with barbecue sauce. Place cut up chicken in single layer in sauce and bake 45 minutes at 350°, turning after first 25 minutes.
Remove from oven and place barbecue sauce over all pieces.
Just before serving, grill over hot coals just to heat and crisp the chicken.
Pass sauce.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Combine bread crumbs, cheese, salt and pepper.
Dip breasts in melted butter, then in bread crumb mixture, coating breasts heavily.
Place breasts in baking dish and bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes, uncovered.
Do not turn chicken.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix oil, sugar and eggs well.
Add remaining ingredients, stirring well.
Place mixture in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with 6 ounces of butterscotch chips and bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: orange jello salad
directions: Mix Jell-O in the Cool Whip; then add cottage cheese and then the fruit.
Let set overnight.

title: "wendy's" chili
directions: In a skillet, over a medium high heat, heat the oil and brown the beef crumbling with a fork until all the pink color disappears. Set aside. Puree the onion soup in a blender and pour over the beef, stirring over a medium heat until it's the consistancy of rice, breaking it up with a fork as it heats. Stir in the spices. Add undrained beans, tomato paste and sauce, stirring until well combined. Heat over low heat at least 20 minutes until piping hot and the flavors have blended.

title: crunchy double chip cookies
directions: Stir flour, salt, baking powder and baking soda; set aside. In a large bowl, beat the sugar and margarine.
Add eggs and vanilla.
Beat well.
Stir in dry ingredients, chocolate morsels and peanut butter morsels.
Drop by slightly rounded measuring teaspoonfuls into remaining crushed cereal, coating dough completely.
Place about 2 inches apart.
Bake at 350° for 12 minutes until a little brown.

title: stratta
directions: Line a
x
9-inch
greased
baking pan with toasted bread. Layer
diced meat on bottom, veggies, cheese and onion soup. Pour
soup/milk
mixture
over all and top with toasted bread shapes cut
with
a
cookie cutter.
Cover with foil and let set overnight
in
refrigerator.
Then
bake the next day just before guests arrive.
Serve with a tossed salad.

title: chocolate-butterscotch krispies
directions: In large saucepan, cook corn syrup and sugar over medium heat, stirring frequently, until mixture begins to boil.
Remove from heat.
Stir in peanut butter.
Mix in cereal.
Press into a buttered 13 x 9 x2-inch pan.
Melt chocolate and butterscotch morsels over hot water, stirring until smooth.
Spread over cereal mixture; chill until firm (15 minutes).

title: mexican cornbread casserole
directions: Grease a 13 x 9 baking dish.
Mix cornmeal, buttermilk and corn together.
In a skillet, cook beef and onions.
Drain well and add peppers.
Pour half the cornmeal mixture into dish. Spread beef over mixture and cover with cheese.
Top with remaining mix.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.
Enjoy!

title: cheesy chicken and rice dinner
directions: Heat 1 Tbsp. oil in skillet. Add chicken and cook until browned. Remove chicken. Add broth, 1/2 cup water and broccoli, stir, heat to a boil. Stir in rice and Velveeta. Top with chicken, cover and cook on low heat about 5 minutes or until cooked through. Gently stir until Velveeta is melted.

title: prize winning quick cherry crisp
directions: Place pie filling in greased baking dish.
In separate bowl, combine dry ingredients.
Add margarine to dry ingredients, and mix until crumbly.	Sprinkle crumb mixture over cherries.
Bake in 375° oven for 30 minutes.
Serve warm or cold with whipped cream.

title: quick and easy chocolate cream cheese pudding pie
directions: In a small bowl, beat cream cheese until soft and fluffy, about three minutes on medium speed.
In medium bowl, prepare pudding as directed on box.
Beat cream cheese into pudding until smooth.
Pour into crust and chill for at least one hour.
Before serving, top pie with Cool Whip and garnish with crushed Heath bar.

title: sponge cake
directions: Beat egg yolks, sugar, flour, baking powder, cold water and lemon extract. In a separate bowl, beat egg whites until stiff. Fold egg white mixture into cake batter with spoon.
Use angel food pan. Bake at 300° for 1 hour.

title: cheese pudding
directions: Mix all ingredients together. Bake at 325° for 40 to 50 minutes or until brown.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Mix and marinate overnight.

title: chicken gumbo
directions: In medium saucepan, combine first four ingredients.
Bring to boil; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 6 minutes or until tender.

title: banana muffins
directions: Sift together flour, baking powder, soda and salt.
Beat shortening until creamy.
Add sugar gradually and continue beating until light and fluffy.
Add egg and beat well.
Add flour mixture alternately with bananas, mixing until batter is smooth.
Turn into well-greased small muffin pans and bake in 425° oven for about 20 minutes or until muffins are done.
Makes about 16 muffins.

title: stir-fried chicken and mushrooms
directions: Remove skin and bone from chicken; slice thinly, holding knife at a diagonal slant.
Mix chicken with next six ingredients; set aside.
Thinly slice mushrooms and onion.
Stir-fry in 1/4 cup oil until tender (2 minutes).
Remove to bowl.
Add three tablespoons more oil; stir-fry chicken mixture until done (2 or 3 minutes). Add mushroom mixture and peas.
Heat through.
Serve with rice. Makes 4 servings.

title: raspberry rice pudding
directions: Mix Cool Whip, sugar, and vanilla; stir in rice and jam. Garnish with raspberries.

title: fat-free sugar-free jello pie
directions: In a large mixing bowl, dissolve Jell-O with the boiling water.
Add the cold water and mix well.
Next add the cream cheese, blending it with a mixer, then add one cup Cool Whip. Pour into pie crust and refrigerate until firm.
Top the pie with Cool Whip and serve.

title: potato soup mix
directions: Combine all ingredients in a large bowl, mixing until completely blended. Store in airtight container. Yield: about 2 1/2 cups of mix.

title: army salad
directions: Mix buttermilk and jello.
Add mandarin oranges, pineapple and bananas (add just before using).
Mix Cool Whip into mixture. Chill and serve.

title: ham cheese ball
directions: Mix all together, except 1 cup of ham.
Roll into 2 balls. Use remaining ham to roll balls in to cover cheese.
Serve with your favorite crackers.

title: chocolate mousse
directions: Combine cream cheese and sweetened condensed milk, beat until fluffy.
Add chocolate syrup.
Dissolve coffee in the hot water, add to chocolate mixture.
Fold in whipping cream.
Pour into individual glasses.

title: veg-all casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients well; put in greased casserole dish.
Melt 1 stick oleo and combine with 2 cups crushed Ritz crackers. Spread over Veg-All.
Cover and bake 25 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: pride of iowa cookies
directions: Blend sugars and shortening; add eggs. Sift dry ingredients together; add to first mixture. Stir in vanilla, coconut, oats and nuts. Mix well and drop by teaspoonfuls on greased cookie sheet. Flatten with bottom of glass. Bake in 375° oven until light brown, about 8 minutes. Makes 5 dozen.

title: gammy's rolls
directions: In a large bowl, combine yeast, 1/2 cup warm water and mix. Then add 1 teaspoon sugar and flour; mix well.
Cover with clean cloth and let rise 30 minutes or until bubbly (in a warm place).

title: fettuccine with three cheeses and toasted almonds(prep: 10 minutes; cook: 15 minutes; serves 4)
directions: Heat a small skillet over low heat; add almonds.
Toast, stirring until lightly browned, about 2 minutes.
Set aside.
Boil heavy cream in a medium saucepan, adjusting heat to avoid boiling over, until slightly reduced, about 5 minutes.
Stir in the cheeses until smooth.

title: imitation canned pineapple
directions: Combine all ingredients and simmer for 20 minutes.
Pack in pint jars. Cover with juice and seal.
Process at 10 pounds pressure for 10 minutes. This can be used successfully in any recipe calling for crushed pineapple.

title: quick desserts
directions: Pull cake apart; put in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour pudding over cake.
Pour cherries over all.
Let set 1 hour.
Spoon into bowls.

title: no bake pie cream cheese-peanut butter pie
directions: In a large bowl, with an electric mixer, combine cream cheese, peanut butter, sugar and milk.
Beat until smooth.
Gently fold in whipped topping. Pour into pie shell. Freeze 4 to 6 hours. Thaw 10 minutes before serving.

title: mystery icing
directions: Blend the flour and milk.
Cook until mixture thickens to consistency of cream.
Cool, but don't chill.
Cream sugar, butter and shortening, adding salt and vanilla.
Add the slightly cooked flour mixture and continue beating until very fluffy.
Yield: Icing for a 2-layer cake.

title: chicken spaghetti
directions: Saute onions, celery and peppers in butter until tender.
Add juice, paste and seasonings and cook down low.
Add chicken and mushrooms and continue cooking.
Just before serving, add spaghetti, cheese and peas.

title: biscuit ring
directions: Combine sugar, margarine and water in 1-quart bowl.
Cook 1 minute.
Stir in nuts.
Separate biscuits and cut each biscuit into quarters.
Add to sugar mixture.
Stir to coat each piece of biscuit with caramel.
Push mixture away from center and set glass in center to make ring mold.
Cook, uncovered, 2 1/2 to 3 minutes, rotating 1/4 turn halfway through cooking time.
Biscuits should be firm and no longer doughy.
Rest 2 minutes.
Remove center mold and invert on serving plate.
Serve warm by pulling apart.

title: peach cobbler(usa)
directions: Mix together milk, sugar and flour.
Melt margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour in flour, sugar and milk mixture, pour peaches on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes or until golden brown.

title: lo-cal hot fudge sauce
directions: Combine cocoa and cornstarch in saucepan, pressing out lumps. Whisk in both milks gently.
Cook over medium heat until thickened and bubbly (2 to 3 minutes).
Remove from heat and cool to lukewarm.
Stir in sweetener and vanilla.
Serve immediately.

title: hamburger stroganoff
directions: Cook bacon; break in small pieces.
Brown hamburger; add onion and cook until tender, then drain.
Stir in soup, salt and paprika. Simmer for 20 minutes, stirring frequently.
Stir in sour cream and heat through; do not boil.
Serve over noodles, cooked as directed on box.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: fruit surprise
directions: Drain all juice, but save.
Pour juice over pudding mix.
Mix and pour over fruit.

title: swiss steak
directions: Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle one side of beef with half of mixture; pound in.
Turn beef and repeat with remaining half of mixture.
Cut beef into 4 or 5 serving pieces.
Heat shortening in skillet until melted.
Cook beef over medium heat until brown (about 15 minutes).
Mix tomatoes with liquid and remaining ingredients; pour over beef.
Heat to boiling; reduce heat.
Cover and simmer until beef is tender, about 45 minutes.

title: italian sandwich beef
directions: Cook in crock-pot on low for 24 hours.
Serve on hard rolls, yeast buns or yeast bread.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Bake 2 boxes Jiffy cornbread mix, then crumble. Mix crumbled cornbread with crumbled boiled eggs, onion, cooked and crumbled bacon, tomatoes, green and yellow peppers and enough mayonnaise to moisten.

title: sausage strada
directions: Break 4 slices of bread into pieces in bottom of a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Melt 1 stick margarine and pour over bread.
Cook sausage and drain.
Sprinkle over bread and then spread cheese over sausage.
Mix eggs, milk, mustard and salt.
Pour over all.
Leave all night in refrigerator.
Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: baked pineapple
directions: Cream butter and sugar, add eggs and beat well. Add salt, pineapple and bread cubes; bake in a 8 x 8 inch greased baking dish at 325° for 40-50 minutes.

title: frozen lemon pie
directions: Separate eggs, beat whites until stiff then beat in sugar. Beat yolks thoroughly, then add lemon juice.
Fold egg yolks into egg whites.
Then fold in heavy cream, stiffly beaten.
Pour into shell that has been lined with graham crackers.
Sprinkle top with cracker crumbs.
Freeze until firm.
Serve frozen.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix the gelatin, cornstarch and hot water; cook about 1 minute.
Add sugar substitute and cool.
Add sliced strawberries to gelatin mixture and coat.
Pour into cooled 9-inch pie shell and refrigerate.
Top with low calorie whipped topping.
Serves 8.

title: summer lime pie
directions: Dissolve gelatin completely in boiling water in large bowl. Stir in lime peel and juice.
Mix cold water and ice to make 1 1/4 cups.
Add to gelatin, stirring until ice is melted.
Stir in whipped topping with wire whisk until smooth.
Refrigerate 10 to 15 minutes or until mixture is very thick and will mound.
Spoon into crust.
Refrigerate 2 hours or until firm.
Garnish with additional whipped topping and lime slices.
Store leftover pie in refrigerator.
Serves 8.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: In the 1
gallon
of
boiling water, break macaroni and add to water.
Stirring occasionally, cook 10 to 15 minutes or until done.
Drain and place in a well-greased baking pan.

title: noodle soup
directions: Place celery, onion and carrots in a soup kettle.
Add water almost to cover.
Simmer, uncovered, for about 30 minutes or until vegetables are tender.
Add broth and bring to a boil.
Add noodles and boil gently for 20 minutes.

title: cracker cookies
directions: Put crackers on buttered cookie sheet.
Cook 1 cup butter and 1 cup brown sugar for 3 minutes.
Pour over crackers and bake at 400° for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle both chips over crackers while hot. Swirl gently as chips melt.
Sprinkle with nuts.
Cut into squares after it cools slightly.
Easy!

title: sour cream orange cookies
directions: Sift dry ingredients and set aside. Cream the butter and brown sugar. Add eggs, vanilla, orange rind and sour cream. Sift in dry ingredients, blending well. Add nuts. Drop by teaspoonfuls on lightly greased cookie sheet. Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes. Top with icing while still warm.

title: microwave fudge pie
directions: Put butter and chocolate in glass mixing bowl.
Microwave on High for 30 to 45 seconds or until melted.
Add sugar and beat well.
Add eggs and beat well.
Stir in flour and vanilla, mixing well.
Add nuts and pour into a 9-inch ungreased pie plate.
Cook in microwave on High for 6 minutes, rotating plate often. Top with vanilla ice cream if desired.

title: crustless quiche lorraine
directions: Grease a 9-inch pie plate or quiche dish with the butter or margarine.
Sprinkle the wheat germ over the bottom and up the sides of the pie plate or quiche dish. Set aside.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Cream margarine and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add flour, salt, cream cheese and vanilla.
Mix well.
Bake in a large tube pan at 300° for 1 hour and 40 minutes.
Cake should be put in a cold oven.

title: san antonio with picante black bean sauce
directions: Sprinkle both sides of chicken with 1 teaspoon of cumin and the garlic salt.
Heat oil in 12-inch skillet over medium-high heat. Add chicken; cook 3 minutes.
In medium bowl, combine beans, corn, Pace picante sauce, red pepper and remaining 1 teaspoon cumin. Turn chicken; spoon bean mixture evenly over chicken.
Reduce heat to medium; cook, uncovered, 6 to 7 minutes or until chicken is cooked through.
Push bean mixture off chicken into skillet. Transfer chicken to serving platter, using a slotted spoon; keep warm.
Cook bean mixture over high heat 2 to 3 minutes or until thickened, stirring frequently; spoon over chicken.
Sprinkle with cilantro and serve with additional picante sauce.
Serves 6.

title: stewed zucchini
directions: Saute onions and potatoes in 2 tablespoons margarine until onions are soft.
Add zucchini and water to cover.
Simmer, covered, until vegetables are tender.
Add lima beans with liquid and 1/4 cup of margarine.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Serves 4 to 6.

title: lasagne with uncooked noodles
directions: Brown and drain ground beef. Add sauce and bring to a boil. Spoon some sauce on the bottom of a 13 x 9 inch baking dish. Layer uncooked noodle, cottage cheese,

cheese, and then sauce. Repeat and end with sauce. Cover and bake at 350 degrees. (Pray that it does not boil over into your oven!). Bake 1 hour, then remove and let sit for about 10 minutes before serving.

title: lemon cake
directions: Beat 4 minutes.
Pour into a greased and floured pan, 9 x 13-inch.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
While hot, poke holes with a cooking fork.
Pour on glaze:

title: cube steak
directions: Spray square baking dish with Pam.
Place cube steak in dish. Mix soups and 1/2 can water.
Mix well.
Pour over steak.
Cover with foil.
Bake 1 hour in 350° oven.
Good over rice or mashed potatoes.

title: king ranch casserole
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients.
Layer with Doritos and cheese. Pour 1 can chicken broth (saved from chicken) over casserole. Bake until bubbly at 375°.

title: old fashioned meat loaf
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large bowl, combine meat, oats, 1/3 cup ketchup, onion, egg and 1 teaspoon bouillon; mix well.
In shallow baking dish, shape into loaf.
Bake 1 hour.
Combine remaining 1/3 cup ketchup, 1 teaspoon bouillon, brown sugar, lemon juice and dry mustard.
Pour over loaf and bake 10 minutes. Remove from oven and enjoy.

title: fruit punch
directions: Mix together in large punch bowl with ice cubes until frozen concentrates completely dissolve.
Then add 2 quarts chilled ginger ale and 1 pint chilled club soda.
Stir well and serve.

title: tiny christmas bites
directions: Combine crumbs and margarine, add milk, vanilla and almond extract.
Stir in remaining ingredients until well blended. Spoon 1 tablespoon into each paper lined miniature muffin pan. Bake at 325° for 25 to 30 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool on rack.
Yields 6 dozen.

title: baked corn
directions: Stir ingredients together.
Bake in 7 1/2 x 13 1/2-inch dish at 350° for 45 minutes.
Don't overbake.

title: crackers -- cookies
directions: Line cookie sheet or 9 x 13 pan with saltine crackers. On a stove, boil the margarine or butter and brown sugar for 3 minutes. Drizzle over crackers. Bake in 350° oven for 7 minutes. Sprinkle chocolate chips. Spread when melted.

title: little cheddar loaves(serves 2.)
directions: Melt butter over medium heat in a 3-quart saucepan. Add onion; cook, stirring often, 2 minutes or until tender. Whisk in soup, milk, hot sauce and half of cheese, stirring just until cheese melts. Stir in macaroni; pour into a lightly greased 9-inch square baking dish. Top with remaining cheese. Bake at 375° for 30 to 45 minutes or until golden and bubbly.

title: theresa's marinara sauce
directions: Individually chop vegetables in a food processor until finely minced.
Place oil in a large pot and saute vegetables along with minced garlic and parsley.
Once vegetables are partially cooked (about 4 minutes), add sauce and broth.
Lower heat and cook for approx. 1 hour.
When sauce is done, add the romano cheese and stir.

title: orange glazed carrots
directions: Combine all ingredients in a saucepan.
Cover and simmer 15 to 20 minutes or until tender.
Uncover and cook until liquid is absorbed.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: breakfast pizza
directions: Spray pan with Pam.
Lay biscuits on pan.
Press biscuits. Scramble eggs and pour on top of biscuits.
Place all meat and cheese on top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: zucchini quiche
directions: Separate dough into triangles; place in 10-inch pie plate with points to center. Press edges together, building up slightly to form an edge at top; crimp.
Bake in a 375° oven for 5 minutes. Sprinkle pecans on bottom of crust.

title: cornmeal cookies
directions: Cream oleo and sugar.
Add eggs; mix well.
Add dry ingredients, mixing well.
Add nuts.
Drop by teaspoon on a greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.

title: date dessert squares
directions: Bring water and dates to boil, turn down heat and simmer 3 minutes.
Cool mixture.
Melt marshmallows in microwave oven or on top of stove, do not cook too fast.
Mix dates, nuts and marshmallows.
Butter a 9 x 9-inch pan and pour 3/4 of Oreo cookie crumbs in pan, spread out.
Pour date mixture on cookie crumbs. Sprinkle remaining crumbs on top.
When ready to serve, cut in squares and top with Cool Whip or whipped cream.

title: caribbean spice chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Drain pineapple juice into large measuring cup.
Combine spices into small bowl.
Stir 1/4 teaspoon spice mixture and cornstarch into pineapple juice; set aside.

title: apple cake
directions: Stir all ingredients together.
Bake in a tube pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: cool whip lemon pie
directions: Blend together and add 1 large container Cool Whip.
Pour into pie shell.
Makes 2 pies.

title: jam and nut cake
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco.
Add one egg at a time.
Mix in milk, soda and dry ingredients.
Bake in cake pans at 350°.

title: granny's fruit salad
directions: Drain syrup from fruit cocktail and pineapple.
Mix sour cream and marshmallows together.
Chop apple and banana.
Combine all ingredients.
Let set for several hours before eating.

title: apple-cranberry sauce
directions: Wash, peel and core apples into small pieces and put in saucepan with orange and lemon juices.
Cook over low heat until apples are soft.
Add cinnamon and then mash with a fork.
Stir cranberries, sugar and ginger into applesauce.
Cook until cranberries are soft.
Serve hot or cold.

title: sweet chocolate chip cookies
directions: Cream together butter and sugars.
Add egg and water and vanilla; beat well.
Sift together flour, soda and salt.
Blend into creamed mixture.
Stir in chips and nuts.
Drop from teaspoon 2 inches apart.
Bake at 350° about 15 minutes.

title: economy pound cake
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt 3 times.
Cream butter, adding sugar gradually.
Add eggs and beat thoroughly.
Add sifted dry ingredients alternately with milk.
Pour into greased tube pan and bake 55 minutes in moderate oven (350°).

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Blend together potatoes, salt, eggs, sugar, butter, vanilla, milk and cinnamon.
Pour into a baking dish.
Crumble together in separate bowl pecans, brown sugar, flour and butter for the topping.
Sprinkle over potato mixture.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: hungarian squash(serves 4 to 6)
directions: Grate squash and barley cover with water.
Add seasonings. Saut onion in oil and add to squash. Cook 15 minutes.
Drain water. Add 1/2 cup sour cream mixed with 1 tablespoon flour. Mix all and simmer 3 to 5 minutes and serve.

title: ham soup
directions: Boil the ham in 2 cups water.
When ham is tender and broth is formed, add all ingredients (undrained), except cabbage.
Cook about 45 minutes.
Add cabbage and cook 15 minutes more.
If tangy, add a touch of sugar.

title: pineapple rise
directions: Drain and grind or puree pineapple.
Add half sweetener. Remove 1 cup of puree and sprinkle gelatin over the top of it to soften.

Combine just egg yolks and rest of the sugar and cook over low heat in double boiler, stirring until mixture thickens. Add the gelatin mixture and stir until the gelatin dissolves. Cool to lukewarm and add remaining puree.
Whip egg whites and salt in a bowl until foamy.
Fold in whipped cream.
Gently fold in pineapple mixture.
Pour into mold or oblong pan.
Chill until firm, about 2 hours.
Garnish with whipped cream and strawberries.

title: divinity candy
directions: Mix the first three ingredients in heavy saucepan and cook on high heat until mixture forms a hard ball when dropped in cold water.
Beat egg whites until they form soft peaks.
Add sugar, water and Karo syrup mixture to beaten egg whites.
Continue to beat until candy will stand up when dropped from a spoon.
Add vanilla and pecans.

title: hot peppers in oil
directions: Remove seeds from peppers while dry, then wash in cold water. Boil 1 quart of salad oil with the 2 gallons peppers.
Let boil and stir until all have been under oil.
Set off fire.
Pack in jars.

title: crock-pot roast beef and potatoes
directions: In large crock-pot, cover roast with water. Cook all night or all day. After roast is done, put broth in kettle with potatoes that have been peeled and halved. Add 1/4 cup ketchup and cook until very tender. Pour back into crock-pot and add rest of ketchup.

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Combine sugar, butter and milk; bring to a rolling boil (soft-ball 235°). Boil 5 minutes over medium heat. Remove from heat; stir in peanut butter until melted. Add Marshmallow Creme, nuts and vanilla. Beat until well blended. Pour into a greased 13 x 9 pan. Cool; cut in squares.

title: fudgy oatmeal bars
directions: Heat oven to 350 degrees.
Grease a 15 1/2 x 10 1/2 pan (I used cooking spray).
Mix brown sugar and butter together, add eggs and tsp. vanilla.
Beat until smooth.
Mix flour, soda, salt and oats together and mix into batter.
Reserve 1/3 of oatmeal mix.
Press remaining mixture in pan and spread to sides of pan and up sides a little way.
Heat chocolate chips, sweetened condensed milk, and butter in a 2 qt saucepan over low heat, stirring constantly until melted.
Remove from heat.
Stir in nuts, vanilla and salt.
Spread over oatmeal mixture in pan.
Drop reserved oatmeal mixture by rounded teaspoon on chocolate mixture. Bake until golden brown, about 25 to 30 minutes.
While warm cut into bars.............Yummy!

title: light fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each.
Add flour and orange juice alternately. Use one cup of the flour to sprinkle nuts and fruit.
Add them to mixture.
Add vanilla.
Put in pan, greased and lined with brown paper.
Place in slow oven about 250° to 275° for about 2 hours or until tests done.

title: date roll candy
directions: Combine sugar, salt, milk and butter.
Boil until sugar is dissolved.
Add dates and stir constantly until soft ball occurs when tested in a cup of water.
Remove from fire and cool.
Beat until creamy and thick; add nuts, mixing thoroughly.
Pour onto cold wet cloth and knead until smooth.
Shape into roll and chill until firm.
Cut into thin slices.

title: sour cream cookies
directions: Cream the sugar and shortening. add eggs and sour cream.
Mix. Add dry ingredients. Dough will be stiff.
Add nuts, if you like. Drop on a greased cookie sheet. Decorate with colored sugar.
Bake at 350° for 10 minutes until set and very lightly browned.
You can use egg substitute or 4 egg whites in place of the eggs.

title: codfish ala vizcaina
directions: Soak codfish night before in water.
Drain and boil in 2 liters of water for 15 minutes.
Shred codfish.
Make sure you take all bones out.
In large skillet alternate layers of potatoes, codfish and onions.
Add the rest of the ingredients. Bring to a boil, then simmer for 30 minutes or until potatoes are done.

title: sole poached with italian vegetables
directions: You can use orange roughy, flounder or cod.

title: chocolate pound cake
directions: Preheat oven to 325°.
Grease, and instead of flour, coat pan with cocoa powder, a 10-inch tube pan.
Cream butter and shortening.
Gradually beat in sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating thoroughly after each.
Combine flour and dry ingredients. Add alternately with milk.
Add vanilla and beat until smooth. Bake for 1 hour and 25 minutes.
Next day serving is best.

title: oatmeal cookies
directions: Put raisins in saucepan; cover with water and boil about 15 minutes.
Drain and reserve 1 cup of raisin water.
Add baking soda to the cup of raisin water and let cool.
Cream sugar and shortening; add eggs and oatmeal.
Sift flour, cloves, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt together and add to mixture with water.
Add raisins and walnut meats.
Drop by teaspoonfuls onto a greased baking sheet.
Bake at 350° until done.
Makes about 6 dozen cookies.

title: buttery cut-out sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar together until fluffy.
Beat in egg and vanilla.
Sift together flour and powder.
Stir into butter mixture; blend well.
Chill dough thoroughly.
Roll out small portions of dough.
Cut with cookie cutters.
Place an inch apart on lightly greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes or until brown at edges.
Remove to a rack to cool.
Icing with a powdered sugar/milk mixture.
Use food coloring to be creative.

title: pumpkin pie
directions: Get dough, toss it, bake is, sauce it, top it, make it.

title: chunky chicken noodle soup
directions: Combine first four ingredients in a Dutch oven; bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat, and simmer for 45 minutes.
Remove chicken from broth, and cool.
Strain broth; discard celery leaves and solidified fat.
Return broth to Dutch oven; add green onions and next 8 ingredients.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes.
Bone and chop chicken; add to broth.
Cook 5 more minutes.
Discard bay leaf.
Sprinkle soup with pepper, if desired.
Yield 7 cups.

title: jailhouse cake
directions: When the carrots are almost done, add raisins and sugar, along with cinnamon, allspice, nutmeg and ginger, with some salt.
When the raisins are tender; cool.
Add enough flour to make a slightly stiff cake batter, along with baking powder and soda to the batch. Add lots of nuts if you have enough, but walnuts are best.
Cook in a slow oven in greased and floured loaf pans for at least 1 hour. If you can't tell when it is done, don't start.
You shouldn't be cookin'.
No fat, no eggs, no milk, no vanilla and no shortening. Wrap and freeze surplus.

title: nanny's zucchini appetizers
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Mix all ingredients together and spread in a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake until golden brown, about 25 minutes.
Cut into squares when cool.

title: garlic dip
directions: Soften cheeses to room temperature.
Blend all ingredients until smooth.
Serve on Ritz crackers or with potato chips.

title: easy peanut butter cookies
directions: Preheat oven to 375°.
Mix milk and peanut butter until smooth. Add biscuit mix and vanilla, mix well.
Roll into 1-inch balls. Roll in sugar.
Place 2 inches apart on lightly greased pan.
Mark with fork.
Bake 6 minutes or until lightly brown (do not overbake).
Cool.

title: low calorie dessert
directions: Mix
all ingredients together and place in refrigerator to cool.
(Mix pistachio pudding as it came from package).

title: kentucky wonder cake
directions: Combine and mix ingredients.
Cook in Bundt pan, tube pan or flat pan at 300° for at least 1 hour.
Top with glaze.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Pour melted margarine in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Layer bread, cheese and ham twice.
Beat eggs and add milk and salt.
Pour over bread mixture.
Cover with foil and refrigerate overnight. Uncover and place in 350° heated oven for 1 hour.
(You may also use crisp bacon or sausage.)

title: cheese ball
directions: Blend 3 cheeses together and coat with pecans.
Dip and eat with desired crackers.

title: sugar cream pie
directions: Add all ingredients together with milk and butter, melted. Cook like pudding. Pour into baked pie shell. Sprinkle with nutmeg and bake for 10 minutes at 350°.

title: tomato hot stuff
directions: Peel and chop tomatoes.
Chop peppers and onions.
Mix chopped vegetables in a heavy vessel.
Add remaining ingredients and boil slowly for at least 2 hours or until desired thickness.
Watch closely to prevent burning.
Pack in pint jars and seal.

title: mock champagne
directions: Pour one of each in a punch bowl.
Freeze juice for ice cubes. Make as much or as little as you need.

title: lisa's snap beans
directions: Drain snap beans and place in a baking dish; mix brown sugar, margarine, soy sauce, and garlic powder; pour over beans. Place bacon on top and bake at 350° for 45 minutes or until done.

title: egg and tomato sandwich
directions: Mix egg, tomato, salt and pepper together.
In frying pan, melt butter and add egg.
Mix.
When egg is cooked, lay cheese on top, just to melt a little.
Place on toast with mayonnaise or butter.

title: banana fritters
directions: *Great opportunity to save bananas heading for the garbage.

title: butterscotch fingers
directions: Mix and
bake 30 minutes in 350° oven.
Cook in greased pan, 5 x
8-inches.
Cut
into 1-inch pieces and roll in powdered sugar while still hot.
Cool.

title: ice ring for punch bowl
directions: Boil water one minute.
Cool to room temperature.
Pour cooled water into 6 cup ring mold.
Freeze.
Arrange mint leaves in mold as desired.
Add remaining water to fill mold.
Freeze. Remove mold from freezer and set at room temperature five minutes before adding to punch bowl.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: The night before serving, grease a 9 x 13-inch baking dish. Place the bread cubes in the dish.
Top with sausage and then the grated cheese.
Combine eggs, milk, salt and mustard; pour over the ingredients in the baking dish.
Cover with aluminum foil and refrigerate overnight.

title: quick homemade vegetable soup
directions: In a 4 or 5-quart pan, brown ground beef, onion and garlic over medium heat for 5 to 8 minutes; drain fat.
Add tomatoes, broth, water, oregano, basil and pepper.
Bring to a boil; lower heat and simmer, partially covered, for 10 minutes.
Add vegetables and pasta.
Cook, uncovered, for 10 to 12 minutes.
Add parsley.
Makes 4 servings.

title: cherry-o cream cheese pie
directions: Mix 1st three ingredients together to make 9-inch crumb crust. Let cream cheese soften to room temperature, then whip until fluffy.
Add condensed milk slowly.
Beat until well-blended.
Add lemon juice and vanilla; blend well.
Pour into chilled prepared crumb crust.
Chill 2 to 3 hours.
Pour can of cherry pie filling over top and serve.
Makes one 9-inch pie.

title: pizzania
directions: Cook spaghetti as directed on box, drain and set aside.
In a skillet cook onion and green pepper; add hamburg and cook thoroughly.
Add sauce and simmer.
Mix Ricotta cheese with spaghetti, then add hamburg mixture, mixing thoroughly.
Pour half into a greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Put on one layer of Provolone cheese, then pour in the rest and add another layer of cheese. Put into 350° oven until cheese starts to bubble.

title: tropical coconut fried shrimp
directions: Thaw shrimp if frozen.
Measure 1 1/2 cups flour; set aside. In a 1-quart mixing bowl, combine the remaining 1 1/2 cups flour, milk, baking powder, curry powder and salt.
Place reserved flour and coconut in 2 separate shallow pans.
Dredge shrimp in flour, dip in bowl, then roll in coconut.
Fry in hot oil at 350° until coconut is golden brown.
Drain on paper towel before transfering to warming tray.
Serve hot with Sweet and Sour sauce.
Makes 6 to 8 servings.
Tail section may be left on for easier handling.

title: authentic louisiana jambalaya
directions: Saute onions, celery and bell pepper until brown.
Add garlic, stewed tomatoes, Ro-Tel tomatoes, salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce to taste, water, rice and chosen meat.
Let come to a boil. Cover and cook 25 minutes or until rice is tender and liquid is reduced.

title: irish bread
directions: Sift flour, baking powder and salt.
Mix sugar, margarine, eggs, caraway seed, raisins and milk.
Put into loaf pan.
Melt butter.
Pour on top of mixture and sprinkle with sugar.

title: hamburger meal
directions: Divide hamburger into 4 sections.
Peel, slice and halfway cook potatoes in saucepan and drain.
Slice onion.
Cut four 10-inch squares of foil.
Place equal shares of potatoes, onions, salt and pepper in foil.
Pour on small amount of A. 1.
Add hamburger patties to the top of potatoes and onions.
Salt and pepper.
Add more steak sauce, then seal tinfoil tightly and bake in oven at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: a.b.c. dip (almonds, bacon, cheese)(serves 8)
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix lightly.
Serve with shredded wheat crackers.

title: cherry tomatoes with feta and parsley
directions: Combine cheese, parsley and 1 tablespoon milk in a food processor; process until smooth, adding more milk, if mixture is too stiff.
Cut off and discard the top quarter of each tomato. Scoop out the seeds with a melon baller.
Fill the tomatoes with the cheese-parsley mixture.
Decorate each with a parsley leaf. These can be refrigerated for several hours, but brought back to room temperature before serving.

title: buttermilk pie
directions: Beat eggs.
Add milk and vanilla.
Add sugar, flour and melted butter.
Mix well.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Use unbaked pie shells.
Makes 2 pies.
This is really a good pie.

title: red beans and rice #3
directions: Cook beans about 4 hours on low heat.
When very tender, add sliced sausage for last 30 to 40 minutes.
Serve over rice.

title: pecan-pie-cake
directions: Reserve 2/3 cup cake mix.
Melt oleo and add remaining cake mix and 1 egg.
Mix.
Put into large Pyrex dish and bake at 350° until done.
While cake is baking, mix other ingredients (Karo, eggs, 2/3 cup reserved cake mix, brown sugar and vanilla).
Pour over first mixture; sprinkle top with crushed pecans.
Bake for another 30 minutes.
Um Um Good.

title: porcupine balls
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Thoroughly mix all ingredients in bowl. Shape meat into small balls (will be twice as big when done). Place the balls on a cookie sheet and bake in oven for 20 to 30 minutes.
Reduce oven heat to 300° and remove meatballs.
Put meatballs in deep baking dish and pour tomato sauce or mushroom sauce over them.
Bake for 45 minutes.

title: carrot cake with cream cheese frosting
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in a bowl; stir well and set aside.
Combine sugar and oil; stir well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well, with a wire whisk, after each addition.
Stir in carrots and next 4 ingredients.
Add flour mixture; stir well.

title: chopped spinach casserole
directions: *Sprinkle Velveeta cheese (shredded) on top (optional).

title: cream cheese puffs
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients; mix well.
Unroll crescent rolls; leave every two attached, forming four rectangles.
Spread each rectangle with 1/4 of cream cheese mixture, carefully spreading to edges.
Beginning with a long side, roll up each rectangle in jelly roll fashion; slice each roll into 6 pieces.
Coat with pecans, pressing pecans into dough; place on ungreased baking sheets.
Bake at 375° for 20 minutes or until golden brown. Yields 2 dozen appetizers.

title: hot chicken casserole
directions: Mix the first 9 ingredients in large baking dish (mix lightly; don't mix so much that you crush the chicken).
Combine potato chips and cheese and sprinkle on top of chicken mixture.
Chill overnight.
Bake in hot oven, 400°, until bubbly, about an hour. Good for company!
The work's done the day before it's served.

title: impossible pie
