directions: Put all ingredients in blender for 30 seconds on high or until thoroughly mixed.
Bake 30 minutes in pie pan in 400° oven.

title: spaghetti sauce
directions: In large heavy pan, saute in oil, onions, green pepper and garlic buds.
Remove from pan and then brown ground beef. Sprinkle lightly with salt and garlic powder while cooking.

Drain all fat, then add cooked onions, garlic and pepper and 5 ounces pepperoni, stewed tomatoes, tomato sauce, tomato paste, mushrooms, 1 paste can of water (or more), 3 pinches of oregano, 2 pinches of basil, 1 pinch thyme, 1 bay leaf (take out after 1 hour), 2 tablespoons sugar and 1/2 cup grated Parmesan and simmer uncovered 2 hours or more on low heat.
Stir occasionally.
Makes 4 quarts of sauce.

title: pumpkin cake
directions: Beat first 5 ingredients well.
Sift together flour, baking powder, soda, salt, nutmeg, cloves and cinnamon and add.
Fold in nuts and raisins.
Bake at 325° in greased and floured 10-inch tube pan, 9 x 13-inch pan or muffin tins*.
Bake 1 1/2 hours (less for muffins).
Sprinkle with powdered sugar and serve warm or cool and frost.

title: blender chocolate mousse
directions: Combine chocolate, sugar and eggs in blender container.
Add hot milk and brandy.
Process on medium speed until smooth.
Pour into dessert dishes.
Chill for 1 hour.
Garnish with whipped cream.
Serves 6.

title: coconut pie
directions: Mix all ingredients; pour into greased Pyrex dish.
Must be deep dish.
Bake at 300° for 40 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Pack into greased 9 x 5 x 3-inch loaf pan.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Unmold.
Serve hot or cold.
For catsup-topped loaf, spread 3 tablespoons catsup over.

title: ono spaghetti
directions: Brown onion and ground beef.
Add chopped green pepper, chorizo
and
mushrooms.
Stir
in	sauce
mix,
2 cans tomato sauce,
3 tomato sauce cans of water and the tomato soup.
Add salt
and pepper to taste.	Simmer for 20 to 30 minutes.
Pour spaghetti sauce over noodles.
Ono!

title: easy mints
directions: Combine butter and water.
Place over low heat until butter melts.
Add salt, food coloring and peppermint.
Gradually add sugar, blending well.
Knead until smooth.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Mix
the
apples
with
lemon juice and 1 tablespoon of cinnamon.
Put apples into bottom of a 9 x 13-inch glass dish. Spread
flat.
Sprinkle
dry
cake
mix
evenly
over
apples. Sprinkle
cinnamon
over
mix
and
drizzle oleo over the top. Cover
dish with aluminum foil and place in a 350° oven.
Bake 20 minutes
or until apples are bubbly.
Remove foil and bake 30 minutes more or until top is brown and apples are tender.

title: easy caramel rolls
directions: Butter a 9 x 13-inch pan. Add chopped nuts.
Place dinner rolls on top of nuts. Sprinkle pudding over rolls.
Melt margarine or butter with brown sugar.
Pour over rolls.
Cover pan with foil.
Put in a cold oven overnight.
In the morning, remove from oven and remove foil. Preheat oven to 375°.
Bake approximately 20 minutes and turn out on serving plate.

title: hot milk cake
directions: Heat milk and butter, then add to other ingredients.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour in tube pan.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Combine cranberries and sugar and set aside.
Dissolve jello in boiling water, then add cold water, lemon juice, cinnamon and cloves.
Chill until thickened partially.
Add cranberries, orange and nuts.

title: yam pie
directions: Melt
butter
and blend with sugar to mashed yams until very creamy.
Add
eggs and beat until smooth; add salt, milk, vanilla and cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: stuffed portabello mushrooms
directions: In large skillet, melt butter.
Baste mushroom caps with butter and place on baking sheet.
Baste inside of caps with butter.
In skillet with remainder of butter, saute vegetables. When about half done, add chicken and finish sauteing, adding Worcestershire Sauce.
Spoon filling into caps.
Top with a liberal amount of your favorite type of shredded cheese. Either in oven or on the grill, heat mushrooms just until cheese melts, then serve warm.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Mix and cool for at least 10 minutes.
Pour on top of mixture in baking dish.
Chill well before serving.

title: angel food
directions: Beat egg whites with salt until frothy.
Add cream of tartar; beat stiff, but not dry.
Fold in sugar, 3 tablespoons at a time, then flour, which has been sifted once, then measured and sifted 3 more times.
Lastly, add vanilla.
Pour into angel food cake pan and bake at 300° to 325° for 1 to 1 1/4 hours.

title: japanese fruit cake
directions: Cream butter and add sugar gradually.
Add eggs, beating after each addition.
Mix and sift dry ingredients and add to batter alternately with milk.
Add vanilla.
Divide batter into two parts.
Bake two plain layers. Into the other half put raisins and spices.
Stir well and bake two spice layers.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
When stacking the layers, begin with a spice layer and then a plain layer.
Use the following filling between layers.

title: basic souffle recipe
directions: Make a white sauce of melted butter, flour and milk.
Beat egg yolks until thick and lemon colored.
Add to the white sauce. Beat the egg whites until stiff, but not dry.
Fold into the white sauce-yolk mixture.
Bake in an ungreased casserole at 325°, starting with a cold oven, for 1 hour.
Remove immediately for eating or it will collapse.
Serves 4.

title: buttered peas and radishes
directions: Cook peas as directed on package. Shortly before end of cooking time, add radishes and continue cooking until radishes are heated through. Don't overcook or radishes will lose their crispness and color. Drain. Add salt and butter and stir until melted. Makes 4 servings.

title: creamed cabbage soup
directions: In a large soup kettle or Dutch oven, combine broth, celery, cabbage, onion and carrot; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; cover and simmer for 15 to 20 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: taco pie
directions: Brown beef and drain.
Add taco seasoning and simmer for 5 to 10 minutes.
Lay rolls flat in baking dish and spoon beef mixture over them.
Spread sour cream, then the cheese.
Crush Doritos and sprinkle on top.
Bake at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: english sally lund bread
directions: In a mixing bowl, dissolve yeast in very warm water.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Beat until smooth (100 strokes).
Cover and let rise 1 hour.
Beat down and pour into greased 10-inch tube pan.
Let rise to within 1-inch of top of pan (45 minutes).
Heat oven to 350° (moderate).
Bake 45 or 50 minutes.
Serve hot. Makes 16 servings.

title: baked egg casserole
directions: Crumble the bread in bottom of a 9 x 13 pan. Sprinkle chopped ham, sausage, bacon or chicken over bread. Mix the eggs with the milk and dry mustard. Pour over bread and meat. Sprinkle with the cheese. Then place slices of American cheese over entire pan. Let stand 3 to 4 hours or overnight in the refrigerator. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: sauteed green peppers
directions: Saute green peppers in butter in a covered skillet over low heat for 15 minutes.
Remove cover and cook until brown.
Season with salt, pepper and Worcestershire sauce.

title: pecan roll
directions: Combine
marshmallow cream, powdered sugar and vanilla. Mix well by
hand.
Mixture will be very dry.
Shape into five 4 x 1 inch rolls.
Chill 2 to 3 hours.
Put caramels and water in top of
double
boiler.
Dip
rolls in melted caramels and then roll in pecans.
Chill 1 hour.
Cut into slices.

title: chocolate-cherry cake
directions: Mix all together and place in a 9 x 13-inch pan (or use Bundt pan) for 40 to 45 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: king ranch casserole
directions: Cut and debone chicken into bite sizes. Place chicken on top of layered chips in large casserole dish. Mix soup and sauce; pour onto chicken and chips. Bake at 375° for 35 to 45 minutes, until bubbly. Place cheese and onion on top until melts. Serve.

title: sherbet punch
directions: Put in punch bowl with ice.

title: pat's five cup fruit salad
directions: Drain fruit slightly.
Stir all ingredients together. Refrigerate overnight for best results.

title: fresh apricot sorbet
directions: Peel apricots.
Remove stones from fruit; puree fruit in blender.
Stir in lemon juice.
Add rum and ginger.
In saucepan, cook water and sugar over low heat.
When sugar is dissolved, bring to full boil and simmer about 5 minutes.
Remove syrup from heat; chill.
Combine syrup and apricot mixture.
Freeze in ice cream maker.
Best eaten soon after it is made.

title: macaroni and cheese
directions: Cook macaroni until tender and drain.
Grate cheese and mix with macaroni while still hot.
Add butter, salt, pepper and paprika.
Stir in sweet milk and pour into casserole.
Sprinkle lightly with paprika.
Bake at 375° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: no knead rich dinner rolls
directions: Scald milk; combine with shortening, sugar and salt.
Cool to lukewarm by adding water.
Add yeast; mix well.
Blend in egg and add slowly flour.
Mix until dough is well blended and soft.

title: chicken pie
directions: Layer chicken in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Mix soup and broth.
Pour over chicken.
Add mixed vegetables.
Mix Bisquick and milk and pour over all.
Top with melted butter.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour. Good leftover, also freezes well.

title: cranberry mold
directions: Spray "Pam" into Tupperware (or other) mold.
Freeze overnight.

title: pizza casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.
Crumble sausage into medium skillet; cook over medium heat until browned, stirring occasionally.
Remove sausage and drain on paper towels.
In large, lightly greased casserole dish, layer on half noodles, one half sausage, and one half remaining ingredients.
Repeat with second layer of noodles, the sausage and remaining ingredients, reserving several pepperoni slices to garnish top.
Bake 35 to 40 minutes. Serve immediately.
Refrigerate leftovers.

title: corn fritters
directions: In a large mixing bowl, combine all ingredients except vegetable oil. Set aside for 20 minutes.
Heat the oil in skillet. Drop one teaspoonful of mixture for each fritter.
Cook until golden brown (without turning), about 1 minute.
Remove fritters with slotted spatula, allowing oil to drip off, putting cooked fritters onto paper towel.
Makes about 20 fritters.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Saute onions and green pepper until almost tender.
Stir together with remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: carrots
directions: Peel and slice carrots into microwavable casserole dish.
Cut up onions on top of carrots.
Cut up margarine into 4 to 5 pats on top of carrots and onions.
Spread sugar over top.
Salt as you would any vegetable.
Do not stir.
Microwave on High 10 to 15 minutes.
Stir carrots and microwave another 10 to 15 minutes or until done.

title: classic macaroni and cheese
directions: Saute vegetables in margarine until tender.
Add process cheese spread and milk; stir over low heat until process cheese spread is melted.
Stir in macaroni.
Spoon into 2-quart casserole; sprinkle with Parmesan cheese.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Top with remaining process cheese spread; continue baking until process spread begins to melt.
Makes 6 servings. (Can also be done in the microwave.)

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Do not mix with electric mixer.
Mix flour, sugar, soda and salt together.
Beat eggs and add to oil.
Add apples and nuts to flour mixture and add eggs and oil; mix well.
Batter will be very thick.

title: barbecue baked beans
directions: Pour beans into casserole dish; add steak sauce, mustard and ketchup, mixing well.
Add brown sugar and bacon pieces.
Place in oven for 45 minutes at 375°.
Bake with a cover.
Cool 5 minutes and serve.
Serves approximately 4 to 6 people.

title: brown sugar syrup
directions: Place sugar, salt and water in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil, cover and simmer 10 minutes.
Remove from heat and add vanilla. Serve warm.

title: butterscotch brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Blend cake mix, eggs and melted margarine to form dough.
Stir in butterscotch brownies.
Spread in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Sprinkle with powdered sugar.
Cut into squares.

title: cheese ball
directions: Cut up onions and meat into small pieces and stir into softened cream cheese.
Add remaining ingredients.
Form into a ball and roll in pecans.
Chill.
Serve with crackers.

title: stuffed bell peppers
directions: Boil bell peppers for 20 minutes.
Boil 1 cup water and add the rice and simmer for 30 to 40 minutes.
Fry the Vege Burger and mix rice and Vege Burger.
Put square Jack cheese in bottom of each pepper.
Fill peppers with rice and burger.
Place strip of Jack cheese on top of each pepper.
Place in oven at 325° for 20 minutes.
Goes good with fruit salad and lima beans.

title: connie's pumpkin cake
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in bowl.
Combine next 4 ingredients in second bowl.
Combine both mixtures.
Bake in greased tube pan at 350° for 1 hour or until done.

title: quick cobbler
directions: Melt butter in pan.
Pour in sugar, milk and flour mixture. Next, drop in pie filling by tablespoon.
Bake at 350° approximately 30 to 45 minutes.

title: baked beans
directions: Bake at 350° for 2 hours.

title: mexican cornbread
directions: Bake until done at 350°.

title: broccoli dip
directions: Cook and drain frozen broccoli.
Saute onion in butter until soft.
Add the rest of the ingredients and cook until everything is hot.
Serve on cocktail bread.

title: cucumber dip
directions: Mix all ingredients except mayonnaise and cream cheese and set for 1 hour. Add cream cheese and enough mayonnaise for good dip consistency. Serve with Wheat Thins or other crackers.

title: banana slush
directions: Put bananas and lemonade in blender.
Mix all the ingredients (except ginger ale) together and freeze.
Remove from freezer about 2 or 3 hours.
Add 5 quarts of ginger ale when ready to serve.

title: austin's hamburgers
directions: Put all your stuff together and eat it.

title: tomato soup
directions: Put 3 quarts water in large saucepan.
Add meat, bones, bay leaves and peppercorns.
Cover and let boil for 1 or 2 hours.
Add tomatoes and carrots; cook 1 hour.
Add 1 tablespoon flour to sour cream and mix.
Make sure soup is bubbly before adding sour cream mix; stir to mix well.
Cover and simmer 1 hour.

title: banana bread
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Bake in 325° oven in greased loaf pan for 1 hour.
Bread is done when tester is dry.
Can add chopped nuts if desired.

title: cinnamon ornaments(this recipe is not edible)
directions: Combine spices in bowl, blend well.
Stir in applesauce. Dough will be stiff.
Roll dough 1/4-inch thick on cookie sheet. Cut out shapes with cookie cutters.
Remove and discard extra dough.
Let dry for 4 to 5 days, do not cover.
Store in airtight container or bag.

title: deviled ham dip
directions: Mix the ingredients and serve with crackers or chips.

title: sour cream gazpacho
directions: Combine 1 cucumber, garlic, 1 cup sour cream and 1 cup broth in blender and blend until smooth.
Continue until all ingredients are blended.
Combine and add vinegar and salt.
Chill and serve topped with toasted almonds.

title: potato casserole
directions: Grease 9x13 inch dish.
Thaw hash browns, enough to separate and spread in dish.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Saute butter and onions in pan; remove from heat.
Add soup, cheese and sour cream. Pour on potatoes.
Cover and bake 30 minutes at 375°.
Uncover and bake additional 30 minutes.

title: acorn squash
directions: Place squash
cut
side down in glass baking dish.
Add small amount of
water, about 1 inch in pan.
Bake at 325° for approximately
minutes
or
until
partially soft.
Remove water from
pan;
turn
squash
cut side up in pan.
Fill each half
with 1/4 cup applesauce; sprinkle with cinnamon.
Return to oven; continue baking until done.
Makes 2 servings.

title: beef and potato loaf
directions: Cover 4 quart greased casserole dish with thinly sliced potatoes.
Sprinkle onion salt, pepper, salt and parsley flakes to taste.

title: fruit pizza
directions: Bake sugar cookies on pizza pan; cool.

title: apple walnut cake
directions: Preheat oven to 350 degrees.

title: chocolate mayonnaise cake
directions: Heat oven to 350°. In a bowl mix flour, salt and cocoa, set aside. In another bowl mix mayonnaise, sugar and vanilla. Add flour mixture to mayonnaise mixture. In measuring cup mix 3/4 cup water with the baking soda. Pour into mayonnaise mixture and stir. This will foam up a bit and may look lumpy. Pour batter into a 9 x 13 pan or 2 round 8 inch pans and bake for 30 minutes or until a toothpick inserted comes out clean. Cool and frost.

title: bread pudding
directions: Grease a 6 x 9-inch pan.
Combine all ingredients, except bread.
Pour milk mixture into pan and add bread, soaking it. Sprinkle with cinnamon.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.

title: five hour stew
directions: Layer all ingredients, except tapioca, in Dutch oven.
Start with meat first.
Smear soup over top.
Sprinkle tapioca on top. Do not stir or mix.
Cover; bake at 250° for 5 hours.
No peeking.

title: creamy pineapple salad
directions: Combine gelatin with 2 cups boiling water; let cool.
Stir in milk and juice.
Chill until slightly thickened.
Fold in remaining ingredients.
Mold in a 2-quart mold or a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Chill until firm.

title: cold carrots
directions: Layer carrots, onions and pepper in a large bowl.

title: cabbage casserole
directions: Saute butter, onion, bell pepper, garlic, celery and ground meat.
Take off fire.
Season and add tomato sauce, Ro-Tel and cream of mushroom soup.
Add rice, chopped cabbage and water. Bake, covered, at 375° for 1 1/2 hours.
Stir often.

title: green tomato pickles
directions: Put tomatoes, onions and hot peppers in large pan.
Mix remaining ingredients together and then pour over the tomatoes; bring to a boil.
Remove from heat immediately and put in sterile jars and seal.

title: snickerdoodles
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Mix butter, shortening, sugar and eggs. Blend in flour, cream of tartar, soda and salt.
Shape dough into balls.

title: marinated t-bone steak
directions: Combine ingredients and pour over meat; let stand for 2 hours or more.
Add damp hickory chips to medium-hot coals.
Cook for 10 to 15 minutes, basting with small part of unused marinade.
Turn and cook for 15 to 20 more minutes with grill cover closed.
Serve with heated unused marinade.
Serves 4.

title: hot sausage balls
directions: Mix well and shape in small balls.
Place on cookie tin and bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: sausage casserole
directions: Mix together well.
Place in large casserole dish.
Bake at 350 degrees for 25 minutes.
Serve with garlic toast.

title: mother "groffs" gelatin fruit salad
directions: Mix gelatin and cold water and let stand 1/2 hour.
Add boiling water and sugar; cool.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: basic irish bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Coat sides of pan with melted margarine, then pour remainder in blender.
(While cooling, mix dry ingredients and raisins.)

title: charlene's cornbread
directions: Batter should be like thick pancake mix.
Heat butter.
Mix dry ingredients.
Stir in buttermilk and butter.
Add egg.
Bake at 450°.

title: easy beef meal
directions: Place sirloin tips in bottom of pan.
Add onion, peppers, mushrooms, stewed tomatoes and a sprinkle of salt and pepper. Spread the packages of gravy mix over ingredients to cover.
Drop in the beef bouillon cubes.
Add water to the point where the beef is covered.
Stir all ingredients occasionally as they cook.
Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.
Place beef dish over noodles or rice.

title: shrimp dip - appetizer("quick and easy")
directions: Mix all of the above well.
If too thick, add 1 tablespoon milk until creamy.
Refrigerate.
Serve with crackers.

title: pizza grilled cheese sandwiches
directions: Spread 1 teaspoon pizza sauce on each slice of bread.
Place cheese on top of four slices of bread.
Place six pepperoni slices on top of cheese.
Now, place your own favorite assorted toppings on top of pepperoni.
Cover with the other four slices of bread. Melt shortening in skillet on medium heat.
Place sandwich in skillet.
Cover for 2 to 4 minutes or until golden brown.
Cut sandwiches into 4 pieces.
Heat remaining pizza sauce and serve with sandwiches as a dip.

title: peach pound cake
directions: Grease a 10-inch tube pan with 2 tablespoons butter.
Sprinkle pan with 1/4 cup sugar.
Cream remaining butter; gradually add remaining sugar, beating well.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each addition.
Add vanilla and mix well.
Combine 2 3/4 cups flour, baking powder and salt; gradually add to creamed mixture, beating until well blended.
Dredge peaches with remaining 1/4 cup flour.
Fold peaches into batter.
Pour batter into prepared pan.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour and 10 minutes.
Remove from pan and cool completely.
Serves 16.
Calories:
14.5 grams.

title: mama matthew's japanese fruit cake(4 layer cake)
directions: Cream sugar and Crisco; add eggs one at a time, beating well after each egg.
Add flour one cup at a time, alternately with milk.
Add vanilla; add third cup of flour as last ingredient. Keeps cake from falling.
Bake 2 layers at 375° until light brown in a greased and floured cake pan.
Grease bottom of pan only.

title: scalloped salmon
directions: Crush saltines with a rolling pin; measure 2 cups crumbs. Melt butter over low heat.
Saute onion in butter.
Combine with saltines, parsley and pepper.
Place 1/2 the mixture in bottom of lightly oiled 8-inch pie pan.
Spoon in salmon.
Cover with remaining crumbs; add milk.
Bake in preheated 400° oven for 20 minutes.

title: quick pigs in a blanket
directions: Chop cabbage in medium pieces and spread in bottom of greased 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Brown meat and onion.
Stir in cooked rice and salt.
Put on top of cabbage.

title: seven minute frosting
directions: Combine first three ingredients in top of double boiler and beat with egg beater until ingredients are mixed.
Place over rapidly boiling water and beat constantly with beater 7 minutes or until frosting stands in peaks.
Remove from water.
Add extract. Fills and frosts top and sides of 2 (9-inch) layers.
If you want chocolate 7 minute frosting, fold in 3 squares melted unsweetened chocolate just before spreading.

title: pistachio bars
directions: In medium bowl, combine flour, margarine and 1/4 cup powdered sugar.
Mix with fork or pastry blender until well combined.
The mixture will be slightly crumbly.
Press evenly into bottom of 8 or 9-inch square shallow baking dish.
Bake at 400° for 8 minutes until just slightly brown at the edges or leave unbaked as desired.
In medium bowl of electric mixer, combine softened cream cheese, remaining 1/2 cup powdered sugar and 1/2 of the whipped topping.
Beat until fluffy and spread evenly on top of the flour crust.
Refrigerate while making pudding layer.

title: sausage muffins
directions: Mix together sausage, cheese, Bisquick, eggs and milk.
Spoon into mini-muffin pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: spinach-sausage quiche
directions: Brown sausage; drain.
Place in deep pie or casserole baking dish.
Heat spinach in microwave until thawed.
Spread over sausage.
Drain first.
Top with cheese.
Blend milk, eggs, Bisquick, salt and pepper.
Pour slowly over top of cheese.
Bake at 400° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Should be golden brown.
Let set for about 5 minutes before serving.

title: chicken parmesan
directions: Melt butter.
Dip chicken into butter then into mixture of dry ingredients.
Place in baking dish.
If any butter is left over, pour on chicken.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: mexican dinner(spanish rice)
directions: Brown rice in hot fat; add all ingredients.
Add enough water to cover rice.
Cover with lid; allow to simmer until rice is tender, about 30 minutes.
Remove lid; continue to simmer until rice is allowed to dry out.
Do not stir often or rice will become mushy.

title: hamburger-baked bean dish
directions: Fry hamburger with green pepper and onion; drain fat.
Combine the rest of the ingredients with the hamburger.
Add salt, pepper and Worcestershire to taste.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in a Dutch oven or roaster.

title: pat's pineapple pound cake
directions: Cream Crisco, oleo and sugar.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one.
Add flour, sifted with baking powder, small amount at a time, alternating with milk.
Add vanilla, stir in pineapple and blend well.
Pour batter into greased and floured tube pan.
Place in cold oven at 325°.
Bake 1 1/2 hours.
Let stand in pan for 10 minutes, then remove carefully.

title: spinach lasagne
directions: Cook noodles as directed on package; drain.
Cook beef and onion until well done; drain.
Stir in spaghetti sauce and mushrooms; heat to boil.
Reduce heat to simmer.
Mix remaining ingredients except Mozzarella slices.
Pour small amount of sauce on bottom of 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Place 3 lasagne noodles on top of sauce.
Spread cheese mixture on lasagne.
Top with a layer of Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat this step with remaining ingredients.
Bake at 350° uncovered for 30 minutes or until bubbly.

title: egg noodles
directions: Beat eggs and whole egg until real pale.
Add baking powder and cold water, then flour, a little at a time until stiff.
Roll real thin and cut into strips.
Break into small pieces and drop into boiling chicken broth.
Boil about 5 minutes and add yellow food color.
Put lid on pot and let set until dinner is ready.

title: sausage pinwheels
directions: Divide tube of rolls into quarters.
Gently seal center seam of each quarter and shape into even rectangles.
Spread 1/4 pound of sausage over each quarter of dough.
Roll around length and slice.
Place pinwheels on cookie sheet and bake at 350°.
Makes about 45 pinwheels.

title: eastern chili
directions: Pressure cook pinto beans until done.
Fry hamburger and onion.
Mix ingredients (except chili powder) and simmer for 1/2 hour.
Add chili powder to taste.

title: vanilla caramel bars with chocolate chips
directions: Mix together cake mix, melted butter, egg and 1/3 cup evaporated milk.
Pat this mixture in a greased 9 x 13-inch cake pan.
Bake at 350° for 8 minutes.

title: irish potato cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs and beat well.
Sift together flour, cocoa, baking powder and spices.
Add milk and flour mixture alternately.
Beat well.
Add hot mashed potatoes, chopped pecans and vanilla last.
Bake in 3 (9-inch) layer pans at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes or in Bundt or tube pan at 350° for 1 hour.

title: apple cake
directions: Combine butter and sugar.
Add eggs.
Add (sifted together), flour, nutmeg, salt, cinnamon, soda and allspice.
Add apples. Bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: hot milk sponge cake
directions: Sift flour and baking powder into a bowl.
Beat eggs in separate bowl until thick.
Add sugar gradually, then add milk, margarine and vanilla that have been heated until a skim appears on top.
Gradually add flour.
Place into a greased 9 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 25 minutes or until toothpick comes out clean.

title: christmas sugar cookies
directions: Cream together margarine, shortening, sugar, eggs and vanilla. Mix flour, baking powder and baking soda and add to creamed mixture a little at a time, stirring together.
Refrigerate overnight.
Roll out dough and cut cookies.
Bake at 350° for 6 to 8 minutes.

title: sausage biscuits
directions: Mix cheese and sausage together.
Add Bisquick.
Roll into bite-size balls and bake at 350° until brown.

title: fried eggplant
directions: Peel and slice eggplant.
Mix flour, salt and pepper.
Cover eggplant with flour mixture.
Drop into hot skillet of oil and fry until brown on one side.
Turn and fry until crisp; remove from oil and drain.
Garnish with sliced red ripe tomatoes.

title: ground beef casserole
directions: Brown beef, onion, celery and pepper.
Mix together soups, sauces and rice.
Add to meat mixture.
Pour into baking dish and top with chow mein noodles.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.

title: crust for fried pies
directions: Mix thoroughly.
Roll dough into golf ball sizes and chill for approximately 15 minutes, then roll flat.
Cut out for desired pie sizes.
Delicious and tender.

title: trix mix
directions: Combine all ingredients in large bowl.
Serve as snack. Yield: 16 to 20 servings.

title: our grasshopper pie
directions: Mix the ingredients.
Press into a 9-inch pie pan.
Chill.

title: betty's good fudge
directions: Combine sugar, milk and butter; bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Boil mixture 4 minutes.
Remove from heat.
Add chocolate and Marshmallow Creme.
Beat until fudge thickens.
Add nuts.
Pour onto cookie sheet.
Cut into squares.
Makes about 3 pounds.

title: fruit cake
directions: Grease tube cake pan with butter and line pan with wax paper, then grease again.
Mix all ingredients, except wine and place in cake pan.
Bake in slow oven (about 300°) until browned and done to touch.
After completely cooled or even next day, pour wine over and let it soak while in cake tin.

title: salad dressing cake
directions: Mix all ingredients together using a spoon.
Bake in greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: orange gold cake with orange butter frosting
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add yolks, one at a time, beating constantly.
Beat in orange rind and juice.
Sift together dry ingredients; add alternately with milk, beating until smooth. Pour into greased and floured spring-form pan.
Bake at 375° for about 1 hour, until done.
Cool; remove from pan.

title: salmon lemon loaf
directions: Flake salmon.
Combine all other ingredients. Spoon into oiled quart loaf pan.
Bake at 350° uncovered with lemon slices over the top for 40 minutes.
Serve with a white mushroom or lemon sauce.

title: cherry crunch pie
directions: Mix flour, nuts, and oleo.
Spread and pat into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
Cool.
Beat cream cheese and powdered sugar.
Stir in Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled crust. Spread cherry pie filling over the top.
Set in refrigerator over night.

title: filled meat loaf
directions: Mix first 7 ingredients together with hamburg.
Make layer on bottom of pan.
Put filling mixture next.
Then hamburg on top. Cover with mushroom soup.
Bake 45 minutes at 350° or until it looks done on bottom.

title: dick buyck's lemon roll
directions: Bake at 375° for 20 minutes.
Fill with your favorite lemon filling.

title: chicken quesadillas
directions: Broil chicken in oven until done.
Cut it into strips.
Mix green pepper, onion, tomatoes and jalapenos together.
Put tortillas on baking sheet.
Spread mixture onto 1 side of each tortilla.
Sprinkle cheese over mixture.
Put tortillas in oven until cheese melts.
Place chicken strips on top of cheese and mixture.
Fold tortillas over.
Cut into 3 pieces.

title: the impossible cake
directions: In blender container, combine milk, sugar, biscuit mix, butter, eggs and vanilla.
Cover; blend on low speed for 3 minutes.
Pour into greased 9-inch round or square pan.
Let stand at room temperature for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle with coconut and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.
Cool on wire rack.
Yields 1 cake.

title: angel hair pasta with shrimp
directions: Saute peppers, onions and garlic in olive oil.
Add shrimp and heat through.
Cook pasta 1 minute.
Serve on heated plates.
Pasta on bottom, shrimp on top.

title: pecan pie bars
directions: Set aside 2/3 cup cake mix.
Mix remaining cake mix, butter and 1 egg.
Mix until crumbly.
Press in pan; bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Mix remaining and beat.
Pour over crust and add pecans and bake at 350° for another 30 to 35 minutes.
Cut into bars.

title: kaffee kunchen
directions: Cream butter and sugar; beat in egg yolks.
Sift dry ingredients; add alternately with milk a little at a time, beating after each addition.
Fold in egg whites.
Pour into greased 9 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle Topper over.
Bake at 350° about 30 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: vanilla pudding
directions: Combine pudding mix and warm water in top of double boiler; cook over boiling water, stirring constantly until thickened. Reduce heat; continue to cook over simmering water for 10 minutes, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add margarine.
Stir in egg slowly.
Return to heat; cook 1 minute longer, stirring constantly.
Remove from heat again and stir in vanilla.
Pour into serving dishes.

title: spaghetti carrettiera
directions: Brown garlic cloves slightly in oil in uncovered saucepan. Add basil,
tomatoes, salt and pepper. Cook over medium heat 15 minutes. Add sauce over al dente pasta (pasta should be in large hot bowl); mix. Add cheese to taste.

title: instant hot cocoa mix
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly and store in covered container. Use 1/4 heaping cup cocoa mix in 3/4 mug hot water.

title: spoon bread
directions: Bring water and salt to a boil. Stir in cornmeal for 1 minute. Remove from heat and add butter.
Beat well.
Add eggs and beat in milk.
Beat again and pour into hot buttered baking dish. Bake for 25 minutes in hot oven at 400° to 450°.
Serve from baking dish.

title: chocolate cookies(no bake)
directions: Bring to a boil over medium heat for 1 minute only the oleo, sugar and milk.
Add dry mixture to cooked wet mixture.
Mix well. Drop onto foil sheets with a tablespoon.
Let cool completely. Makes 3 dozen or more cookies.

title: baked beans
directions: Brown hamburger and onions.
In a baking dish, add baked beans, hot sauce, ketchup and brown sugar.
Mix well.
Drain fat from hamburger and add to the baked beans.
Cook at 325° for 45 minutes.

title: applesauce pecan bread
directions: Combine first 6 ingredients in large mixing bow.
Stir in nuts, egg and applesauce.
Pour into greased loaf pan and bake at 350 degrees for 1 hr.

title: circle home cookies
directions: Cream the shortening and sugar.
Add eggs, water and vanilla. Combine the flour, salt and soda and add to the creamed mixture.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook onion and celery until tender.
Put 1/2 of corn bread in bottom of dish.
Place cut up chicken on top of corn bread.
Mix onion, celery soup and broth together.
Pour over chicken and corn bread mixture.
Add rest of corn bread on top of this.
Bake at 350°.

title: chicken mediterranean
directions: Salt and pepper chicken.
Cook chicken in oil until brown on each side; drain fat.
Add to chicken the sauce, vinegar and olives; bring to a boil.
Reduce heat; simmer for 15 minutes.

title: dutch grape pie(germany)
directions: Remove skins and mash grapes and cook for 15 minutes.
Remove seeds, add skins and the sugar and butter.
Line pie pan with crust.
Sprinkle with 1 tablespoon flour.
Place mixture in crust, sprinkle the other tablespoon flour.
Cover with second crust. Bake in medium hot oven at 350° until crust is golden brown.

title: orange butter coffee cake
directions: Soften yeast in warm water.

Add sugar, salt, eggs, sour cream and melted butter. Stir. Add flour. Beat well. Let rise until double in bulk (about 2 hours). Knead on floured surface about 15 times. Roll half of the dough to a 12-inch circle. Brush with 1 tablespoon melted butter.
Sprinkle with half of the 3/4 cup toasted coconut, 3/4 cup sugar and grated orange rind.
Combine the 3/4 cup sugar, sour cream, orange juice and 1/4 cup butter. Boil 5 minutes, stirring constantly.
Pour hot mixture over rolls to cover all.
Sprinkle with 1/4 cup toasted coconut. Cut into 12 wedges.
Roll up, starting with wide end.
Place point side down in greased 9 x 13-inch pan. Repeat procedure with other half of the dough.
Let rise until light, about 1/2 hour.
Bake 30 minutes in a 325° oven.
Leave in pan.

title: egg nog
directions: Mix all ingredients in blender.

title: peach pie
directions: Melt oleo in casserole dish.
Mix sugar, flour and milk together.
Pour over melted oleo.
Place fruit on top.
If fresh fruit is used, sweeten with extra sugar.
Bake 1 hour at 350°.

title: orange biscuits
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder. Add orange rind. Cut in shortening. Add juice and sour cream. Roll to 3/4-inch on floured board. Cut and bake on nonstick cookie sheet 8 minutes at 425°. Cool on wire rack or serve warm. Good with orange marmalade.

title: peach cobbler
directions: Melt margarine in large baking dish.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Combine with milk and pour over margarine.
Do not stir!
Place peaches and syrup on top.
Bake at 350° until brown for 40 minutes.
Serves 10.

title: banana nut bread
directions: Cream oleo, sugar and eggs; add sifted flour, soda and salt, then add vanilla, bananas, buttermilk and nuts.
Mix well.
Bake in well-greased and floured bread pan or small loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes or until done.

title: round steak
directions: Tenderize both sides of the steak and cut into serving pieces. Salt and pepper to taste.
Brown both sides in hot oil.
Place in casserole dish.
Top each piece of steak with a slice of onion. Spoon soup and a half can of water over meat.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: german chocolate pound cake
directions: Cream sugar and shortening.
Add eggs, flavoring and buttermilk.
Sift together flour, baking soda and salt; add to mixture.
Mix well, then add chocolate that has been softened in a warm oven or in a double boiler.
Blend together well.

title: savory meat ball casserole
directions: Combine ground beef, pork sausage, bread crumbs, 1/3 cup Pet evaporated milk, chopped onion, chili powder and pepper.
Mix well. Shape by tablespoons into meat balls.
Brown.
Cover and cook 10 minutes.
Place in 2 1/2-quart casserole.

title: pineapple delite
directions: Add pineapple to jello and heat.
Cool to room temperature. Fold in Cool Whip.
Chill well at least 30 minutes.
Serves 4.

title: cohasset seafood supreme
directions: When we lived in this small fishing village, seafood was an inexpensive item, served several times a week and dressed up like this for company.

title: aunt linda's apple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Add spices to suit taste, such as allspice and cinnamon.
Mix all ingredients together.
Beat with mixer on medium speed for 2 minutes.
Pour in greased and floured tube pan and bake for 1 hour.

title: spanish rice casserole
directions: Brown hamburger with onion and drain.
Mix the rest of ingredients together and put in greased casserole dish.
Bake in 350° oven for 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours.
Do not cover dish and stir every half hour.

title: raspberry bars
directions: Cream margarine, shortening and sugar.
Mix in remaining ingredients.
Press half of mixture in bottom of 13 x 9-inch pan. Spread with jam.
Top with remaining crumbling mixture.
Press down lightly.
Bake at 400°
for 25 to 30 minutes.
Makes 3 dozen bars.

title: shrimp dip
directions: Soften cream cheese in bowl; add remaining ingredients, except shrimp, and blend well.
Add shrimp and then mix thoroughly.

title: homemade barbecue sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients; simmer 20 minutes.
Use as baste on meats on grill or in oven.

title: giant oatmeal spice cookies
directions: Sift flour with spices, salt and baking soda.
Set aside. Cream butter; add vanilla, both sugars and beat until creamy. Add eggs and beat on low speed.
Add sifted dry ingredients.
Stir in oats with a spoon.
Line two cookie sheets with aluminum foil (shiny side down).
Place 10 cookies on each sheet (1/4 cup each). Let stand 2 hours before baking.
Bake at 375° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Reverse sheets once during baking.
Cookies are soft when done.
Cool on racks.

title: black bean soup
directions: Sort and wash beans; place in a large Dutch oven.
Cover with water 2 inches above beans.
Let soak at least 8 hours.
Drain. Add chicken broth, 2 cups water, ham hocks, salt pork and bay leaf to beans; bring to a boil.
Cover, reduce heat and simmer 1 1/2 hours.

title: erika's cornbread
directions: Mix together. Spray pan with Pam lightly. Makes 12 muffins or 9 X 9 pan. Bake at 400° for 25 minutes (don't over cook).

title: tutti frutti ice
directions: You make up each package of Kool-Aid using 2/3 cup of sugar in each pitcher of Kool-Aid.
You pour the Kool-Aid in ice trays and freeze it.
After frozen, you put each kind of ice in glass and pour in some Sprite, then drink.

title: cream cheese pie
directions: Combine cream cheese, 1/3 cup sugar, 1 egg, vanilla and salt; blend until smooth and creamy.
Spread in pastry shell.
Sprinkle with pecans.
Combine remaining ingredients; beat until well blended.
Pour over cream cheese mixture and pecans.
Heat oven to 375° and bake 35 minutes.

title: hush puppies
directions: Mix and deep fry spoonfuls in hot grease.

title: stuffed mushrooms with spinach
directions: Brush mushroom caps with oil.
Place on baking sheet, round side up, and broil for 1 minute.
Blend spinach with cheese; fill mushroom caps.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and bake on greased cookie sheet at 375° for 10 minutes or until bubbly.
Serve immediately.
May be frozen and baked unthawed.
Serves 8.

title: spanish noodles
directions: Cube onions, peppers, mushrooms and pork chops.
Saute in 2 tablespoons butter.
Cook noodles and drain.
Mix with soups and rest of ingredients.
Put in 13 x 9-inch pan; top with cheese. Bake at 350° until cheese melts.
Serve.

title: pleasin' cheese 'n herb
directions: Blend all ingredients.
Yields 1-1/2 cups of dressing.

title: apple pie(sugar free)
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Place in a 9-inch pie pan with uncooked crust.
Dot with butter.
Cover with foil and poke holes in top.
Bake at 400°
for about 50 minutes, or until apples are tender.

title: coconut drop candy
directions: Mix sugar, milk, butter, coconut and pecans.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place a toothpick in each ball.
Place in refrigerator to chill.
Melt chocolate.
Dip chilled balls in chocolate and place on waxed paper to cool.
Ease toothpicks out of balls after they have been dipped in chocolate.
Yields 3 dozen.

title: norwegian brown sugar cookies
directions: Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs; beat well.
Mix in flour, salt and soda until well blended.
Stir in remaining ingredients. Drop by teaspoonfuls onto ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Yields 5 dozen.

title: potato puff(meal-in-one)
directions: Thaw and drain spinach.
Separate eggs.
Combine mashed potatoes, spinach, butter, seasonings and 4 egg yolks.
Beat 4 egg whites until stiff and fold gently into vegetable mixture. Gently place in a 1 1/2-quart oven casserole.
Bake at 375° for 30 to 40 minutes until puffed and golden.
Serves 6.

title: egg casserole
directions: Mix all together and bake in greased casserole at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: fruit salad with vanilla pudding
directions: Combine all the ingredients; let stand at least 4 hours before serving.

title: chicken taco casserole
directions: Blend sauce and soup. Stir in chicken and onion. Grease a 13 x 9 casserole. Put in 1/2 chips. Pour in chicken mixture. Put cheese on top and the rest of the chips. Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: sweet 'n sour chicken
directions: Brown chicken in oil.
Add garlic, green pepper and carrots; saute briefly.
Add bouillon, soy sauce, vinegar, sugar, ginger and pineapple with juice.
Simmer until time to serve.
Mix cornstarch with a little water and thicken.
Serve over rice.

title: sweet dills
directions: Drain pickles. Reserve	1/2
cup
juice. Add to rest of the ingredients.
Mix
well. Add pickles.
Refrigerate 3 days, at least.

title: bran-fruit muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400 degrees and prepare 12-cup muffin pan; lightly grease or spray with non-stick spray or line with paper baking cups.

title: "simply fine"(eggless, milkless, butterless cake)
directions: Put all ingredients in saucepan and bring to boil for 3 or 4 minutes; set aside.
When cooled to lukewarm, add flour sifted with baking soda.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: parmesan burgers(makes 4 servings)
directions: In bowl, mix beef and 1/4 cup steak sauce; shape into 4 patties.
Dip patties in egg, then coat with bread crumbs.

title: orange roughy with peppers(serves 2)
directions: Preheat oven to 275°.
Place fillets in shallow baking dish. Season with salt and pepper.
Sprinkle with basil, garlic and oregano.
Bake for 45 minutes.
Meanwhile, cook peppers and onion in olive oil until crisp-tender.
Arrange pepper mixture over fish and sprinkle with almonds.
Garnish with lemon.

title: potato and pumpkin casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Arrange pumpkin slices, potato slices and onion in a baking dish.
Combine half and half, wine, cheese and margarine in a bowl, mixing well; spoon over vegetables. Bake, covered, 40 minutes or until vegetables are tender.

title: applesauce muffins
directions: Put all ingredients into your mixing bowl and mix well.
Bake in muffin tins at 400° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cherry cheesecake cupcakes
directions: You will need 12 cupcake papers and 2 cupcake pans.

title: spinach noodles
directions: Knead together well. Divide dough into 4 parts and knead each part.
Roll thin and place to dry slightly.
Place layers on top of each other with a thin layer of flour between them.
Cut as you would noodles, wide, not fine.
Serve with tomato sauce and grated Parmesan and Romano cheeses.

title: cranberry spinach salad
directions: In medium saucepan, saut almonds in butter until lightly toasted. Remove and drain on paper towels. Toast sesame seeds in same pan. Remove and drain on paper towels. In large bowl, toss salad greens (washed and drained) with toasted almonds and cranberries. In a medium bowl, whisk together sesame seeds, poppy seeds, sugar, onion, vinegars and oil together. Top with greens just before serving.

title: seven-up cake
directions: Mix all ingredients.
Pour into 2 (8-inch) greased and floured cake pans or sheet cake pan.
Bake as directed at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: great grandma's caramel corn
directions: Boil sugar,
corn syrup and water until it forms a hard ball in	water.	Then
add
the	baking soda, butter and lemon extract. Pour over popped corn.
Mix and eat.

title: buttermilk cream pie(diabetic pie)
directions: Combine flour and margarine in bowl with fork.
Blend together.
Beat egg yolks and fructose together.
Add flour mixture and beat until well blended.
Beat in buttermilk and lemon juice.
Put in unbaked pie shell.
Bake at 425° for 10 minutes. Reduce temperature to 350° and bake 20 to 25 minutes or until filling is firm.
Allow to cool.

title: raspberry cheesecake pie
directions: Line unpricked pastry shell with a double thickness of aluminum foil.
Bake at 450° for 8 minutes or until lightly browned.
Cool on a wire rack.
Reduce heat to 350°.
In a blender, combine cottage cheese and milk; process until smooth. In mixing bowl, beat cream cheese and sugar until smooth.
Beat in cottage cheese mixture, flour and vanilla.
Beat in eggs just until blended.
Pour into pastry shell.
Sprinkle with 1/2 cup raspberries. Gently press berries into filling with back of spoon. Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
Cover with foil if browning too quickly. Cool for 1 hour; refrigerate for 1 hour.
Top with whipped cream and remaining berries.

title: tomatoes vinaigrette
directions: Arrange tomatoes in glass baking dish.
Shake oil, vinegar, oregano, salt, pepper, mustard and garlic in tightly covered jar. Pour over tomatoes.
Cover and refrigerate, spooning dressing over tomatoes occasionally, at least 2 hours.

title: sweet potato casserole
directions: Mix together first 7 ingredients and place in greased casserole dish; then mix remaining ingredients together and put on top sweet potatoes.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes.

title: prince charles soup
directions: Mix broth, tomatoes, sugar, salt and pepper in a 2-quart pan. Bring to boil.
Add garlic, if desired.
Simmer 10 minutes, uncovered.
Just before serving, add greens; stir.
Serve hot or cold.

title: teena's wassail
directions: Boil with apple juice and 1 liter of 7-Up.

title: cream gravy
directions: Set dial at 260° and boil down any remaining juices until only drippings remain.
Blend flour with drippings, stirring until well mixed and browned.
Add salt, pepper and paprika and slowly add milk, according to desired thickness or chicken broth and light cream.
Cook, stirring until thickened.
Add parsley to suit taste or mushrooms.

title: easy popovers
directions: Using a whisk or fork combine eggs
and
milk.
Stir in remaining ingredients and disregard
lumps.
Fill well-greased muffin tins 3/4 full.
Place in cold oven and bake at 450° for 25 minutes or until golden brown.

title: apple dumplings
directions: Combine sugar, water, cinnamon and nutmeg.
Cook to boiling. Add oleo and food coloring.
Make a dough of the flour, baking powder, milk and shortening.
Divide into 6 circles.
Put an apple in circle of dough.
Sprinkle with a little cinnamon-nutmeg and oleo.
Close dough around apple.
Place in pan and pour syrup over.
Bake at 375°
for 35 minutes.
Serve with milk or ice cream or as is.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Mix cream cheese and peanut butter together with hands.
Add sugar slowly, mixing ingredients with electric mixer.
Add whipped topping and continue beating with mixer until thoroughly combined. Pour into 2 pie crusts.

title: pumpkin bars
directions: Beat together eggs, sugar, oil and pumpkin.
Combine dry ingredients and add to pumpkin mixture.
Mix well.
Spread in ungreased 15 x 10 x 1-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: mississippi mud pie
directions: Mix together and put in a 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Bake for 15 minutes at 350°.

title: beef stroganoff
directions: Coat beef stew meat with flour and brown with chopped onion in small amount of oil.
Season with salt and pepper.
Add broth and soup and simmer for 30 minutes.
Serve with rice, noodles or mashed potatoes.

title: cheesy topping for veggies
directions: Mix together all ingredients except oleo and crumbs.
Cook vegetable (broccoli, cauliflower, Brussels sprouts or asparagus) until tender.
Place in casserole dish.
Pour cheese mixture over vegetable.
Mix bread crumbs and oleo, sprinkle over cheese.

title: onion patties
directions: In a mixing bowl, combine the dry ingredients.
Stir in milk, adding a little more if needed, to make a thick batter.
Mix in onion.
Heat oil in a deep fat fryer to 375°.
Drop batter by tablespoonfuls into oil and fry to a golden brown.
Turn and brown other side.
Drain on paper towels.
Serve warm.
(We just fry ours in a skillet and flip when brown.
Very good.)

title: sweet potatoes
directions: Cook and peel sweet potatoes.
Soak in butter for 5 minutes, then roll in brown sugar and nut mixture.
Pour remaining butter and brown sugar mixture over potatoes and bake.

title: pork schnitzel with mushroom sauce
directions: Flatten each pork chop lightly with a flat meat mallet to a uniform thickness.
Place flour on a plate.
Place the eggs in a shallow dish.
Place seasoned bread crumbs in another shallow pan. Coating both sides each time, dip a pork chop in the flour first (shake off excess), then the eggs (coat well), then the bread crumbs.
Place on another plate until all 6 chops are breaded. Heat 1 tablespoon of the vegetable oil in a large non-stick skillet on medium-high heat.
When oil is hot, add 3 of the pork chops without letting the sides touch.
Cook to golden brown, about 2 minutes, and turn over for another 2 minutes.
Place cooked chops on a towel-lined plate and repeat for the remaining 3 chops, adding another tablespoon of oil to the pan first.

title: lucille's baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients, except bacon.
Put bacon on top. Bake for 2 hours (or less) in a 325° to 350° oven.

title: west pecos ham bites
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Spread on cracker (either Ritz or Triscuits works best).
Broil 3 to 5 minutes or until slightly browned.
Serve hot.

title: big mama's wedding punch
directions: Boil hot water; add to lemon jello and sugar.
Stir until dissolved.
Add cold water, pineapple juice and almond extract. Stir until well blended and place in freezer for 2 days.
Take out about 4 hours before ready to serve.
Punch will be slushy.

title: key lime cheese cake
directions: Brown pie shells in oven as directed. Mix all ingredients together. Mix on high speed for about 4-5 minutes. Pour into shells and refrigerate for 2 hours.

title: nonna's rice balls
directions: Cook rice and drain (do not rinse). Brown chop meat or mash leftover meatballs with fork. (If using meatballs, omit browning and draining meat.) Drain meat; put in a bowl. Add salt, pepper, tomato sauce, parsley, grating cheese and Mozzarella; mix well.

title: almond chicken salad
directions: Mix chicken, almonds and celery in bowl.
Combine mayonnaise, yogurt, lemon juice, parsley, salt and pepper.
Blend into chicken and toss lightly.
Yields 4 servings.

title: rice custard with leftover rice*
directions: Combine eggs, sugar and salt.
Gradually add milk, stirring. Add cooked rice, raisins and vanilla.
Pour into greased (with oleo or butter) casserole.
Set casserole in pan of hot water in oven.
Bake at 350° for 1/2 hour.
Remove from oven.
Stir. Sprinkle with nutmeg or cinnamon and dot with butter.
Bake 30 to 40 minutes until set.
Makes 6 servings.

title: bisquick surprises
directions: Mix together ingredients.
Mold mixture around olives or pieces of Vienna sausage.
Bake at 450° for 8 to 10 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve hot.

title: tang salad
directions: Keep juice from canned fruit.
Mix dry pudding and Tang.
Add 1 1/2 cups fruit juice.
Do not beat. Gently fold in fruit.
Add any amount of Cool Whip.

title: rolls
directions: In large bowl, add warm water and sprinkle yeast on top to dissolve.
Melt margarine in saucepan (don't get too hot).
Add well beaten egg, sugar and salt.
Add to yeast mixture.
Add flour and knead well.
You might have to add a little more flour while you knead the mixture.
Grease sides of bowl and mixture. Let rise until double.
Bake at 400°.

title: cheese crisps
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, combine cheese, flour, cereal, sugar, salt, cayenne, mustard, melted butter and Worcestershire sauce.
Mix with your hands until well blended. Form mixture into one-inch balls and arrange about one inch apart on an ungreased baking sheet.
Use a fork to form a crisscross pattern while pressing balls into disks about 1/4-inch thick. Bake until edges are golden brown, 10 to 12 minutes.
Serve warm or at room temperature.
These freeze well.

title: cream cheese brownies
directions: Mix together; spread into 13 x 9-inch pan.
Mix will be crumbly.

title: frosted fudge squares
directions: Melt chocolate and butter in top of a double boiler over simmering water; set aside to cool.
Beat egg whites lightly with a wooden spoon; gradually add sugar, salt and vanilla, stirring well, and stir in cooled chocolate mixture.
Sift flour over pecans.
Mix well and stir into batter.
Spread batter in a greased 12 x 8 x 2-inch baking pan.
Bake at 325° for 35 to 40 minutes.
Frost with Favorite Brownie Frosting.
Cut into 1 1/2-inch squares while warm.
Yields about 3 dozen.

title: beatrice straw's gingerbread
directions: Mix and chill.
Roll medium thick.
Cut into bars, cut all at once.
Mark dough with fork.
Bake at 350°.

title: glorified rice
directions: Bring water to boil; add salt and rice.
Cook 30 minutes or until tender.
Drain and rinse.
In large bowl, add to rice (cooled) the marshmallows, pineapple, nuts, sugar and salt and mix lightly.
Add whipped cream, turning easy.
Chill.
Garnish with chopped nuts and cherries.

title: crustless quiche
directions: Mix well the flour, salt and baking powder.
Add the remaining ingredients.
Mix very well by hand.
Pour into a greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: sesame chicken
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Toast sesame seed coated with 3 tablespoons butter.
Set aside.
Dip chicken breasts in evaporated milk and roll in bread crumbs mixed with salt and pepper.
Place on foil-lined baking sheet.
Top with 1/4 cup sesame seed.
Bake skin side up and do not turn.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cabbage wedge meal
directions: Remove tough outer leaves of cabbage.
Cut into 6 to 8 wedges. Arrange in a buttered casserole or skillet.
Put uncooked rice, ground beef and onions between wedges.
Combine tomatoes, water and seasonings.
Pour over casserole.
Cover and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 30 minutes.

title: veggie squares
directions: Spread dinner rolls on cookie sheet and press together.
Bake just until set.
Mix cream cheese, sour cream and Ranch dressing mix and spread on dinner rolls.
Chop 2 to 3 cups each of broccoli, cauliflower and carrots.
Put on top of cream cheese mixture. Chill and cut into squares.
This is good with grated Cheddar cheese sprinkled on top of vegetables.

title: squash casserole
directions: Butter
casserole
dish and sprinkle layer of crumbs in dish. Mix
together
remaining
ingredients and pour in dish. Sprinkle remainder
of crumbs on top of squash mixture.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mystery pecan pie
directions: Combine flour with salt in mixing bowl.
Cut in shortening until mixture is the size of small peas.
Sprinkle water, a little at a time, over mixture while tossing and stirring lightly with fork.
Add water to driest particles, pushing lumps to side, until dough is just moist enough to hold together.
Form into a ball. Flatten to 1/2-inch thickness; smooth edge.
Roll out on floured surface in a circle, 1 1/2-inches larger than inverted 9-inch
pie pan.
Fit loosely into pan.
Fold edge to form a standing rim; flute.
Spread cream cheese mixture in bottom of pastry-lined pan. Sprinkle with pecans.
Gently pour syrup mixture over pecans. Bake at 375° for 35 to 40 minutes, until center is firm to touch.

title: classic cole slaw
directions: Combine first 4 ingredients. Stir in remaining ingredients. Cover; chill. Makes 6 cups.

title: chocolate layered dessert
directions: Mix above and spread into an 8-inch pan and bake at 350° for 15 minutes; cool completely.

title: baked corn
directions: Mix flour and sugar together.
Beat eggs; add to corn and to melted butter.
Blend well.
Pour into greased 1 1/2-quart baking dish.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°, or until knife inserted in middle comes out clean.

title: pineapple ice
directions: In saucepan, combine the sugar and water; stir until dissolved.
Bring to boil; boil for 5 minutes, covered, without stirring (to avoid crystallization).
Chill the syrup.
Add 1 cup drained, crushed pineapple and 6 tablespoons lemon juice.
In ice cream churn, freeze until hard, then salt over the frozen ice. Makes 9 servings.

title: hash brown casserole
directions: Mix all the ingredients.
Put into baking dish.

title: potato pancakes
directions: Combine all ingredients, except the potatoes, in a blender. Blend at high for 2 to 3 seconds.
Gradually, while blending, add the potatoes.
Blend for 45 seconds.
Cook for 3 to 4 minutes on each side.

title: christmas cake
directions: Cream sugar and oleo.
Add eggs, milk, lemon and vanilla.
In another large bowl, mix dry ingredients well.
Add creamed mixture and mix well.
Makes 2 small or 1 large cake.
Bake 2 hours at 275°.

title: oven fries
directions: Scrub potatoes thoroughly.
Cut each potato lengthwise into eight slices.
Brush the cut surface of the potatoes lightly with melted margarine.
In a plastic bag, combine the Parmesan cheese, garlic salt, paprika and onion powder.
Add eight potato slices to the bag; shake to coat (the potatoes will not be completely coated).
Spray an 11 x 7 x 1 1/2-inch baking pan with nonstick coating.
Arrange the potatoes in a baking pan.
Repeat with the remaining potatoes.
Bake, uncovered, in a 400° oven for 25 to 30 minutes or until tender.
Serve hot.
Makes 3 or 4 servings.

title: zucchini milano
directions: Peel casings from sausages. Crumble meat into frying pan and saute 10 minutes. Remove with a slotted spoon and set to the side.

title: dirt cake
directions: Crush cookies and place half of the crumbs in 9 x 13-inch pan. Mix sugar, cream cheese and butter.
Fold in Cool Whip.
In a separate bowl, mix pudding, milk and vanilla.
Fold in the cream cheese mixture.
Pour over cookie crumbs, then top with remaining crumbs.
Refrigerate.

title: green enchiladas
directions: Melt cheese, soup and milk in double boiler. Add pepper and pimentos.
Brown meat.
Cut tortillas in 1/4 pieces.
Layer tortillas, layer of meat and layer of sauce.
Repeat.
Bake at 350° until cheese is bubbly. Use a 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: chicken enchilada casserole
directions: Cube chicken.
Combine sour cream, soup and chilies.
Toss with chicken to coat.
Cut tortillas into small pieces, approximately 1 x 2-inch.
Spray casserole dish with Pam.
Layer beginning with tortillas, then chicken mixture, then cheese.
Repeat two or three times, depending on size of casserole dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until cheese has melted and casserole is bubbling. Serve with spanish rice, chips, salsa and guacamole.

title: corn pudding
directions: Heat butter and milk together until butter melts.
Stir in corn, eggs, flour, sugar and salt; blend well.
Pour mixture into ungreased loaf pan and bake at 325° for 45 minutes or until set.

title: fruit salad pie
directions: Mix in 9 ounces Cool Whip.
Pour in baked pie shells.
Better if chilled.

title: baked barbecue spareribs
directions: Salt ribs.
Place in shallow roasting pan, meat side up. Roast at 450° for 30 minutes.
Drain fat.
Top each piece with a slice of onion and a slice of lemon.
Combine remaining ingredients in a saucepan and bring to a boil.
Pour over ribs. Lower oven to 350° and bake 1 1/2 hours.
Baste every 15 minutes. Makes 4 servings.

title: chocolate fudge or peanut butter fudge
directions: Mix sugar and evaporated milk in saucepan over medium heat. Bring to a boil, stirring constantly.
Cook approximately 25 to 30 minutes or until mixture comes to a definite soft ball stage.
If hard rolling boil (bubbles plopping), turn off.
Add chocolate chips or peanut butter chips, marshmallow cream and nuts.
Pour into greased 9 x 13 x 2-inch pan.
Cool and refrigerate.

title: banana bread
directions: Can be assembled (in order listed) and baked in bread machine on "batter breads" setting.
Or preheat oven to 350°.
Grease bottom only of regular size loaf pan.
Mix ingredients in order listed, mixing well between each ingredient.
Pour into pan.
Bake until toothpick comes out clean (8-inch pan 1 1/4 hours, 9-inch pan 55 to 60 minutes).
Cool 5 minutes.
Loosen from sides of pan and remove.
Cool completely before slicing.

title: herbed veal stew
directions: Brown meat in oil.
Saute onion in remaining fat for 3 minutes.
Return meat to kettle; sprinkle with 1 teaspoon salt and flour.
Stir 1 minute over medium heat.
Dissolve bouillon cubes and add to kettle.
Add bay leaf and marjoram.
Bring stew to boiling.
Cover and simmer 1 1/2 to 2 hours.
Serve over rice.

title: chicken salad
directions: Mix all ingredients except potatoes.
Chill.
Just before serving, add potatoes.
Serve in lettuce lined bowl.

title: whiskey punch
directions: Do not add any water.
Can be made ahead and frozen.

title: big john's pie dough
directions: Place flour in a mixing bowl.
Using the dough hook attachment, add the butter slowly.
When the mixture is pea size, dribble in the water.
This dough makes a nice golden crust and is almost foolproof to make (I can do it!).
Form the dough into balls that weigh 1 ounce for each inch your pie pan is.
These can be wrapped and frozen until needed; just thaw and roll out.

title: tamale casserole
directions: Place tamales in a long casserole dish (be sure to remove papers off tamales). Pour juice from tamale can over tamales. Put both cans of chili over the tamales. Top with cheddar cheese. Crumble Fritos for the topping.

title: choco-nut dainties
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix butter, sugar, egg and vanilla. Blend in flour and salt.
Stir in chocolate chips.
Shape dough into 2-inch logs.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet and bake 12 to 14 minutes.
Cool.
Spread nuts on waxed paper.
Dip one end of cookie into Chocolate Coating and then in nuts.
Place cookies on waxed paper until set.
Store airtight or refrigerate.

title: banana bread
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add beaten eggs and bananas. Sift flour, salt and soda.
Add bananas to mixture.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Pour into greased pan.
Bake for one hour at 300°.

title: strawberry dumplings
directions: If strawberries are unsweetened, sweeten to taste; bring to boil.
Mix Bisquick, milk and sugar.
Drop into boiling strawberries.
Turn heat down to medium heat and cook 15 minutes.

title: apricot bread
directions: Soak apricots for 30 minutes in warm water.
Mix sugar, shortening and egg thoroughly.
Stir in 1/4 cup water and orange juice.
Sift together flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt and stir into liquid to form batter.
Blend in chopped nuts and apricots.
Line bottom of pan with waxed paper.
Grease and flour sides of pan.
Pour in batter and let stand 15 minutes.
Bake at 350° for 55 minutes.
Makes 1 large loaf or 2 medium or 3 small loaves.

title: cherry angel dessert
directions: Cut or tear cake into 1/2 inch pieces to measure 8 cups. Place half the cake cubes in a 9 x 9-inch baking pan.
Reserve 1/3 cup pie filling; spread remaining filling over cake.
Top with remaining cake cubes.
Combine the pudding mix, milk and sour cream.
Spoon over cake.
Cover and chill.
To serve, cut into squares and top with reserved cherries.
Yields 9 servings.

title: bran muffins
directions: Mix eggs, sugar and oil.
Pour some of buttermilk in with cereal in a separate bowl.
Sift flour and baking soda and salt. Add to egg mixture alternately with buttermilk.
Last add the cereal and mix well.

title: oven barbecued spareribs
directions: Cut ribs in serving size pieces.
In
large saucepan, cover ribs with salted water.
Cover and simmer until nearly tender (about one hour).
Meanwhile, in a saucepan, melt butter; add garlic and cook 4 to 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients and bring to boil.
Drain ribs and place in shallow baking pan.
Pour boiling sauce over ribs.
Bake at 350° for 20 minutes, basting often with sauce.
Serves 4.

title: sausage and egg puff
directions: Mix ingredients, cover and refrigerate.
Uncover and bake at 350° in a 2-quart casserole for 1 hour, or until brown on top.

title: mexican fruit dessert
directions: Toss oranges, bananas and strawberries with liqueur.
Beat whipping cream and powdered sugar in chilled bowl until stiff. Spread over fruit and sprinkle light layer of cinnamon over top. Serve immediately.

title: pecan cream delight
directions: Mix oleo, flour and pecans.
Press into 9 x 13-inch baking dish.
Bake at 375° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: cinnamon flour tortillas
directions: When making tortillas, follow instructions on the package of flour.
Roll tortilla dough thin (round). Using a large deep frying pan, pour the cooking oil into pan and heat cooking oil to a boil on low fire.
Put flat rolled out tortilla into the hot cooking oil slowly until it has a nice brown color and with tongs, flip the tortilla.

title: luncheon sandwich(great for ballgame nights)
directions: Combine margarine, poppy seed, onion and mustard.
Spread on open hamburger buns. Add a slice of cheese and a slice of ham. Place on baking sheet and cover with foil. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes or until cheese melts.
Makes 6 servings.

title: pecan chewies
directions: Mix together in a pot the brown sugar and margarine.
Melt on medium heat and let cool.
Stir in eggs, one at a time.
Add vanilla, flour and pecans.

title: spinach-stuffed potatoes(reduced fat)
directions: Prick potatoes several times and bake at 400° for 45 minutes until soft.
Cool slightly; cut potatoes in half lengthwise and scoop out potato pulp leaving 1/4 inch shells.
Place pulp in bowl, mash until smooth.
Add spinach, 3 tablespoons cheese and next 6 ingredients.
Stir.
Fill potato shells with spinach mix. Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Place on baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
Yields 4 servings.

title: fresh apple cake
directions: Peel apples, chop and set aside.

title: easy potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in baking dish.
Combine all remaining ingredients and pour mixture over potatoes.
Cook, covered, 45 minutes and then uncovered another 15 minutes in a 350° preheated oven.

title: pork and mushroom soup a la tugboat
directions: Quickly brown pork chops, then place in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish.
Add onions, green peppers and mushroom soup with 1 can of water.
Bake at 325° for 1 to 1 1/2 hours.
Feeds 4 to 5.

title: peach pound cake
directions: Cream butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating well after each one.
Add vanilla and almond extracts.
Sift together the flour, baking soda and salt; add to creamed mixture.
Fold in sour cream and peaches.
Pour into greased and floured 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 350° for 75 to 85 minutes, or until toothpick inserted in center comes out clean.

title: out of this world cake
directions: Combine first 7 ingredients in large mixer bowl, mix well. Stir in coconut and pecans.
Pour into greased and floured 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake for 30 to 40 minutes at 350° or until cake tests done.

title: crustless quiche muffins
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Butter muffin tins.
In large bowl, combine eggs, cream, broccoli, salt and pepper.
Stir in bacon bits.
Pour into muffin tins, filling each approximately halfway. Bake 1 hour or until knife in center comes out clean.
Makes 12 to 15 muffins.

title: lemon bars
directions: Cream butter and confectioners sugar; blend in flour.
Mix well.
Press evenly in 11 x 17-inch jelly roll pan.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.
Beat eggs slightly; add remaining ingredients.
Beat until well mixed.
Spread evenly over crust. Bake an additional 13 to 15 minutes or until set.
Don't burn. Sprinkle with confectioners sugar while still warm.
When slightly cooled, but still soft, cut into squares.
Place in container with tight fitting lid.
Separate layers with freezer wrap.
Store in freezer.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Combine all ingredients and bake in a Bundt pan at 325° for 1 1/2 hours.

title: lasagne
directions: Brown meat slowly; spoon off excess fat.
Simmer ground beef, sausage, onion, tomatoes, garlic salt, basil leaves, salt and tomato paste for 30 minutes, stirring occasionally.

title: no fools pie
directions: Melt butter in 9 x 9-inch baking pan.
Mix other ingredients together.
Pour over butter.
Add fruit on top.
Bake at 350° for 40 minutes.

title: perfect buttermilk biscuits
directions: Mix ingredients with enough buttermilk to make a soft sticky dough.
Pour out on floured board.
Work with flour until you can handle dough.
Pinch off biscuits.
Place in pan with lots of melted shortening, at least 1/4 inch of shortening in pan.
Bake at 400° until done.
Perfectly delicious!

title: dump cake
directions: Grease an 11 x 13-inch pan and spread ingredients in order given except for butter and nuts; cut up butter into pats and layer over top.
Bake at 350° for approximately 45 minutes to 1 hour.

title: sweet potato balls
directions: Combine first 3 ingredients (salt to taste.)

title: carrot salad
directions: Combine vegetables in large bowl.
Combine remaining ingredients in small saucepan.
Heat over medium heat until blended well.
Pour over vegetables.
Chill overnight.
Makes 24 servings.

title: oatmeal macaroons
directions: Cream the butter and sugar.
Add eggs, oatmeal, salt and vanilla.
Drop on greased cookie sheet and bake at 350°.

title: deviled egg balls
directions: In a small bowl mix eggs, onion, bacon, mustard and mayonnaise.
Mix until creamy.
Form into 1-inch balls.
Roll in cheese or parsley-chives.
Arrange on plate.
Garnish with parsley sprigs, cherry tomato halves and or radish roses.
Cover with plastic wrap and refrigerate.

title: c. m. p. dessert
directions: Mix and press in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake 10 to 15 minutes. Cool.

title: pork chops supreme
directions: Brown chops on both sides in skillet.
Top each seasoned chop with a slice of onion and lemon.
Sprinkle with brown sugar.
Top each with catsup.
Add water to skillet and cover tightly and cook slowly on top of stove in oven.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: rice pudding
directions: Cook milk, rice and salt in double boiler for 45 minutes. Remove from heat.
Mix eggs, sugar and vanilla together.
Add to rice.
Add a little of hot mixture to the egg mixture, a little at a time.
Sprinkle with cinnamon.

title: baked cheese
directions: Pinch together
all seams on the crescent rolls to make one piece
of
dough.
Remove
red plastic from around cheese, place in
center of dough.
Wrap the crescent dough around the cheese, sealing
any
holes.
Bake at 350° to 375° until crescent rolls are brown.
Serve with sliced apples.

title: pork chop bake
directions: Place all vegetables in casserole.
Add water.
Top with chops, sprinkling on rest of envelope of Shake 'n Bake.
Bake at 400° for 1 hour.

title: ground beef and vegetable soup
directions: In large saucepan cook the meat and onion until meat is brown; drain.
Add other ingredients.
Cook until vegetables are tender, stirring occasionally.

title: dinette cake
directions: Put all ingredients into a large mixing bowl and mix thoroughly at low speed for 1 minute.
Then beat for 2 minutes at medium speed.
Pour into greased and floured 8-inch square pan (2 inches deep).
Bake in 350° oven for 30 to 35 minutes.

title: chicken reuben
directions: Place chicken breasts in 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking pan.
Top with sauerkraut.
Place Swiss cheese on top of sauerkraut.
Pour Thousand Island dressing over all.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.

title: escalloped chicken and noodles
directions: Melt butter.
Blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Gradually add broth and cook over medium heat, stirring constantly, until mixture thickens.
Pour gravy over noodles, chicken, peas and eggs in 2 quart casserole.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs.
Bake at 375° for 30 minutes.

title: cracker niblies
directions: In large bowl, mix all ingredients.
Put in refrigerator overnight.
Enjoy!

title: carrot cake
directions: Sift together the first 6 ingredients.
Make a well and add eggs, oil and water.
Beat well, then add carrots and nuts.
Mix well.
Pour into greased and floured pans.
Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.
Frost with Cream Cheese Frosting.

title: pimento cheese
directions: Beat with mixer the cheddar and cream cheese together. (Do not over beat.)
Stir in mayo, pimento and pepper, blend well. This can be used for party sandwiches or put in a crock and served with crackers.

title: lasagna
directions: Brown hamburger with onion.
Drain well.
Place in a large bowl and add sauce.
Add seasoning, cottage cheese and water. Layer bottom of pan with this mixture.
Place layer of dry noodles atop mixture.
Keep alternating layers until all ingredients are used.
Sprinkle cheese on top of mixture.
Seal top with aluminum foil to steam baked noodles.
Bake at 350° for 50 to 60 minutes.

title: scramble
directions: Mix all cereals, nuts and pretzels in large roaster.
Mix oil, Worcestershire sauce and salt well and drizzle over mix.
Bake at 250° for 2 hours.
Use a wooden spoon or plastic spoon to stir every 15 minutes.
Makes about 8 quarts.

title: mom's navy bean soup
directions: Soak dry beans overnight according to package directions. Drain and rinse beans.

title: cinnamon cake
directions: Mix cinnamon and sugar and set aside.
Mix cake mix, sour cream, eggs and oil together and mix well.
Pour 1/2 of batter into a greased and floured pan.
Sprinkle with 1/2 of cinnamon and sugar mixture.
Pour remaining batter into pan and sprinkle remaining sugar and cinnamon mixture over top.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: sour milk pancakes
directions: To well-beaten egg yolks add milk alternately with dry ingredients which have been sifted together.
Mix thoroughly; add butter and when cool, fold in stiffly beaten egg whites.
Have griddle hot.

title: maple nut muffins
directions: Cream butter and brown sugar.
Add egg, extract and syrup; beat well.
Mix dry ingredients in separate bowl.
Add mixture to egg mixture; fold in nuts (save 1/4 cup for topping).
Spoon into well-buttered muffin tin.

title: oven-fried chicken(low-fat)
directions: Remove skin from chicken breasts.
Combine crumbs, cheese and spices in bowl.
Pam spray shallow baking pan.
Dip chicken pieces in milk; coat with crumbs.
Place in pan; brush with oil.
Bake in 400° oven 45 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: armadillo eggs
directions: Wash and devein peppers by cutting off the stem area and running the blade of a sharp knife inside the pepper to remove the vein and seeds.
If you don't remove all of the seeds, you may regret it later.
After the peppers have drained and are pretty much dry, stuff them with the grated cheese.

I usually squish it in the palm of my hand, that way it's easier to stuff. After the peppers are stuffed, combine the remaining cheese with the sausage (it's best if this is at room temperature) add the Bisquick and mix thoroughly.
You may have to use your hands to mix this, so I suggest taking off your rings.

title: pork chops and rice
directions: Season pork chops with lemon pepper seasoning, salt and pepper. Flour lightly and fry until brown on both sides.
Then saute onion and bell pepper in grease.
Lay pork chops in baking dish.
Cover with rice.
Mix broth, soup, onion and pepper together.
Pour in 1/2 cup water.
Mix well.
Pour mixture over top of pork chops. Bake at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: sloppy joes
directions: Cook hamburger.
Drain well.
Mix other ingredients in and stir well.
Simmer very slowly until onions and peppers are done. Add some water and cook longer if necessary.
(This enhances flavor.)

title: hot crab souffle
directions: Dice 6 slices of bread into baking dish.
Mix the crabmeat, mayonnaise, onion, celery and green pepper; spread over diced bread.
Trim crust from remaining 6 slices of bread and place slices over mixture.
Mix eggs, milk and soup together; pour over all.
Place in refrigerator overnight.
Top with cheese and paprika.
Bake, uncovered, in oven at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cabbage salad
directions: Shred cabbage, slice onions and crush noodles.
(Do not use soup seasoning of Ramen noodles.)
Combine.
Toast 1/2 to 1 cup almonds, then add 1/2 cup sesame seed.
Add to cabbage mixture. Sesame seed will toast quickly.

title: no bake cookies
directions: Mix first 4 ingredients all together in saucepan over medium heat; bring to a boil for 3 minutes.
Add peanut butter and oatmeal to first ingredients.
Mix well.
Drop teaspoon size or larger cookies on wax paper.
Completely cool and put in a cookie jar.

title: ground meat casserole
directions: Mix all ingredients together and bake for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: oven baked fish(light; nonfat)
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Process crackers into fine crumbs using food processor or blender.
Stir dry mustard into crumbs.
Beat egg white with milk in a broad shallow bowl.
Spread cracker crumbs on a plate.
Dip fish fillets one at a time into egg white mixture, then place in cracker crumbs and turn to coat all surfaces.
Place on baking sheet and bake at 425° for about 15 minutes until coating is crisp and fish flakes easily with a fork. Serve with lemon wedges, if desired.
Contains 166 calories and 1.7 grams fat per serving.
Makes 4 servings.

title: spoonburgers
directions: In a heavy skillet, brown meat over medium heat.
Add garlic, onion and salt.
Cook 5 minutes.
Add remaining ingredients except buns.
Simmer about 20 minutes or until thick.
Spoon onto toasted buns.

title: shamrock rolls
directions: Combine potato, scalded milk (cool to lukewarm) and 1 tablespoon sugar.
Add crumbled yeast and 2 cups flour.
Mix thoroughly.
