Add sugar, salt, shortening, eggs and 2 cups flour. Knead lightly.
Place in a greased bowl.
Let rise to double in size.
Shape into 3 (1/2-inch) balls.
Put into muffin tin.
Bake at 350° for 12 to 15 minutes.

title: marinated cucumbers
directions: Mix together; then add the cucumber slices.

title: chocolate chip pound cake
directions: In a large bowl, blend all ingredients except chocolate chips.
Then stir in the chips.
Pour into a greased Bundt pan or tube pan.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: cheesy puffins
directions: Heat oven to 400°.
Grease bottom only of muffin pans.
Mix ingredients vigorously about 1/2 minute.
Fill 12 greased muffin cups 2/3 full.
Bake for 15 minutes.
Serve warm.

title: zucchini pineapple bread
directions: Beat eggs, oil, sugar and vanilla until thick and foamy.
Add zucchini and pineapple.
Combine remaining ingredients and stir into first mixture, just until blended.
Pour into greased and floured loaf pans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour or until pick inserted in center comes out clean.
Yields 2 loaves.

title: lemon fruit dip(appetizer)
directions: Beat cottage cheese on high speed in blender.
Stir in yogurt and lemon peel.
Serve with fruit as dippers.
Makes about 1 2/3 cups.

title: upside-down pizza
directions: Brown sausage with onion.
Layer in baking dish: browned meat, tomato sauce and cheese.
Mix Bisquick, milk and eggs.
Pour over top of layered mixture.
Bake at 350° for 35 minutes.
Top will brown.

title: corn casserole
directions: Saute onion in butter until tender.
Stir in flour and cook 1 minute over low heat, stirring constantly.
Gradually stir in sour cream, corn and salt; cook over medium-low heat, stirring constantly until thoroughly heated (do not boil).
Stir in half the bacon; pour into a greased shallow 2-quart casserole dish. Sprinkle remaining bacon over top.
Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: strawberry cake
directions: Put cake mix, flour and jello in bowl; mix well.
Add water, juice, salad oil and eggs.
Mix well.
Add 5 ounces of strawberries (mostly berries, save juice for icing).
Mix.
Bake in tube pan for 45 minutes at 350°.

title: lunchtime tuna or chicken casserole
directions: Cook onion and celery in broth in microwave on High. Add seasonings. Crumble toast. Add with chicken to broth.
Mix well. Top with cheese.
Microwave for 5 minutes or can put in oven for 15 minutes at 375°.
Serves 1.

title: small one egg cake
directions: Put all in bowl; beat well.
Put in loaf pan or round pan, oiled.
Bake at 350° for 35 to 45 minutes.
Test with toothpick.

title: wilted onions
directions: Put onions in a ceramic or glass bowl.
Bring other ingredients to a boil.
Pour over onions and let stand.
When cool, refrigerate overnight.
These keep well in a tightly closed container.

title: whipped cream horseradish sauce
directions: Mix horseradish root, lemon juice, vinegar, salt, sugar, cayenne and onion juice.
Chill.
Just before serving, fold this mixture into whipped cream.

title: hot noodle salad
directions: Cook noodles in boiling water for 7 to 9 minutes or until tender.
Drain well.

title: smothered okra with tomatoes
directions: In a large skillet, over high heat, heat the margarine and olive oil until very hot.
Add the okra, salt, cumin, white pepper and red pepper; stir constantly to prevent sticking.
Cook for about 15 minutes, or until the okra is no longer slimy, then add the tomato and paprika.
Reduce the heat to medium and continue cooking.
When the okra starts to stick, scrape the bottom of the skillet with a spoon; continue cooking and stirring until the okra turns a light brown color.
Gradually stir in the water.
Cook, uncovered, for about 30 minutes longer, or until all the liquid has evaporated, stirring often.

title: english trifle
directions: Bake
cake
according
to
directions.
Let cool.
Tear cake into
small pieces and sprinkle of bottom of 10-inch pan or casserole
dish.
Drain fruit cocktail (save juice to make jello) and
sprinkle
on
top of cake.
Add nuts.
Make jello according to directions, using juice from fruit cocktail along with
cold water.
Sherry
may be added to jello according to taste.
Pour jello
over
cake
and fruit cocktail.
Let set, preferably overnight.
Make
instant
pudding and spread over set jello. Make Dream Whip and spread over pudding.

title: chocolate-peanut butter bars
directions: Cream the margarine and brown sugar. Stir in flour until crumbly.
Press in ungreased 9 x 13-inch pan. Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Let cool.

title: marinara sauce
directions: Cook onion and garlic in olive oil in a Dutch oven over medium-high heat, stirring constantly, until tender. Add tomatoes and remaining ingredients. Bring to a boil, reduce heat to medium and cook, stirring occasionally, 20 minutes or until most of the liquid evaporates. Remove and discard bay leaves.

title: asparagus salad
directions: Dissolve jello in 1 cup boiling water and let cool.
Add all ingredients and put into mold.
Chill until firm.

title: chocolate chip pecan cake
directions: Prepare pudding according to directions.
Set aside to cool. Into a large bowl, put cake mix, eggs, cooking oil and the prepared pudding.
Beat well.
Pour into a well-greased and floured cake pan (9 x 13-inches); sprinkle with pecans and chocolate chips.
Bake 30 to 35 minutes at 350°.

title: breaded tomatoes
directions: Cook onion until tender.
Add tomatoes, bread, seasoning and sugar.

title: taco casserole for dip
directions: Combine bean dip, mayonnaise, sour cream and taco seasoning. Finely chop onions, olives and tomatoes.
Put shredded cheese on top.
Cover and refrigerate.
Serve with nacho chips.
Will serve 15 to 18.

title: broccoli cauliflower salad
directions: Cut cauliflower and broccoli in bite-size pieces.
Mix all together.
Refrigerate for 1 hour.
Serve.

title: frog's eye salad(may be prepared fat free)
directions: Combine sugar, flour and salt.
(If using honey, omit sugar from this first step and add the honey with pineapple juice.) Stir in pineapple juice and eggs.
Cook, stirring constantly until thickened.
Add lemon juice; cool to room temperature.
Prepare Acini De Pepe; mix well and refrigerate overnight or at least 4 hours in airtight container.
Add remaining ingredients and mix thoroughly.
Refrigerate in airtight container until thoroughly chilled.
Refrigerate leftovers.
(Marshmallows and coconut can be optional.)
Yields 25 servings.

title: limeade pie
directions: Mix all ingredients and pour into crusts.
Chill until firm.

title: cheesy broccoli noodle soup
directions: Saute onion.
Set aside.
To 6 cups boiling water, add bouillon cubes, noodles and broccoli (cooked according to package directions).
Cook until tender.
Add onions, cheese, milk, salt and pepper.
Cover and let simmer.

title: black bean soup
directions: Sort and wash beans; place in large Dutch oven or stockpot. Add 10 cups water and salt, bring to boil and cook 1 minute. Remove from heat; cover and let stand 1 hour.

Do not drain beans. Add celery, onion, green pepper, carrot, basil, oregano, black pepper, cumin, red pepper, garlic cloves, and bay leaf to beans. Bring mixture to boil, cover, reduce heat and simmer uncovered 1 1/2 hours or until beans are tender.
Add tomatoes, corn and tomato sauce; stir well.
Bring to boil, reduce heat and simmer uncovered 30 minutes.
Discard bay leaf.
Yields 4 1/2 quarts (serving size 1 1/2 cups).

title: breakfast apple crisp
directions: Cut apple into 3/4-inch chunks.
Place in a microwave bowl and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Cover with plastic wrap and microwave on High for 3 minutes.
Uncover, add cereal and microwave 1 minute more. Eat.

title: rolls
directions: Mix yeast in warm water.
Add sugar, salt, lard and enough flour for thick dough; mix well.
Put in greased bowl and cover in refrigerator until ready to use.
Pinch
off as much as needed. Let rise until double in size.
Bake in greased pan in 300° oven.

title: anna's corn pudding
directions: Stir the flour, salt, sugar, and butter into the corn.
Beat eggs well and add milk.
Combine all ingredients in an oven dish. Bake slowly at 250 degrees for about 40 minutes.
Stir from bottom three times while baking.

title: sauerkraut salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together lightly.
Chill several hours before serving.

title: stuffed artichokes roman style
directions: Clean, trim and blanch artichokes and drain well.
To make a stuffing, combine bread crumbs, minced garlic, chopped celery, grated Parmesan cheese, parsley and seasonings to taste.
Adjust ingredients to your liking.
Push the stuffing down between the leaves of the artichokes.
The chokes may be removed, if desired and the center filled with stuffing (you may want to double the recipe in this case).
Drizzle olive oil over the artichokes and place them on a rack in a baking dish.
Cover the bottom of the dish with 1-inch of boiling water.
Bake, covered, for 1 hour in 350° oven.

title: fruit punch
directions: Dilute orange juice concentrate with two orange juice cans of water; dilute lemonade concentrate with 3 lemonade cans of water. Set aside.
Combine sugar and water; boil until syrupy.
Add cranberry juice cocktail, cider, orange juice, lemonade and juice from cherries.
Garnish with cherries.

title: mary's potato casserole
directions: Boil potatoes with skins on. Cool. Peel and grate potatoes. Add melted margarine, sour cream, chopped onion and grated cheese. Put in casserole dishes and bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Sprinkle grated cheese over top and put back in oven until cheese is melted.

title: bran muffins
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add egg and beat well.
Stir in milk then bran flakes.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Stir them into bran mixture just enough to moisten them.
Fill muffin pans 2/3 full and bake at 425° for 20 minutes.

title: hanky panky
directions: Fry sausage and chuck until done, drain. Add garlic and oregano. Stir until mixed well. Spread on rye bread and place on cookie sheet. Broil until lightly brown.

title: old timey beef stew(make out stew)
directions: Cut steak into 1/2-inch pieces and boil separately until tender.
Add seasonings to the water.
Boil the roast by itself until tender, then slice in 1-inch pieces and square it.
Make sure water is well seasoned.
You boil them separately because it may take the roast longer to get done.
You do not want your meat mushy.
You want it to stay firm and look nice.
You should also boil the following vegetables separately until they are firm: celery, carrots, potatoes, onions and lima beans.
They should be firm, not mushy.
Boil macaroni separately until tender.

title: marshmallow nut roll
directions: Mix all ingredients, except 1 cup graham cracker crumbs.
Roll out into one large log roll.
Sprinkle graham cracker crumbs on top.
Refrigerate.
This can be cut into small rolls or left as one large roll.

title: spicy chicken with beans
directions: In large saucepan, cook chicken, onions and garlic in hot oil over medium heat, 8 to 10 minutes, or until chicken is no longer pink and onion is tender.
Drain fat.
Add cumin, salt and pepper; cook and stir for 1 minute more.
Stir in undrained tomatoes, tomato sauce and, if desired, jalapeno peppers.
Bring to boil. Reduce heat.
Cover and simmer for 20 minutes, stirring occasionally.
Add black beans and Great Northern beans; heat through.

title: garlic croutons
directions: In shallow baking pan, place bread cubes and drizzle with oil and sprinkle with garlic salt.
Bake in 350° oven 18 to 20 minutes or until golden, stirring once.
Cover tightly and refrigerate.

title: flavorize favorite fish grill or broil
directions: Marinate fish for several hours (in refrigerator) in fresh lemon juice, putting in a few slices of lemon and onion, salt, pepper and garlic (if desired).
Grill or broil until fish flakes easily with a fork.

title: mexican chicken
directions: Bake at 350° until warm.
Stir altogether; top with shredded cheese.

title: babe ruth balls
directions: Mix all ingredients together except chocolate and paraffin. Chill for a few minutes.
Shape into balls and put on wax paper.

title: fresh strawberry pie
directions: Mix cornstarch, sugar and Jello; add water.
Cook until thick stirring constantly.
Remove from heat; add butter and lemon juice.
Cool.

title: cranberry daiquiris
directions: Fill blender with all and blend until foamy.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Note:
Pureed strawberries or raspberries are a great topping.

title: breakfast casserole
directions: Spread pizza dough in 9 x 13-inch pan.
Top with sausage.
Add layer of hash browns, then layer of cheese.
Beat eggs and milk together and pour over top.
Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: crabmeat in hollandaise sauce
directions: Blend butter, flour and milk.
Add beaten egg yolks.
Stir constantly until thick over heat.
Remove from heat.
Add lemon juice, salt and chopped shallots.
Serves 6.

title: fresh fried potato chips
directions: Put potatoes in a large bowl and add salt and pepper.
Moisten well with Pet milk.
Sift about 1/2 cup flour over potatoes and coat potatoes well.
Fry in deep fat until brown.

title: brownies
directions: On low heat, melt butter and chocolate squares.
Beat eggs into sugar, one at a time.
Add vanilla, melted chocolate and butter to mixture.
Add flour and mix thoroughly.
Spread in greased 8 x 11-inch pan.
Sprinkle with nuts and chocolate chips. Bake at 350° for 30 to 45 minutes.
If you 1/2 the recipe, use an 8 x 8-inch pan.

title: cabbage and ham salad
directions: Cut ham in julienne strips.
Dice celery, green pepper and onion. Slice eggs.
Combine all ingredients and toss lightly with mayonnaise. Serve on lettuce.

title: grilled cornish hens
directions: Remove bagged
parts
from
inside
hens.
Wash hens in cold water.
Pat
dry
and place in a large pan.
Pour Italian dressing over
hens and marinate, covered, in the refrigerator for at least 8 hours.

title: pineapple casserole
directions: Drain pineapple and put in bottom of a 10 inch pie plate or 8 x 10 inch baking dish. Mix cheese, sugar and flour. Sprinkle over pineapple. Crumble crackers over cheese topping and drizzle melted butter over crackers. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes. Recipe can be doubled to use a 9 x 13 inch baking dish.

title: dutchess soup
directions: Combine chicken stock, celery, carrots and onion; simmer until vegetables are tender.
Add frozen vegetables and simmer 5 minutes more.
Add 1 cup hot milk.

title: nacho dip
directions: Spread cream cheese (at room temperature) into bottom of 8 x 8-inch pan.
Spread chili on top, then shredded cheese.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Dip out with nachos.

title: lemon dessert
directions: Mix all ingredients thoroughly.
Pour into baked pie shell. Chill 4 or 5 hours or longer before serving.
Top with strawberries before serving or your favorite fruit, such as blueberries, pineapple or peaches.
Makes 2 (8 or 9-inch) pies.

title: turkey casserole
directions: Mix soup and milk, cook until hot; stir well.
Add half of soup mixture to macaroni and press against sides and bottom of baking dish.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Mix all the above ingredients in large bow.
Pour into a large casserole dish and bake at 350 degrees for 45 minutes.

title: easy macaroni and cheese
directions: In a medium saucepan, melt butter; blend in flour, salt and pepper.
Gradually stir in milk and cheese; cook and stir over medium heat until thickened and smooth.
Stir in sour cream and macaroni; heat thoroughly.
Serve immediately.

title: e-z salad dressing
directions: Mix ingredients together. Store in jar in refrigerator. Excellent in tossed salad.

title: harding home russian tea
directions: Blend together.
Use 2 teaspoons per cup of tea.

title: homemade noodles
directions: Sift flour, salt and baking powder into a large bowl; add flour.
Make a well in the center of the mixture.
Add eggs, one at a time, mixing slightly after each addition to make a stiff dough.
Knead until smooth.
Roll out very thin on a floured surface.
Allow to dry for 20 minutes.
Roll up loosely, slice 1/4 inch wide, unroll, spread out and let dry for 2 hours.
If desired, store in tightly covered container until needed.
Yields 14 cups uncooked noodles.

title: chocolate crackle cookies
directions: Melt 1 bag of chips over double boiler.
Cool. Cream butter and sugar.
Add eggs one at a time.
Add vanilla and melted chocolate.
Mix well.
Sift flour, salt and baking powder together, then add to mixture.
Mix well.
Stir in oats and second bag of chips.
Drop by rounded tablespoonful into powdered sugar and roll into balls.
Be sure to coat well with sugar.
Bake at 350° for about 10 minutes, more for a crisper cookie, less for a soft fudge-like center.
Makes 5 1/2 dozen.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Drain oranges.
Reserve juice.
Cut oranges up.
Combine flour, salt and soda; sift.
Add chocolate chips, nuts and oranges into flour mixture and mix.
Beat oil and sugar together and add vanilla and eggs.
Add flour mixture and oil mixture alternately with reserved juice.
Mix well.
Put in tube pan.
Bake in 300° oven for 1 hour and 15 minutes.

title: pasta and lentils
directions: In a pot put enough oil to cover the bottom of pot.
Saute garlic until cloves begin to become transparent or brown.
Remove from pan.
Add lentil soup, tomato sauce, salt and pepper.
Cook for 1/2 hour.
Cook, drain and add pasta to all the sauce.
Mix well and let stand for 5 minutes.
Serve with grated Parmesan cheese.

title: cheese cake
directions: Soften cream cheese.
Beat in sour cream and sugar until smooth.
Add eggs, one at a time.
Add flour and vanilla.

title: cheese rounds
directions: Let butter and cheese stand until soft.
Mix butter, cheese, salt and Tabasco with hands, gradually adding flour.
Divide into three parts and work into long rolls in wax paper.
Chill in refrigerator.
Slice thin; put pecan on top.
Bake on ungreased baking sheet at 350° for about 15 minutes.
Allow to brown slightly.
Makes about 100.
These freeze beautifully and are good for teas and coffees.

title: nacho dip
directions: Place all ingredients in crock-pot.
Cook approximately 1 hour on high (just needs to be melted together).
Get Deli Style nacho chips to dip with.
This can be frozen and reheated in the microwave.

title: mexican pie
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Bake at 325° to 350° for 50 minutes or until middle is done.
Let stand 15 minutes before cutting.
Top with sour cream, salsa, chopped tomato or shredded cheese for garnish.

title: cucumber sandwiches
directions: Grate cucumber and onion fine. Place in towel and squeeze all liquid out. Combine with cream cheese and blend well.
Add enough mayo until spreadable.

title: sausage cake
directions: In mixing bowl combine meat and sugars and stir until mixture is well blended.
Add eggs and beat well.
Onto piece of waxed paper, sift flour, ginger, baking powder and spices.
Stir baking soda into coffee.
Add flour mixture and coffee alternately to meat mixture, beating well after each addition.
Pour boiling water over raisins and let stand 5 minutes.
Drain well and dry raisins in cloth.

Fold raisins and walnuts into cake batter. Turn batter into well-greased and floured 10-inch angel food cake pan plus 1 (8-inch) layer cake pan or 1 small 8 x 4 x 2-inch loaf pan as the recipe makes too much batter for one pan.
Bake 1 1/4 to 1 1/2 hours at 350°, until done.
Cool 15 minutes in pan before turning out.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Cook broccoli in small amount of water just until tender. Don't overcook.
Season with salt, butter and pepper.
Drain off excess liquid if there is more than about 1/4 cup.
Add remaining ingredients.
Bake in a 2 1/2-quart casserole dish at 350° for 45 minutes.

title: scrambled eggs
directions: Combine eggs and milk in small bowl.
Cut ham and cheese into small pieces and add to mixture.
Whip with a fork.
Sprinkle a small amount of salt, pepper and onion powder to mixture.
Stir as needed.
Heat a skillet.
Add oil to bottom until hot.
Pour in mixture and turn as needed.
Cook thoroughly.
Serve hot with milk and toast.

title: cooked mayonnaise
directions: In small saucepan, stir together egg yolks, vinegar, water, sugar, mustard, salt and pepper until thoroughly blended.
Cook over very low heat, stirring constantly, until bubbles in 1 or 2 places.
Remove from heat.
Let stand 4 minutes.
Pour into blender container; very slowly add oil.
Blend until thick and smooth.
Occasionally, turn off blender and scrape down sides of container with rubber spatula, if necessary.
Cover and chill if not using immediately.
Makes about 1 1/4 cups.

title: summer squash casserole
directions: Cook sliced squash and onion in boiling, slightly salted water for about 3 minutes.
Squash must still be a little crisp.
Drain. Combine chicken soup and sour cream.
Stir in shredded carrots, squash and onions.
Add salt to taste.
Combine stuffing mix with melted butter.

title: chicken paprikas
directions: Saute onions in oil in a Dutch oven.
Add paprika.
Mix well. Add chicken pieces - coat well with paprika/oil/onion mixture. Add chicken broth, pepper and tomato.
Bring to boil, add bouillon cubes and reduce heat, simmer for 45 minutes or until chicken is tender.
In a separate bowl, mix sour cream and flour.
Blend well.
Ladle some broth from the chicken into the sour cream.
Mix well.
Add sour cream mixture to chicken, stirring constantly. Bring to a boil and turn off heat.
Serve over noodles or rice. Serves 4.

title: fried fish batter
directions: Mix well; dip in fish and fry.

title: fruit cocktail dessert
directions: Mix ingredients and pour into flat cake pan.
Sprinkle top with 1 cup of brown sugar and 1 cup nuts.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until done.

title: bean salad
directions: Combine vinegar, sugar, oil and seasonings; beat until thoroughly blended.
Pour over vegetables; mix lightly.
Cover; marinate in dressing in refrigerator several hours or overnight. Drain.
Makes 8 servings.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix squash, sugar, mayonnaise, sauteed onions, eggs and salt and pepper. Pour into oiled baking dish. Sprinkle cheese on top of mixture. Add crackers on top of cheese. Spray with cooking spray. Bake at 350° for 40 to 45 minutes.

title: yankee cranberry pie
directions: Butter a 10-inch pie plate or quiche tin.
Spread berries over the bottom and sprinkle 1 cup sugar and nuts over them.
In small bowl, beat eggs until frothy.
Add 1 cup sugar and beat well. Slowly mix in flour, margarine and oil.
Beat until blended and pour over berries and nuts.
(I usually add a little vanilla and use less sugar.)
Bake at 350° for 75 minutes.

title: cheese bread
directions: Cut off top of crust of bread.
Slice diagonally both ways, without cutting through the bottom crust.
Mix lemon juice, poppy seed, mustard and butter in a pan.
Melt.
Add onion.
Place bread on large sheet of foil.
Pour butter mixture over bread, stuffing cheese into slashes.
Wrap with foil and refrigerate overnight. Bake at 350° for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: picnic roll-ups
directions: Spread cream cheese thinly on meat.
Roll up and cut in halves. Use toothpicks to garnish.
Easy snack.
Great for picnics!

title: peanut butter fudge
directions: Bring to boil.
Boil 7 minutes on medium heat.

title: dusty miller cookies
directions: Place all ingredients into a large mixing bowl; mix well. Form into 1-inch balls.
Roll in granulated or powdered sugar and place 2 inches apart on cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes.

title: sandwich spread
directions: Saute onion and pepper until tender in 2 tablespoons oil.
Add choplets, nuts, thyme and garlic in a little water.
Stir in choplets and all other ingredients.
Stir.
Use as a sandwich.

title: wanda rice's oatmeal cookies
directions: Mix together.
Dough will be very stiff but will flatten in oven.
(One cup molasses and no milk may be used instead of sugar.)
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.

title: easy buttermilk rolls
directions: Sprinkle yeast in 1/4 cup water.
Add buttermilk, shortening and sugar.
Sift flour, soda and salt into liquid mixture; mix until smooth.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Roll out and shape as desired.
Place in greased
baking dish and let rise 30 minutes. Bake at 400° for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Makes 2 dozen.
May be refrigerated for days.

title: spinach salad
directions: Break apart lettuce and spinach.
Add bacon which has been fried, drained and crumbled.
Mix sugar, salt, mustard, onion, vinegar, poppy seed and oil to make the dressing.
Add cottage cheese to greens and toss with dressing.

title: porcupines (hamburg balls)
directions: Mix hamburg, rice, salt and pepper and onion together.
Form into balls.
Brown and keep covered.
Add 1/2 cup water and 1 can whole tomatoes.
Simmer, covered, for 1 hour.
Add more water, if needed.

title: broccoli cheese casserole
directions: Cook broccoli according to directions, drain and add next 4 ingredients.
Top with crushed crackers mixed with melted butter. Bake at 350° for 20 minutes.

title: 3 day dream cream cake
directions: Day 1:
Mix together Cool Whip, sour cream, sugar and about 1/2 cup milk. Refrigerate overnight to give sugar time to dissolve. Will be thin.

title: marinated pasta salad
directions: Combine pasta and water in 2-quart casserole.
Cover with plastic wrap and microwave at High 16 to 18 minutes or until pasta is tender; drain.
Rinse with cold water and drain well.
Combine pasta, tomato and next 9 ingredients in medium bowl; toss gently. Cover and chill at least 2 hours.
Makes about 4 (1 cup) servings.

title: moist and crispy chicken
directions: Place crushed cereal, paprika, salt and pepper in plastic food bag.
Shake to blend.

title: fruit salad with cool whip
directions: Serve prepared fruit with Cool Whip to dip into.

title: doughnuts
directions: Beat eggs until light.
Add sugar, beating well.
Blend in shortening.
Add dry ingredients alternately with milk and sugar mixture.
Roll 1/4-inch thick on floured board.
Cut with doughnut cutter and fry a few at a time in 4-inches hot (360°) oil or shortening, turning once.
Drain on paper towel.
Dip in sugar or frosting.
Makes 24.

title: sourdough biscuits
directions: Dissolve yeast in warm water.
Add oil and buttermilk and mix well (be sure oil is well blended).
Add the 4 cups of flour and mix well.
Then add 5 cups of flour, salt, baking powder and soda and mix well.
Dough is ready to bake.
Seal in airtight bowl and refrigerate.
To bake, pinch off amount needed and bake about 20 minutes at 350°.
Will keep about 2 months refrigerated if sealed properly.

title: appetizer fruit combo
directions: Drain pineapple, reserving juice.
In bowl, combine pineapple chunks, melon balls and strawberries.
Combine pineapple juice, marmalade and orange liqueur.
Pour over fruits.
Stir.
Chill 1 to 2 hours.
Stir occasionally.
Serves 6.

title: gingerbread pancakes
directions: Sift together twice, all ingredients except shortening.
Cut shortening into dry ingredients with 2 knives or a pastry blender until mixture resembles cornmeal.

title: pecan fingers
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Cream oil, butter and confectioners sugar.
Blend in 1 1/2 cups flour.
Press evenly in bottom of ungreased baking pan (13 x 9 x 2-inch).
Bake 12 to 15 minutes.

title: broccoli rice casserole
directions: Cook and stir onion in 1 tablespoon of the butter in large skillet on medium heat until tender.
Add rice, soup, broccoli and Cheese Whiz; mix lightly.
Spoon into 1-1/2 quart casserole dish. Toss together remaining 1 Tbsp. butter, melted and bread cubes; sprinkle over casserole.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes or until thoroughly heated.

title: impossible buttermilk pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease pie pan with Pam.
Put all ingredients in blender.
Beat on high at least 30 seconds or until smooth like cream.
Pour in pie pan and bake 30 minutes or until knife inserted in center comes out clean.
Cool 5 to 10 minutes before serving.

title: grumpy cake
directions: Bake the cake mix in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 20 minutes.
Cool cake in the pan.
Beat together the pudding mix, cream cheese and the milk until thick and creamy.
Spread on cooled cake.
Spread pineapple over pudding mixture.
Cover with Cool Whip and sprinkle nuts over the top.
Chill overnight in refrigerator.

title: sausage pie
directions: Fry sausage and drain very well.
Line pie crust with American cheese, cut to fit.
Put sausage in pie crust.
Mix egg and milk together and pour over sausage.
Top with Mozzarella cheese.
Bake at 350° until pie crust browns or about 30 minutes.

title: haluski
directions: Chop up cabbage fine, mix with onion.
In a large skillet over medium heat, melt butter. Add cabbage and onion mixture and blend well.
Add salt, pepper and crisco oil, saute until a little brown.
Cook noodles according to package instructions and drain well.
Add noodles to cabbage mixture and mix together well. Serve hot.
Makes 6 servings.

title: dutch potato pancakes
directions: Combine ingredients.
Drop by heaping tablespoonfuls on a greased grill or large frying pan. Brown well on both sides.

title: *ghela cu vin(beef stew with wine)
directions: Brown beef in a little oil until tender. Add all other ingredients and remaining oil.
Cook on low heat 30 to 40 minutes. Serve over rice.

title: turtle cake
directions: Bake cake according to box directions in a 9 x 13-inch pan. While cake is still warm, punch several holes in it with the bottom of a wooden spoon.
Pour condensed milk and caramel in holes and on top of cake.
Let cake cool some and ice with Cool Whip.
Sprinkle top with Heath bar.
Refrigerate several hours before eating.
Keep leftovers in refrigerator.

title: chipped beef dip
directions: Combine together all ingredients.
Bake at 250° in casserole dish for 1 hour.
Serve with rolls.

title: italian sausage with wine(vino con salsiccia)
directions: In large skillet
heat
oil.
Place
Italian sausage in skillet and brown on
medium high heat for 10 minutes, turning often.
Add white wine to pan and cover with lid.
Cook for 30 minutes on low heat.
Serve with Italian bread, if desired.

title: fried apple tarts
directions: Put fruit and water in heavy saucepan and let soak for 1 hour or overnight.
Simmer until thick, about 45 minutes.
Stir in sugar.

title: teriyaki chicken
directions: Remove skin from chicken pieces.
Baste each piece on both sides with sauce.
Bake uncovered, top side down, on greased cookie sheet at 375° for 20 minutes.
Turn pieces over; baste tops.
Top each piece with a pineapple ring.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes more.

title: california stuffed zucchini
directions: Saute onion, celery, mushrooms and garlic in butter.
Scoop out zucchini.
Saute this scooped portion with the onion, celery, mushrooms and garlic.
Add ground beef; brown.
Add tomato sauce, pimento, 1/2 cup cheese, salt, oregano and pepper.
Fill each zucchini half with mixture.
Sprinkle with remaining cheese.
Bake at 350° to 375° for about 30 minutes.
Absolutely delicious!!!!

title: five-hour stew
directions: Cut vegetables and meat into bite-sized pieces.
Arrange in baking dish.
Mix tomato soup with equal amounts of water.
Add wine (optional) and 1 or 2 tsp cornstarch. salt and pepper vegetables to taste.
Pour soup mixture over vegetables.
Cover. Bake at 350 for five hours or overnight in crockpot on low.
Serves 8-10.

title: cooked play dough
directions: Combine all ingredients in a medium saucepan, cook on high, stirring constantly, until desired consistency is reached.
Store in airtight container.

title: whipped pound cake
directions: Beat butter and sugar until light and fluffy.
Add eggs, one at a time, beating 1 minute after each.
Whip cream until stiff peaks form.
Add flour and cream alternately, just until combined after each.
Beat in vanilla.
Pour batter in a greased 10-inch tube pan.
Bake at 300° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Cool for 10 minutes.
Remove from pan.

title: squash casserole
directions: Mix first 5 ingredients together.
Layer mixture with dressing about three times.
Finish with dressing.
Bake in a 350° oven for 30 minutes.

title: enchilada pie
directions: Brown beef and onion in small amount of oil. Add salt, pepper, chili powder and tomato sauce.
In casserole alternate layers of tortillas, meat sauce, chopped olives and cheese. Add water; cover and bake at 400° for 20 minutes.

title: pumpkin (squash) soup
directions: Saute apple and onion in large pot. Add water or chicken broth, pumpkin, bay leaf, curry, nutmeg, and salt and pepper. Simmer for 15 minutes. Puree in blender or processor. Return to pot. Add 1/3 cup milk and simmer 5 minutes more.
Unpeeled apples work as well.

title: mini ham puffs
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Chop ham and onion finely.
Place in a bowl.
Add cheese, egg, pepper and mustard.
Stir to combine. Spray mini-muffin pan with Pam.
Unroll crescent rolls and press dough into one large rectangle.
Cut rectangle into 24 pieces. Place dough pieces in mini-muffin pan cups.
Form a cup.
Place filling in each cup.
Bake for 15 minutes or until lightly browned.
Yield:
24 appetizers.

title: broccoli salad
directions: Cut up first 4 ingredients.
Put in bowl.
Mix salad dressing, sugar and vinegar and pour over the broccoli mixture.
Cover tightly and put in refrigerator overnight.

title: cilantro mashed potatoes
directions: Place potatoes in saucepan.
Cover with water.
Bring to boil and boil until tender.
Drain, peel and mash or grate.
While potatoes are still warm, mix in butter, yogurt, cilantro, pepper and salt.
Transfer to serving bowl.
Garnish with cilantro sprigs, chives and Serrano chiles.
Serves 6.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients together in a large bowl. Place in a baking dish or pan; shape until firm. Cover with small amount of catsup. Bake for 1 hour at 350°.

title: stripe it rich cake
directions: Prepare cake as directed on package.
Bake in 9 x 13-inch pan. Remove from oven.
Poke holes at once down through the cake with wooden spoon end.
Holes should be in 1-inch intervals.
After poking holes in cake, mix together the pudding and sugar in saucepan.
Gradually stir in milk and butter.
Cook over medium heat until it comes to full boil.
Quickly pour over warm cake, filling the holes.
Spread evenly over cake to frost.
Chill at least 2 hours.
Store in fridge.

title: vegetable dip
directions: Mix all together and chill.

title: sugar cookies
directions: Mix in order; roll into small balls.
Press down with a fork. Cook
on greased cookie sheet at 350° for about 8 to 10 minutes.

title: plain muffins
directions: Pour in a greased muffin pan.
Cook until golden brown.

title: laura's jam sandwich
directions: Take one slice of bread in each hand.
Jam them together.
Eat and enjoy.

title: raspberry-grilled hens
directions: In a food processor bowl or an electric blender container, place inegar, orange juice, oil, 1/4 cup raspberries, garlic, salt and pepper.
Cover and process for 1 minute or until all ingredients are thoroughly combined.
Set aside.

title: dump cake
directions: In a greased 9 x 13-inch pan, layer pineapple followed by pie filling (do not mix layers).
Top with dry cake mix.
Sprinkle with cinnamon and top with thin butter pats.
Top whole mess with nuts and coconut.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 50 minutes.

title: lemon snowflakes
directions: Combine cake mix, Cool Whip and egg.
Beat with electric mixer until blended.
Batter will be very sticky.
Drop by teaspoons into confectioners sugar.
Roll lightly to coat.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.

title: tomato-cucumber cocktail
directions: Peel cucumbers; chop finely.
Cook in small amount of water on medium heat for about 5 minutes; drain well and process cucumbers and 2 cups of the vegetable juice cocktail in blender or food processor until smooth.
Pour into pitcher.
Stir in remaining vegetable juice and celery salt.
Serve over ice cubes in a tall glass, garnished with a cucumber slice.
Yield:
8 servings.

title: maple pumpkin cheesecake
directions: Preheat oven to 300°. Combine crumbs, sugar and margarine; press firmly on bottom of 9-inch spring-form pan or 13 x 9-inch baking pan. In large mixer bowl, beat cheese until fluffy. Gradually beat in sweetened condensed milk until smooth. Add pumpkin, eggs, 1/4 cup pure maple syrup, cinnamon, nutmeg and salt; mix well. Pour into prepared pan. Bake 1 hour and 15 minutes or until edge springs back when lightly touched (center will be slightly soft). Cool. Chill. Just before serving, remove side of spring-form pan. Top with Maple Pecan Glaze. Refrigerate leftovers.

title: fennel italian cookies
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Make a well and put in water, oil and beaten egg.
Mix well.
Take a piece and roll pencil thin.
Make a knot.
Bake 1/2 hour at 350° on an ungreased cookie sheet.

title: peanut butter logs
directions: Blend peanut butter, honey, and dry milk. Add raisins and mix well. Stir in graham cracker crumbs. Roll teaspoonful of mixture on wax paper to shape in logs. Refrigerate one hour. Make about 50.

title: hot seafood spread
directions: Mix mayonnaise, lemon juice, onion, salt and other ingredients.
Pour into greased 2-quart casserole.
Bake at 400° for 15 minutes.
Serve as a hot, open-faced sandwich or in a chafing dish/warming tray to spread on crackers.

title: chicken rice casserole
directions: Simmer chicken, 2 tablespoons onion and salt in just enough water to cook.
When cooked, bone and cut into bite size pieces. Mix all other ingredients; except oil, with chicken.
Spoon into baking dish and drizzle oil over top.

title: green bean casserole
directions: Cut green beans into serving size pieces and steam until tender.
Saute onion in olive oil until translucent.
Add lemon rind, dill and yogurt and heat thoroughly.
Place green beans in casserole dish and cover with yogurt sauce.
Top with bread crumbs.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 30 minutes, until sauce is bubbly.

title: king ranch chicken casserole
directions: Mix chili powder, cream of chicken soup, cream of mushroom soup, broth from chicken and Ro-Tel tomatoes together.
Spray 3-quart casserole with Pam.
Crunch up Doritos.
Grate Cheddar cheese.
Layer the Doritos, chicken, onion, bell pepper, soup mixture and cheese.
Repeat 4 layers.
Bake for 1 hour at 350°. Serves 8 to 10.

title: marshmallow icing
directions: Cook sugar, water and corn syrup until it forms a soft ball when tested (238°).
Beat egg white stiff.
Add marshmallows, then the syrup, very slowly, beating constantly.
Add flavoring.
Beat until of the right consistency for spreading.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients together.
Mix eggs, oil and vanilla together.
Add to dry mixture.
Add pineapple (drained) and zucchini to batter.
May add raisins and/or nuts.

title: punch
directions: Mix all together.
To make taste better, add booze.

title: chocolate goodies (brownies)
directions: Beat egg, add melted butter and stir into cake mix. and press into lightly greased 9 x 13 pan.
Sprinkle chopped nuts over dough and press into mixture.
Combine cocoa with sugar
Beat eggs into softened cream cheese.
Add sugar mixture.
Pour over cake mix. Bake at 350° for 45 minutes.
Cool.
Cut into squares.

title: italian pasta and beef
directions: Cook macaroni as directed on package; drain.
Meanwhile, in large saucepan over medium heat, brown ground beef and onion; drain.
Stir in cooked macaroni, soup, beans and corn.
Cook until thoroughly heated.
Makes 6 servings.

title: creamed cabbage
directions: Bring 2 cups milk to a boil in a large saucepan over medium heat.
Stir in oleo and cabbage; simmer for 7 minutes, stirring frequently.
Dissolve flour in 2 teaspoons milk and add.
Heat thoroughly.

title: chocolate sheet cake
directions: Bring to boil water, margarine and oil.
Beat together eggs, buttermilk, soda, vanilla, flour, sugar and Choco-bake; add to margarine mixture.

title: pears baked in red wine
directions: Combine wine, sugar, cinnamon stick, bay leaf, and vanilla in 9 inch round pie plate or other baking dish.
Stir to blend.
Cut thin slice from the bottom of each pear so it will stand upright. Place pears in wine mixture and spoon a little sauce over each pear.
Bake at 350° for 45 to 55 minutes, basting frequently with wine as it thickens and pears become tender.
Remove bay leaf and vanilla bean if used.
Serve warm or at room temperature with wine spooned over each serving.
Serves 4.

title: spinach casserole
directions: Thaw spinach and squeeze out excess moisture.
Beat eggs with cornstarch.
Add spinach and mix.
Add remaining ingredients. Bake in greased 1 1/2 quart casserole at 325° for 40 minutes. Serves 6 to 8.

title: banana pudding
directions: Mix sweetened condensed milk and water.
Add pudding mix; beat until well blended.
Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip.
Layer pudding, vanilla wafers and banana slices in dish.
Begin and end layers with pudding mixture.
May crush a few vanilla wafers to sprinkle on top of pudding for decoration.

title: a happy home recipe
directions: A good deed is never lost:
He who shows courtesy reaps friendships.
And he who plants kindness gathers love.

title: vegetable casserole
directions: Mix vegetables, celery, onion, cheese and mayonnaise together in greased casserole dish.
Top with cracker crumbs and dot with butter.
Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: chicken stuffed with potatoes
directions: In large bowl, place potatoes, rosemary, parsley, garlic and olive oil.
Salt and pepper the chicken inside and out.
Toss ingredients in bowl gently and stuff chicken.

title: oyster sauce
directions: Combine all ingredients and mix well.
Parboil ribs or chicken with fresh ginger until tender. Drain.
Pour marinade over meat. Let set (can leave up to 4 hours).
Bake, broil or barbecue.

title: hot artichoke dip
directions: Mix well. Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until brown and bubbly on top. Serve with Tostitos.

title: white icing
directions: Cook without stirring sugar and water until thread spins. Beat until stiff egg whites and salt.
Add syrup in thin stream over egg whites, beating continuously.
When nearly all of syrup is added, add cream of tartar, then add remaining syrup.
Beat until it will hold its shape and nearly cool.

title: cheesy chicken casserole
directions: Place chicken pieces in casserole dish.
Place soup, broth and Velveeta in a double boiler and heat until smooth and melted. Pour over chicken.

title: praline pecan crunch
directions: Heat oven to 250°.
Combine cereal and pecans in greased 13x9 pan; set aside.
Combine corn syrup, brown sugar, and butter in saucepan and bring to a boil
over medium heat.
Remove from heat, and stir in vanilla and baking soda.
Pour over cereal and pecans. Stir to coat evenly.
Bake 1 hour, stirring every 20 minutes. Spread on baking sheet to cool.
Break into pieces.

title: tuna cashew
directions: Mix all ingredients together, except 1/2 cup of the noodles. Put in 1 1/2-quart size casserole, greased.
Sprinkle the 1/2 cup noodles over the top.
Bake in a 325° oven uncovered about 35 to 40 minutes.

title: mexican dip
directions: Mix all ingredients together.
Heat at 350° until hot. Sprinkle cheese on top when taken out of oven.
May eat alone or with chips.

title: apple cake
directions: Cream sugar, oil and eggs; add flour, soda, salt and spices. Blend thoroughly.
Add apples and pecans.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in 7 x 12-inch pan.

title: pastry for double-crust pie
directions: Prepare as directed for Pastry For Single-Crust Pie, but use these amounts.
Divide dough in half.
Roll out half of dough as directed in Pastry For Single-Crust Pie.
Fit into pie plate. Trim pastry even with rim.
For top crust, roll out remaining dough.
Cut slits for escape of steam.
Place desired filling in pie shell.
Top with pastry for top crust.
Trim top crust 1/2-inch beyond edge of pie plate.
Fold extra pastry under bottom crust; flute edge.
Bake as directed in individual recipe.

title: peanut butter pie
directions: Whip cream cheese until soft and fluffy.
Beat in peanut butter and sugar.
Slowly add milk; fold in Cool Whip.
Pour into pie shell and refrigerate before serving.

title: fruit dip
directions: Whip cream cheese.
Add Marshmallow Fluff and beat until smooth.
Add lemon, strawberry or orange juice to flavor.

title: barbecue curried pork chops
directions: In small skillet, saute onion, garlic and curry powder. Remove from heat and stir in lemon juice, corn syrup, salt and pepper.
In large bowl, cover chops with marinade and let stand 2 to 3 hours.
Remove from marinade, keeping for basting.
Grill 4 to 5-inches from source of heat for 20 to 25 minutes, turning occasionally and basting with marinade.

title: zucchini apple pie
directions: Cook zucchini in boiling water until crisp.
Drain well.
Toss with lemon juice and salt.
Combine sugar, cinnamon and cream of tartar, nutmeg and flour in large bowl.
Mix well.
Stir in zucchini.
Line a 9-inch pie plate with pastry.
Pour in zucchini mixture.
Dot with butter.
Top with remaining pastry.
Bake 400 for 40 minutes or until golden brown.

title: abalone cocktail
directions: Mix together; let stand overnight.
Serve cold with fancy crackers.

title: chicken or beef marinade
directions: Mix all ingredients together until blended well.
Pour over chicken or beef or both; cover and refrigerate 3 to 12 hours before cooking.

title: oysters rockefeller
directions: Cook spinach according to directions on package. Drain well. Press out excess water and set aside.
Wash oysters and arrange in muffin pan that has been lined with foil baking cups.
Stir together cooked spinach, chopped onion, parsley, 2 tablespoons melted butter, salt and hot pepper sauce.
Top each oyster in cup with 1 tablespoon of spinach mixture.

title: bacon crackers
directions: Wrap cracker in 1/2 slice bacon.
Bake at 375° until brown. Delicious.

title: marvelous macaroons
directions: Combine coconut, sugar, flour and salt in mixing bowl.
Stir in egg whites and extract.
Stir in almonds; mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto lightly greased baking sheets.
Bake at 325° for 20 to 25 minutes or until edges of cookies are golden brown.
Remove from baking sheets immediately.
Makes 2 1/2 dozen.

title: brunch casserole
directions: Crumble sausage in medium skillet.
Cook over medium heat until browned, stirring occasionally.
Drain well.
Line bottom of a buttered 13 x 9 x 2-inch baking dish with crescent rolls, firmly pressing perforations to seal.
Sprinkle with sausage and cheese.

title: broccoli-rice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In saucepan, over medium heat, in hot oil, cook celery and onion until tender, stirring often.
Stir in soup and milk.

title: cranberry sparkle punch
directions: Place cake of ice or ice cubes in punch bowl.
Add fruit juices; stir.
Pour carbonated beverage carefully down side of bowl.
Orange slices and whole fresh cranberries may be added for garnish.
Makes 2 1/2 to 3 quarts.

title: diabetic cranberry jello salad
directions: Put all ingredients into blender and blend until fine (except jello, hot water, topping and nuts).
Add jello, dissolved in hot water; cool first.
Then chill overnight.
Add nondairy topping. Sprinkle with nuts before serving.
This salad is good with turkey at Thanksgiving time.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Any vegetable or any amount may be used.

title: lime chicken (lite choice)
directions: Combine first 5 ingredients and marinate chicken breasts for several hours or overnight in a covered bowl.
Bake for 40 minutes at 350° or cook on grill.

title: taco salad
directions: Shred or chop lettuce.
Add cooked meat and chopped tomatoes. Without opening bag squeeze the chips until crumbled well.
Add cheese.
Mix taco sauce and sour cream. Blend all ingredients well to mix.
Better if sits in fridge a couple hours.
Tasty!

title: tomatoes vinaigrette
directions: Slice tomatoes in wedges.
In small bowl, whisk vinegar, salt, pepper and mustard until blended.
Whisk in oil and parsley.
Pour over tomatoes.
May add 1 cucumber, sliced.
Makes 4 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Lay the steak on a board and pound it.
Cook the minced onion in the 1 tablespoon of drippings.
Add breadcrumbs, seasoning, celery, parsley and milk, then spread the mixture over the steak. Roll it up like a jelly roll and tie it with string so it looks like a little body.
Dredge the body with flour, brown it all around in the 2 tablespoons of drippings.
Cover it with the sliced onions.
Pour boiling water into the pan.
Cover tightly and simmer for 2 1/2 to 3 hours.
Or bake it in a tightly covered roaster at 350° for 2 hours.
When the body is tender and brown, a cup of sour cream may be added to make a marvelous gravy.

title: banana split cake
directions: Melt 1 stick of butter and combine with graham cracker crumbs. Pat in bottom of 9 x 13-inch pan; set aside.
Combine confectioners sugar, eggs and 1 stick butter; beat until fluffy. Spread over graham cracker crust.
Spread crushed pineapple over filling.
Slice bananas and arrange over pineapple layer.
Spread Cool Whip over bananas and garnish with nuts and cherries.

title: vegetable pizza
directions: Spread out rolls to form crust in a 10 x 15-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Cool.
Mix softened cream cheese, mayo and Ranch dressing.
Spread over crust.
Cover with chopped vegetable of your choice.
Cover with sheet of waxed paper and press down with a cutting board to set.
Refrigerate one hour or overnight.

title: best bleu cheese dressing
directions: Mix all ingredients well and refrigerate.
Let set for several hours for flavors to blend.

title: grama ethel's parmesan cheese rounds
directions: Mix ingredients together to make a spreadable paste.
Add more cheese if too moist or a little mayonnaise if too dry.
Spread on lightly mayonnaised bread, cut into triangles or rounds.
Broil until brown and bubbly.

title: oma (grandmother) stehling's rolls
directions: Dissolve package of yeast in warm water; add sugar and shortening, salt, egg and flour.
Beat until smooth.
Make into dough and place in refrigerator overnight.
Remove next day and roll into fairly thin 1/2-inch piece.
Cut in small circles.
Put melted butter on one edge; fold over and press edges together. Place in greased pan and let rise.
Bake at 400° for 10 to 14 minutes.

title: children's cookies
directions: Sift flour, soda, baking powder and salt together. Beat shortening and white sugar together. Add remaining ingredients in given order. Drop by teaspoonfuls on cookie sheet. Bake at 375° for 10 minutes. Makes about 4 dozen.

title: fruit cup
directions: Slice all fruits into small bite-size pieces.
Pour over fruit the orange juice, using a little less water than called for in package directions.
Needs to be refrigerated at least 2 days before serving.
Serve in a fruit cup over orange sherbet ice cream.

title: chunky macadamia nut white chocolate cookies
directions: Beat butter at medium speed with electric mixer until fluffy. Gradually add sugars, beating well.
Add egg and vanilla, mixing well.
Combine flour and next 3 ingredients.
Gradually add to butter mixture, mixing well.
Stir in morsels and nuts; drop by rounded teaspoonfuls onto lightly greased cookie sheets.
Bake at 350° for 8 to 10 minutes or until lightly browned.
Remove to wire racks to cool.
Yield: 3 dozen.

title: never fail pie crust
directions: Mix flour, sugar and salt.
Cut in Crisco to texture of small peas.
Add egg.
Mix together vinegar and ice water, then add to mix.
Bring ingredients together, mixing as little as possible. Divide dough.
Roll out to desired size on a lightly floured piece of waxed paper.
Makes 2 pies and 1 crust.
Bake crust 10 to 12 minutes in 425° oven.
Bake fruit pie 25 minutes in 375° oven, then remove foil that covers the edges of the pie.
Bake for 20 to 25 minutes more or until crust is golden.

title: fat free chocolate cake
directions: Dissolve coffee in boiling water.
Mix first 6 ingredients together; stir well.
Sift dry ingredients together.
Pour moist ingredients into dry ingredients; stir well.

title: coffee eggnog
directions: In a small bowl, beat egg whites until soft peaks form. Gradually beat in sugar, also forming stiff peaks.
In a large bowl, beat egg yolks until lemon colored.
Gradually beat in coffee, salt, vanilla, milk and 3/4 cup water.
Stir in egg whites mixture and whipped cream; mix well.
Serve well chilled with chocolate sprinkled over each serving.
Yields 12 servings.

title: lazy pierogi
directions: Chop bacon into very small pieces.
Fry until crispy.
Remove from pan and saute onion in bacon fat.
Set aside.
Add cabbage and sauerkraut in frying pan and stir.
(Add more bacon drippings.) Cover.
Cook down.
Add bacon and onions.
Blend in cooked noodles.

title: party cheese ball
directions: Combine cheeses; add other ingredients. Chill and shape into ball. Roll in chopped nuts. Makes a large ball or 3 or 4 log rolls.

title: shrimp rolls
directions: Rinse shrimp in cold water; drain thoroughly.
Divide rolls into
8 triangles on lightly floured pastry cloth.
Stretch each gently at wide edge.
Place shrimp, cheese and green pepper on wide edge of triangle.
Do not extend to edge (allow about 1/2-inch space at each side).
Sprinkle lightly with black pepper.

title: pecan waffles
directions: Sift the dry ingredients together.
Beat egg yolks until thick.
Combine beaten egg yolks with milk and melted butter. Stir into dry ingredients.
Add chopped pecans, mixing only until blended.
Beat egg whites until stiff and fold into batter.
Bake in hot waffle iron.
Serve with favorite syrup or topping.

title: pink stuff
directions: Stir all together and enjoy.
Keep refrigerated.
May use lime Jello.

title: stuffed onions(lo-fat)
directions: Using sharp knife, hollow out center or each onion leaving a 1/4-inch thick shell.
Place onions in an 8-inch square glass pan; set aside.
In a medium bowl, mix peas, mushrooms, carrots, thyme, pepper and granules. Fill onions with mixture.
Cover tightly and microwave on High 7 to 9 minutes until onions are tender and the stuffing is hot all the way through.
Makes 4 servings.

title: freezer slaw
directions: Shred the vegetables.
Sprinkle with salt.
Let stand 1 hour. Drain mix if water accumulates.
Combine remaining ingredients in a saucepan.
Bring to a boil 3 minutes.
Pour over cabbage mixture. Stir well.
Freeze in plastic bags or chill overnight to serve. Freezes up to 3 months.
Yield:
10 servings.

title: nanny harris' tea cakes
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In a large bowl, cream sugar, shortening, eggs and extract.
Gradually add flour, kneading until mixture is stiff enough to roll.
On a lightly floured surface, roll dough 1/4-inch thick.
Cut into desired shapes.
Place on greased cookie sheets.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes.
Makes 6 dozen.

title: corn pudding
directions: Beat eggs at room temperature.
Add flour.
Mix and add all other ingredients.
Cook at 325° for 1 hour and 15 minutes.
Let stand 10 minutes before serving.
Will thicken as it cools. Serves 6 to 8.

title: flank steak with coriander sauce
directions: Place flank steak in a large dish.
Combine garlic, oil and wine and pour over meat.
Refrigerate for 2 hours.
Combine coriander, olive oil, red onion, salt and pepper and let sit at room temperature for 30 minutes.
Grill meat over hot coals for 10 minutes.
Slice meat diagonally against the grain.
Drizzle with the coriander sauce.

title: lorna shinn's plum nutty
directions: Boil the ground orange (including peel) and water for 20 minutes.
Add plums, raisins and pectin and bring to a boil.
Add sugar.
Bring to a hard boil, stirring constantly, for 1 minute. Skim and add walnuts.
Seal in hot jars.

title: butter cookies
directions: Use ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake 6 minutes at 400°.
Cool.

title: crispy baked chicken
directions: Remove all skin from the chicken; rinse and dry the pieces thoroughly.
Dip in milk, mix cornflake crumbs with rosemary and pepper and roll in the seasoned crumbs.
Let stand briefly so coating will adhere.
Place chicken in an oiled baking pan (line pan with foil for easy clean up).
Do not crowd; pieces should not touch.
Bake at 400° for 45 minutes.
Crumbs will form a crisp skin.
Makes 4 servings.

title: crispy baked halibut
directions: Cut fish into 4 portions, pat dry and brush with oil.
In shallow dish, stir bread crumbs, Parmesan cheese, tarragon, paprika and pepper.
Dip fish to coat both sides.
Arrange on baking dish or pan.
Sprinkle leftover crumbs on top.
Bake at 450° for 8 to 12 minutes or until fish flakes easily.
Do not turn during baking.

title: little brown jug breakfast rolls
directions: Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle with nuts. Pull thawed bread into walnut size pieces. Fill pan with single layer of bread pieces.

title: tamale pie
directions: Mix together.
Pour over the top of the meat mixture; cook in oven until golden brown.

title: peanut blossoms
directions: Cream together shortening and peanut butter.
Gradually add sugars.
Mix well.
Add egg, milk and vanilla.
Beat well.
Blend in dry ingredients.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Roll in sugar. Place on ungreased cookie sheets.
Bake at 375° for 8 minutes. Remove from oven and place solid milk chocolate candy kiss on top, pressing down so cookie cracks around edges.
Return to oven. Bake 2 to 5 minutes longer.

title: pasta with shrimp and broccoli
directions: Steam broccoli 6 minutes (until a little soft).
Saute garlic in olive oil along with shrimp.
Then add broccoli and continue to saute for a few minutes.
Cook and drain pasta.
Add the pasta to the rest of the ingredients. Saute for another 5 minutes or so. Add at least 1 cup of Romano cheese (more if you like).
Mix well, add salt and pepper to taste.

title: skillet cabbage
directions: In a large skillet, add oil, onion, pepper and tomato.
Saute. Add cut up cabbage and water. Season with salt and pepper to taste.
Cook with lid and simmer until cabbage is done.

title: company pickle chunks
directions: Cover cucumbers with boiling water; let stand until next morning.
Repeat this procedure 3 times (days).
On fifth day, drain and slice cucumbers into 1/2-inch cubes or pieces.
Combine remaining ingredients (sugar, spices, salt and vinegar).
Bring to boiling point and pour over cucumbers; let stand 2 days.
On third day, bring to boiling and seal in hot, sterilized jars.
Hot water bath for 5 minutes.

title: ice cream in a can
directions: Mix well, except salt; put in a 1 pound coffee can.
Put cover on tight and seal with duct tape.

title: kahlua
directions: Put water and sugars in saucepan.
Boil 5 minutes.
Cool 5 minutes.
Add coffee with wire whisk.
Cool completely.
Add vodka and vanilla.
Age 2 to 5 days.
Makes 5 1/2 cups.

title: rotini bake
directions: Mix all five ingredients.
Put in 13 x 9-inch baking dish.
Top with (optional) additional cheese if you like.
Bake in 350° oven for 25 minutes.
Super easy, super good.
Serve with garlic bread.

title: spaghetti salad
directions: Break pasta into 3-inch pieces; cook as directed.
Drain and rinse with cold water and refrigerate.
Dice vegetables and mix into pasta; add jar of Salad Supreme and Italian dressing.
Mix well and refrigerate overnight.
Will last forever!

title: mozzarella rice balls
directions: In a medium bowl, combine rice, Parmesan cheese, roasted peppers, egg, salt and pepper.
Shape rice balls using 1/3 cup rice mixture for each ball. Gently insert cheese cube into center of each ball.
Re-shape rice mixture around cheese cube to cover completely.
Coat balls with bread crumbs.

title: green beans with bacon
directions: In a microwave-safe bowl, combine the first six ingredients. Cover and microwave on high for 6 minutes or until the beans are tender.
Sprinkle with bacon.

title: coconut and pineapple pie
directions: Preheat oven to 350°. In a large bowl, mix together butter, sugar, flour, eggs, pineapple, coconut, salt and vanilla. Pour the mixture into pie shell. Bake 40 to 50 minutes until set. Cover the pie with aluminum foil if the crust and filling get too brown.

title: vegetarian lunch
directions: Cook macaroni from dinner according to package directions. Drain thoroughly.
While macaroni is cooking, melt 1/4 cup butter in large skillet.
Add vegetables.
Cook over low heat, stirring occasionally, until crisp-tender.
Remove from heat and add macaroni.
Stir in remaining 1/4 cup butter and milk.
Sprinkle contents of cheese sauce packet over top.
Continue stirring until cheese is thoroughly blended.
Add pimento and mix gently. If necessary, return skillet to very low heat and continue stirring.
Heat until mixture reaches serving temperature.

title: candied apples on a stick
directions: You will need 10 to 12 wood skewers.

title: shrimp salad
directions: Place prepared shrimp in 2 quarts of rapidly boiling salted water; cook 4 to 6 minutes.
Drain and cool.
Cut each shrimp into 3 to 5 pieces, depending on original size.
Add other ingredients, mixing well.
Refrigerate 3 to 4 hours before serving.
Yield: 6 to 8 servings.

title: peach cake
directions: Mix egg and milk together.
Sift together flour, baking powder and salt.
Cut in margarine or butter (as you would do for a pie crust).
Mix sugar and cinnamon.
Line the pan with peaches (in rows).
Spread flour mixture on peaches.
Sprinkle cinnamon and sugar over peaches.
Bake in large, glass baking dish at 350° for 30 to 40 minutes or until done.

title: irish soda bread
directions: Preheat oven to 425°.
Brush baking sheet with butter. Combine flour, soda and salt; mix well.
Add buttermilk; mix. Turn onto lightly floured board.
Pat into circular loaf, 8-inches round x 1 1/2-inches thick.
Cut x into top of loaf, 1/2-inch deep.
Bake 45 minutes.

title: creole kisses
directions: Add sugar gradually to the beaten egg whites.
Add vanilla and chopped nuts and drop by spoonfuls onto foil covered baking sheet. Bake 20 to 30 minutes at 350°.

title: brown rice
directions: Mix together and bake for 30 minutes at 350°.

title: chicken monahan
directions: Combine flour and pepper in a bag for shaking.
Shake each piece of chicken in flour until coated.
Melt butter in baking dish.
Add flour coated chicken to baking dish (skin side down). Bake 30 minutes at 350°.
While chicken is baking, combine soup, mushroom sauce and water in a pan and heat.
After 30 minutes, turn chicken over.
Pour off any remaining butter and cover with gravy.
Bake for an additional 30 minutes at 350°.

title: beef nacho casserole
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Brown meat and drain.
Stir in salsa, corn and chili powder.
Layer 1/2 each of meat mixture, chips and cheese in 2-quart casserole.
Repeat layers.
Bake 20 minutes or until thoroughly heated.
Top with shredded lettuce and chopped tomatoes, if desired.
Makes 6 servings.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook vegetables until tender.
Layer vegetables in a casserole dish; add chopped chicken.
Mix 3 tablespoons chicken broth with soup.
Pour over chicken.
Top with canned biscuits.
Bake until biscuits are brown, about 30 to 45 minutes at 350°.

title: corn chowder
directions: Cook vegetables in water for ten minutes.
Melt butter; stir in flour until thickened, 1 minute.
Add cheese and milk, stirring, until cheese is melted.
Stir in corn; heat.
Do not boil.
Add bacon.
Serves 8.

title: rosemary's frozen salad
directions: Cream together the cream cheese, milk, sugar and salt.
Add whipped cream and fold in pineapple and relish.
Pour into a 9 x 9-inch baking dish or individual paper baking cups.
Freeze.

title: chop suey
directions: Brown meat and add celery, onion and 1/2 cup water (15 minutes).
Add bean sprouts, vegetables, mushrooms, gravy, sugar, soy sauce and molasses.
Cook until warm.
Serve over rice.

title: hamburger casserole
directions: Brown meat and onion; pour off grease.
Cook macaroni.
In large casserole dish, combine meat, macaroni, soup, tomato sauce, catsup, mustard, salt and pepper.
Cook for 1 hour at 325°, covered.

title: creamy banana pudding
directions: In large bowl, combine sweetened condensed milk and water. Add pudding mix; beat until blended.
Chill 5 minutes.
Fold in Cool Whip.

title: greek style orzo with spinach and tomatoes
directions: Use tomatoes held at room temperature until fully ripe; core and coarsely chop (makes about 2 cups), set aside.
Cook orzo according to package instructions; drain and set aside.
In nonstick skillet, heat oil until hot.
Add onion and garlic; cook, stirring occasionally, until crisp, about 5 minutes.
Stir in chicken broth, oregano, salt, black pepper, reserved tomatoes and orzo.
Cook until tomatoes are slightly softened, about 3 minutes. Stir in spinach; cook until heated through, about 3 minutes.
Stir in cheese and serve hot.
Yield:
Four to six portions with 348 calories per portion.

title: barbecue beans
directions: Brown hamburger, bacon and onion.
Add pepper, pork and beans, kidney beans, lima beans, sugars, catsup, barbecue sauce, pinch of salt and mustard.
Bake in slow oven for 1 to 1 1/2 hours or slow crock-pot for 3 to 4 hours.
Serves 6 to 8.
Great with hamburgers.
Freezes well.

title: chicken casserole
directions: Cook the bell pepper, onion and celery in a little chicken broth and the margarine.
In casserole dish, put layer of macaroni, layer of vegetables and layer of chicken.
Pour 1/2 of the soup which has been diluted with the milk.
Repeat layer of macaroni, vegetables and chicken, then remaining soup.
Sprinkle cheese on top.
Bake for 30 minutes at 350° (you can add 1/2 cup ham to this).
tags: amount of chicken broth or water

title: german apple cake
directions: Beat until fluffy oil and eggs.
Add sugar and vanilla.
Beat well.
Add flour, soda, cinnamon and salt.
Fold in nuts and apples.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour in 9 x 13-inch pan.

title: feather rolls
directions: Put yeast in warm water and set aside.
Beat eggs until light and add yeast.
Mix sugar, salt and shortening until crumbly like pie crust, then add 3 cups flour and egg mixture.
Mix well and add the other cup of flour.
Work in well.
Cover and let stand in refrigerator overnight.
Divide into thirds.
Roll out to 1/8-inch thick.
Cut into triangles and roll from large to small end and place on a greased cookie sheet and let raise for 3 hours.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.
Yield:
3 dozen.

title: chili from aunt willie
directions: Brown meat in fat and add flour, comino seed, paprika, red pepper and chili powder.
Put into large pot and add remaining ingredients.
Cover with water and cook slowly 3 to 4 hours.

title: twice baked potatoes(grandchildren's favorite)
directions: Peel and slice potatoes.
Cook as if you are creaming potatoes. When done, whip and add salt and pepper.
Add sour cream, shredded cheese, bacon bits and parsley flakes.
If needed to thin, add salad dressing.
I like to add at least 2 or 3 tablespoons salad dressing for flavor.
Pour into 13 x 9-inch baking dish or divide and freeze part, if desired and top with cheese and Bac*Os and chives when ready to bake.
Bake 30 minutes until set.

title: cream cheese pound cake
directions: Combine all ingredients.
Mix well.
Pour into a tube or Bundt pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour and 20 minutes.

title: texas chili con carne
directions: Brown the meat, garlic and onion in a 400° oven for 3/4 hour, or until well browned.
Stir frequently.
Add flour; blend well. Add remaining ingredients; stir well.
Cover; lower heat to 350° and cook for 1 1/2 hours.

title: margaret's broccoli
directions: Cook broccoli for 5 minutes after bringing to boil (no salt). Mix all other ingredients together.
Add well drained broccoli. Top with Ritz cracker crumbs and dot with butter.
Cook at 350° for 1 hour.

title: chocolate pie
directions: Sift flour, salt, sugar and cornstarch.
Combine with hot milk and cook until thick.
Add chocolate, broken very small.
Cook until smooth.
Cook another minute; cool.
Add vanilla and pour into baked shell.

title: mexican rice
directions: Mix together and bake at 350° for approximately 30 minutes. Serves 6.

title: crab stuffed potatoes
directions: Bake potatoes until done. Split in half lengthwise and scoop out pulp.
Reserve shells.
Mash potato pulp with butter, milk, onion and salt until mixture is smooth and creamy.
Stir in grated cheese and crabmeat.
Fill shells with mixture.
Sprinkle with paprika and bake at 450° for 15 minutes.

title: mexican corn bread
directions: Mix all together and pour into large greased pan or two skillets.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 40 to 50 minutes.

title: thompson's summer pasta
directions: Combine first 8 ingredients and let set at room temperature 1 to 2 hours.
Cook linguine. When linguine is ready to serve, drain and toss with tomato and cheese mixture.
Serve with Parmesan cheese.

title: chocolate caramelita bars
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Grease 9 x 13-inch baking pan.
Combine first seven ingredients; mix well.
Reserve 1 cup; press remaining into bottom of prepared pan.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes or until light brown.
Cool 10 minutes.
Top with nuts and chocolate pieces.
Mix caramel and 1/4 cup flour until smooth; drizzle over chocolate pieces to within 1/4 inch of pan edges.
Sprinkle reserved oat mixture on top.
Bake 18 to 20 minutes or until golden brown. Cool.

title: lemon pineapple salad
directions: Dissolve jello in heated pineapple juice and pineapple.
Stir in softened cream cheese until completely melted.
When cool, add salt, nuts and whipped cream.
Place in refrigerator until set.

title: marinated beef strips
directions: Cut beef into thin strips; cut onions into thin slices and separate into rings.
Combine beef, onion, salt and pepper. Sprinkle with lemon juice; stir in sour cream.
Chill.
Serve on lettuce-lined dish with rye bread.

title: stir-fried chicken and vegetables
directions: Slice chicken into 1/4-inch strips.
Heat oil in skillet at high setting.
Add celery, green pepper, onion, salt and ginger. Cook, stirring quickly and frequently, until tender-crisp, about 3 minutes.
Remove vegetables.
Stir-fry chicken in oil left in skillet until chicken turns white, about 3 to 5 minutes.
Return vegetables to skillet.
Add bean sprouts, water chestnuts, bouillon and 1/2 cup water.
In a cup, blend cornstarch and soy sauce.
Stir into skillet; cook until mixture thickens.
Stir constantly.
Serve with rice or noodles.

title: gumdrops
directions: Soften gelatin in 3/4 cup cold water.
Mix remaining 1/4 cup water, sugar and corn syrup in saucepan, stirring until sugar is dissolved.
Cook until soft ball stage (medium heat).
Add gelatin; mix and stir over heat for 1 minute.
Stir in color and flavorings.
Set aside to cool.

title: barbecue meats
directions: Place chops or meat into a crock-pot.
Pour a little sauce on each piece.
Add no water.
Cover and cook approximately 8 hours on low.
Finger lickin'!

title: monkey bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Mix sugar, cinnamon, melted butter, nuts and raisins in a 2-quart casserole dish.
Cut each biscuit into quarters.
Lightly fold (do not stir) biscuits into sugar mixture until coated.
Bake for 30 minutes or until center biscuits are fully cooked.
Remove from casserole dish onto plate.

title: roast lamb(arni psito)
directions: Cut incisions in meat and fill with garlic mixed with salt and pepper.
Rub leg of lamb with lemon juice and sprinkle with additional salt and pepper.
Place in roasting pan with water and top with butter.
Bake at 450° until browned, lower to 300°, cover and bake until done.
When meat is half cooked, peeled and quartered potatoes can be placed around meat.
Uncover 10 minutes before serving to allow potatoes to brown.
Makes 6-8 servings.

title: beef casserole
directions: Brown ground beef, then drain.
Add tomatoes, parsley flakes, onion, ketchup and steak sauce.
Let this mixture simmer for 30 minutes.
Pour over cooked noodles, then add cream of mushroom soup and mix lightly.
After mixture is mixed, top with shredded cheese. Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: ham and green bean casserole
directions: Peel potatoes; slice and line the bottom of pan.
Layer green beans, onion, ham, cheese and cream of mushroom soup.
Finish with another layer of cheese on top and bake at 375° for 1 hour.

title: china's strawberry salad
directions: Combine all ingredients except nuts. Beat until smooth; spread in a dish and add nuts on top and chill. For a different salad change jello and pie filling to cherry.

title: pita bread
directions: Mix all the above together.
Add more flour up to 4 cups to make a soft dough.
Roll out onto a floured board.
Knead 10 minutes.
Place dough into a greased bowl.
Cover and let rise 2 hours until double in bulk.
Punch down; let rest 10 minutes. Divide into 6 parts.
Roll out into 8 or 9-inch circle.
Place on ungreased cookie sheet.
Bake at 450° for 5 to 8 minutes or lightly brown.

title: snoberry cookies
directions: Mix together in order given and beat 2 minutes.
Stir in nuts, cherries and coconut.
Drop on greased cookie sheet.
Bake at 375° for 12 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all ingredients except ketchup and shape into loaf in shallow baking dish.
Spread ketchup on top.
Bake about 1 hour in 400° oven.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Beat eggs until foamy.
Add oil, sugar, zucchini and vanilla. Mix well with beaters.
Sift dry ingredients together and add to egg mixture along with nuts.
Divide batter into two loaves.
Bake at 325° for 45 to 60 minutes.

title: corn light bread
directions: Mix dry ingredients.
Make a hole in the center and add buttermilk, egg and melted shortening.
Beat well.
Pour into greased loaf pan.
Bake 50 minutes at 370°.
Cool a few minutes in pan and then turn out before it sweats in pan.

title: vegetable noodle casserole
directions: Cook noodles according to package directions; drain and set aside.
Saute celery, onion, green pepper and broccoli in oil until tender.
Stir in milk, salt, pepper and cheese.
Spoon into a lightly greased 1 1/2 quart baking dish.
Cover and bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Sprinkle with bread crumbs and drizzle with butter; bake uncovered for 10 minutes.
Yields 4 to 6 servings.

title: oriental steak soup
directions: In Dutch oven, combine beef, onion, celery, basil, bouillon, soy sauce and 8 cups water.
Bring to boiling.
Reduce heat. Simmer uncovered for 1 1/2 hours; add frozen vegetables and mushrooms.
Return mixture to boiling.
Reduce heat and simmer for 15 minutes.
Serves 6.

title: linguini salad
directions: Mix all ingredients together; refrigerate overnight.

title: tater tot casserole
directions: Brown ground meat. Mix with tomato sauce and paste and whole kernel corn. Fry Tater Tots and place in the bottom of casserole dish. Cover with ground meat, tomato sauce and paste and whole kernel corn. Cover with cheese and place in oven or microwave until cheese melts.

title: pineapple coconut pie
directions: Mix
all ingredients, except margarine.
Melt margarine and pour into unbaked pie shell.
Pour pie mixture over butter or margarine.
Bake
at
450° for 10 minutes.
Reduce oven to 350° and
bake
45 minutes, until golden.
Makes 1 large or 2 small pies.

title: peanut butter balls
directions: Melt in a saucepan.
Dip balls and put on wax paper to harden.

title: hot rolls
directions: Dissolve the yeast and 1 teaspoon sugar in the warm water. Mix all the ingredients together and let stand for 1 hour.
Salt mixture to taste.
Knead well, and make out into buns.
Let stand 1 1/2 hours.
Bake at 425° until golden brown.

title: chocolate pizza
directions: Microwave chips and 14 ounces almond bark in 2-quart microwave-safe bowl on High 2 minutes; stir.
Continue microwaving 1 to 2 minutes or until smooth when stirred, stirring every 30 seconds.
Stir in marshmallows, cereal and peanuts.
Pour onto greased 12-inch pizza pan.
Top with cherries.
Sprinkle with coconut.
Microwave remaining 2 ounces almond bark with oil in 1-cup glass measuring cup 1 minute.
Stir.
Continue microwaving 30 seconds to 1 minute or until smooth when stirred, stirring every 15 seconds.
Drizzle over coconut.
Refrigerate until firm.
Store at room temperature.
Makes 10 to 12 servings.

title: corn casserole
directions: Fry bacon crisp; chop in small bits.
Drain oil from pan.
Add eggs and corn and mix.
Roll crackers in foil with rolling pin until crushed.
Press on top of other ingredients.
Melt margarine and sprinkle over crackers.
Bake at 425° for approximately 30 minutes.

title: pecan clusters
directions: Combine in large bowl the kisses and Marshmallow Creme and set aside. Combine milk, sugar and margarine and bring to a boil. Boil for 8 minutes, stirring constantly. Pour over kisses and Creme until melted and well blended. Add pecans. Drop by teaspoon onto wax paper. This must be done fast to keep candy from getting hard. Makes over 100 small pieces.

title: watergate salad
directions: Mix everything together in a large bowl until evenly mixed (will be green).
This can be spooned into individual dishes or left in a large dish for serving.
Refrigerate.
Serves 6+.

title: chicken noodle soup
directions: Cook chicken until done.
Take chicken off bones (keep broth). Mix chicken, broth, chicken noodles, onion and cream of chicken soup.
Salt and pepper to taste.
Simmer on low heat until noodles are tender.
Serve while hot.

title: raspberry ribbon salad
directions: Dissolve gelatin in water.
Stir in raspberries, pineapple and nuts.
Blend well.
Spoon 1 1/2 cups gelatin mixture into lightly oiled 8-cup mold.
Chill and set.
Spread 1 cup sour cream over gelatin.
Spoon half of remaining raspberry mixture over sour cream layer.
Chill until set.
Spread 1 cup sour cream over raspberry layer.
Spoon last of raspberry mixture over sour cream.
Chill until firm.
Unmold onto lettuce leaves.
Yields 14 servings.

title: ann's pecan pie
directions: Combine ingredients.
Pour into pie crust.
Bake at 325° for 1 hour.

title: fudge brownies
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
In large saucepan, over low heat, melt 1 cup chips with margarine.
Remove from heat.
Add biscuit mix, sweetened condensed milk, egg and vanilla.
Stir in remaining 1 cup chips.
Turn into well-greased 13 x 9-inch baking pan.
Bake 20 to 25 minutes or until brownies begin to pull away from sides of pan.
Cool.

title: hamburger soup
directions: Brown beef and drain excess fat.
Add next 6 ingredients. Cover and simmer for 15 minutes.
Stir in raw macaroni.
Simmer for 30 minutes.

title: peach salad
directions: Mix jello with 2 cups liquid and let partially set.
Add cream cheese and sour cream.
Mash peaches and add all ingredients.
Use blender and blend well.
Pour into molds and let set.
Apricots may be used instead of peaches.

title: beef cheese ball
directions: *Jar is blue, found in canned meat section.

title: cornbread salad
directions: Bake
and crumble cool cornbread.
Mix all other ingredients and
add
Miracle
Whip salad dressing to your desire. Refrigerate.

title: mexican fire and ice casserole
directions: Preheat oven to
350°.	Combine all ingredients and mix well. Bake in 1-quart casserole covered about 25 minutes.

title: chewy cheesecake swirl brownies
directions: Mix the brownies (acccording to package directions - type can be your choice; toffee brownie mix is really good, low-fat kind works fine). Spread mixture in a pan, reserving 3/4 cup of the mix. Add the chocolate chips to the reserved mix and set aside. Mix together the cream cheese, sugar, butter, egg yolks and vanilla. Spread the mix on top of the brownie mix in the pan. Then drop spoonfuls of the reserved mix with chips on top of the cheese mix. Run a knife through the mixture making swirls. Bake at 325° for 35 to 45 minutes or until done.

title: toffee bars
directions: Beat all ingredients until well mixed.
Pat evenly onto greased 10 x 15-inch cookie sheet.
Beat egg white and brush over dough.
Sprinkle 1/2 cup finely chopped almonds or walnuts and pat gently into dough.

title: potatoes a la wade
directions: Bake in oven at 425°
for 35 minutes.

title: jello salad(pink stuff)
