directions: Mix the pie filling, milk, pineapple tidbits and pecans. Fold in the Cool Whip. Pour in a pretty bowl. Store in refrigerator several hours or overnight. Then serve and eat all you can.

title: pizza
directions: Roll out dough and stretch onto 14-inch pan.
Brush with olive oil or pesto.
Arrange tomatoes, meat, peppers and artichoke hearts evenly over pizza.
Season with oregano, salt and pepper.
Sprinkle cheese evenly over pizza.
Bake at 425° for 20 to 25 minutes.

title: black bing cherry pie
directions: Mix thoroughly all ingredients except whipping cream, sugar and vanilla; whip whipping cream, add sugar and vanilla.
Fold into cherry mix.
Pour into prepared graham cracker crumb crust.
Set in refrigerator for several hours or overnight.

title: morning glory muffins
directions: Preheat oven to 400°.
Beat eggs, oil and almond flavoring with wire whisk and set aside.
Mix dry ingredients in large mixing bowl.
Add peeled and grated carrots, apple (peeled and grated), raisins, nuts and coconut.
Add egg mixture and stir until moistened.
Put in prepared muffin pan and bake 15 to 20 minutes.
Makes 18 muffins.

title: snappy green beans
directions: In medium saucepan, cover green beans with water. Cook until al dente (crisp, not mushy). Drain. Add hot Italian dressing. Enjoy.

title: artichoke squares
directions: Drain marinade from one jar of artichokes into frying pan. Chop all artichokes, set aside.
Add onion and garlic to frying pan and saute till golden; about 5 minutes.
In a bowl, beat eggs with fork, add bread crumbs, salt, pepper, oregano and
Tabasco sauce. Stir in cheese, parsley, artichokes and onion mixture. Turn into a greased 7 x 11 inch baking dish.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until set.
Let cool.
May reheat in pan at 325° for 10 to 12 minutes to serve warm.
Makes 3 dozen.

title: czechoslovakian casserole
directions: Have the sour cream and cottage cheese near room temperature.

title: raspberry coffee cake
directions: Grease and flour an 8-inch spring-form pan.
In a large bowl, stir together 1 1/2 cups flour, 1/2 cup sugar, baking soda, baking powder and salt.
With a pastry blender or two knives, cut in 1/2 cup butter until pieces are the size of small peas.
Make a well in the center of mixture and set aside.

title: oatmeal bread
directions: Combine boiling
water,
oats,
whole
wheat flour, brown sugar, salt and butter.
Cool
until lukewarm.
Dissolve yeast in 1/2 cup warm water.
Add to
batter.
Add
enough
flour
to
make a smooth, elastic dough.
Let rise until
double in bulk.
Shape into 2 loaves and put in greased pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes.
When bread is done, grease top with butter and
cover with cloth until cool.
If desired, you may use more brown flour and less white.

title: microwave oven-crispy chicken
directions: Coat chicken with coating mix according to directions. Arrange chicken in an 8-inch glass dish with meatier portions toward the edges. Cover with waxed paper. Cook on High 16 to 18 minutes or until done.

title: turkey and wild rice soup
directions: In a large stockpot, bring the chicken broth to a simmer. Heat oil in a small skillet over medium-high heat. Add the onions and carrots; saut for 10 minutes. Add the turmeric and ground red pepper; saut for 2 more minutes. Add the sauted mixture to the broth. Simmer 10 minutes. Add remaining ingredients and simmer 10 minutes more. Makes 6 servings, 1 cup size.

title: taco salad
directions: Spread cream cheese on small tray. Chop lettuce and cover with cream cheese.
Pour the salsa over lettuce.
Sprinkle cheese over salsa. Cut up the tomatoes and place on top of salad.

title: pasta e fagioli(pasta and beans)
directions: Cover bottom of a 6-quart kettle with olive oil.
Add garlic, basil, oregano and fennel.
Cook until garlic is lightly browned. Cook pasta al dente.
Drain well and set aside.
Add beans and pasta to olive oil mixture.
Add chicken broth and mix well.
Add cheese, more broth if needed, salt to taste and 1/2 teaspoon black pepper.

title: turkey soup
directions: Cook turkey carcass in water for 1 1/2 hours.
Strain and refrigerate.
Clear fat off cold broth.
Return to heat and add the remaining ingredients.
Cook 1/2 hour longer.

title: quick apple cobbler
directions: Grease a 2-quart baking dish with margarine.
Pour in apple pie filling.
Sprinkle with cinnamon if desired.
Combine remaining ingredients and crumble over pie filling.
Bake at 350° for 30 minutes or until golden brown.
Serve with ice cream or Cool Whip.

title: chocolate eclair cake
directions: Mix pudding and milk together, then fold in Cool Whip.
Line bottom of casserole dish with graham crackers, then spread half the mixture over that.
Put another layer of graham crackers and then the other half of the mixture, and cover the top with graham crackers.
Melt frosting in microwave (about 25 to 35 seconds) and pour over the top.
Refrigerate overnight or until chilled.

title: six cup salad
directions: Drain juice from pineapple and oranges.
Mix, refrigerate for 3 to 4 hours.
Garnish with the cherries.

title: string bean casserole
directions: Put onion rings on top of all other ingredients in a casserole.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes until heated through.

title: easy lasagna
directions: Brown ground beef and drain.
Add water, sauce and salt. Bring to boil.
In 2-quart (11 3/4 x 7 1/2-inch) baking dish, layer hot sauce, uncooked lasagna noodles, Ricotta cheese and Mozzarella cheese.
Repeat layers, ending with sauce.
Top with Parmesan cheese and grated Mozzarella cheese.
Cover dish with foil and bake at 375° for 1 hour.
Makes 6 servings.

title: crab quiche appetizers
directions: Using small muffin tins, shape enough dough into each tin. Mix all ingredients the night before serving quiches.
Pour into shells.
Bake at 350° until set.

title: magic puff tuna sandwich
directions: Mix Bisquick, mayonnaise and egg.
Stir in remaining ingredients except bread.
Spread ingredients evenly over 6 slices bread.
Bake at 450° for 10 minutes or until puffy and golden brown.

title: *shrimp mold
directions: Heat can of undiluted soup.
Dissolve gelatin in cold water. Add gelatin mixture to soup.
Add cheese and blend well with wire whisk.
Add vegetables and shrimp and mix well.
Pour into well-greased mold or pan.
Refrigerate for 8 hours.

title: ma neeley's chocolate pie
directions: For each cup of milk, use 2 level tablespoons of any coarse cereal such as rice, cornmeal, cracked wheat, oatmeal or barley and 2 level tablespoons of any sweetening, such as any sugar, syrup, honey or molasses.
Flavor with nutmeg, cinnamon or any spice and season with salt.
Put flavored and seasoned milk in double boiler, or if a large amount is being prepared, put in kettle.
Add cereal and sweeting.
Cook about 1 hour without covering.

title: oatmeal pie crust
directions: Mix flour and salt in bowl.
Cut in shortening until crumbly. Add oats; mix well.
Add water, mixing well.
Shape into a ball. Press over bottom and sides of 8-inch pie pan.
Bake at 425° for 15 minutes.
May fill with pie filling before baking and bake as directed for filling.

title: candy
directions: Melt butterscotch morsels.
Add peanuts and noodles.
Mix well.
Spoon onto wax paper.

title: bing cherry salad
directions: Bring sugar, vinegar and oil to boil.
Continue to cook until sugar is dissolved.
Pour liquid mixture
over chopped cabbage, onion and carrot.
Marinate overnight.

title: luscious apricot bars
directions: Cover apricots with water and boil 10 minutes or until soft. Cool and chop into fairly small pieces.
Mix together the butter, sugar and 1 cup flour.
Press into bottom of an 8-inch square pan. Bake at 350° for 25 minutes.

title: pretzel salad
directions: Thaw frozen strawberries.
Mix the pretzels, butter and sugar. Pour into a 9 x 12-inch baking dish and bake at 400° for 4 to 6 minutes.
Cool.
Cream the cream cheese and sugar together; fold in Cool Whip.
Spread over cooled pretzel layer.
Prepare strawberry jello with 2 cups boiling water.
Add frozen strawberries.
Pour onto cheese mixture when jello is slightly thickened.

title: tuna-noodle casserole
directions: Combine all ingredients, except cheese.
Pour into a greased casserole dish.
Top with cheese.
Bake at 375° for 25 minutes or until brown.

title: 7 layer bar cookies(no mixing - make right in baking pan!)
directions: Melt margarine in a 13 x 9 x 2-inch pan.
Sprinkle cracker crumbs over margarine to make crust.
Sprinkle chopped walnuts evenly over crumbs.
Scatter chocolate and butterscotch chips over nuts.
Sprinkle coconut evenly over chips.
Pour sweetened condensed milk evenly over coconut.
Bake in a 350° oven for 25 minutes or until lightly browned on top.
Cool in pan 15 to 30 minutes.
Cut into small bars.

title: tasty thins or pecan squares
directions: Cream margarine, butter and sugar.
Add egg yolk, flour and vanilla.
Mix well.
Spread thin in 2 greased pans (15 1/2 x 10 1/2 x 1-inch).
Brush egg white over this pastry.
Sprinkle nuts on top.
Bake at 300° for approximately 30 minutes or until golden.
Cut in small squares while hot.
Cool on rack.
Recipe from Hills and Pines Garden Club, Raleigh, North Carolina.

title: sugar cookie dessert
directions: Bake sugar cookies according to directions.
Cool.
Beat cream cheese until softened; add sugar.
Spread on cookies.
Top with your favorite fruit.

title: zucchini bread
directions: Mix all ingredients well.
Add nuts or raisins if desired. Bake in two loaf pans for 1 hour at 325°.
Can also be frozen.

title: easter eggs
directions: Shape into balls and let set, then coat with chocolate.

title: chocolate zucchini drops
directions: Cream sugars, butter, salt and eggs.
Add dry ingredients plus rest of items.
Drop by spoonfuls onto greased sheet and bake at 350° until edges are golden brown.

title: buttermilk rolls
directions: Dissolve yeast in water.
Sift flour, baking powder, soda, salt and sugar; add Crisco, yeast water and buttermilk.
Make like biscuit dough and let set in refrigerator overnight.
Melt butter in pan; roll out rolls and dip in butter; let rise until double (about 4 hours).
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: red velvet cake
directions: Cream together (# 1 - 4), then add a little at a time (# 5). Then add slowly (# 6). Add (# 7 - 10), mix all together well, and bake in 3, 8-inch baking pans, at 350 degrees for 25 to 30 minutes.

title: sweet pickles
directions: Cut cucumbers in 1-inch slices and soak in salt water overnight.
For 1 quart of cukes, use 1 pint of vinegar (diluted if strong), 1/2 cup sugar, 2 level teaspoons mixed pickling spice and a little salt.
Put vinegar, sugar, salt and spices on stove.
When it boils, add cukes and stir until they turn color.
Put in jar with lid lightly screwed on.
Drain and reheat vinegar for 2 days. Then seal.
Just reheat the vinegar, not the cukes.
Makes a very crisp sweet pickle.

title: easy jello salad
directions: *Use pineapple for lime jello or use mandarin oranges for orange jello.

title: elegant beef tenderloin
directions: Rub tenderloin with 2 tablespoons of softened butter. Place tenderloin on a rack in a shallow pan. Bake at 400° for 20 minutes. In a small saucepan, cook scallions in remaining butter until tender. Add soy sauce, mustard and pepper. Stir in sherry. Heat just to boiling. Pour sauce over tenderloin and return to oven. Bake 25 to 30 minutes for medium-rare. Baste frequently while cooking. Serves 4.

title: snack crackers
directions: Combine dressing mix and oil.
Add lemon pepper, dill weed and garlic powder.
Spread on cookie sheet or 9 x 13-inch pan and place in 150° oven for 15 or 20 minutes.

title: crock-pot chicken parisienne
directions: Sprinkle chicken with salt, pepper and paprika. Place in crock-pot. Mix wine, soup and mushrooms until well combined. Pour over chicken. Sprinkle with paprika. Cover and cook on low 7 to 9 hours or high 3 to 4 hours. Last 30 minutes, remove chicken and stir in sour cream mixture. Replace chicken. Cook last 30 minutes. Serve over rice or noodles.

title: french-fried dill pickles
directions: Press pickle slices between paper towels to remove excess moisture.
Set aside.

title: chicken-chipped beef casserole
directions: Line 8 or 9-inch square casserole with dried beef.
Wrap each chicken breast with lengthwise strip of bacon and arrange in casserole.
Mix soup and sour cream together and pour over chicken.
Bake, uncovered, at 250° for four hours.

title: cole slaw
directions: This is very good with fried fish.
You may add 3 or 4 radishes and some green pepper very finely chopped, not over a teaspoon, if you like.

title: 4 bean bake
directions: Mix all ingredients into crock-pot.
Cook on slow for 4 hours or in 350° oven for 1 hour.

title: chicken cacciatore
directions: Broil chicken, skin side up, for 5 to 10 minutes.
Make a sauce of all the other ingredients except mushrooms and Sweet 'N Low. Add chicken to sauce and simmer in covered skillet for 3/4 hour. Add mushrooms.
Cook uncovered for 10 to 15 minutes.
Add Sweet 'N Low and serve.
Serves 3. Each portion contains 3 ounces of dinner vegetable.
Freezes well if made ahead.

title: grandma's tea cakes
directions: In a mixing bowl, cream shortening with sugar.
Add eggs and extract.
Beat well.
Add remaining ingredients.
Mix well.
Chill for 1 to 2 hours.

title: mexican chicken casserole
directions: Make a sauce of soups, broth and Ro-Tel.
Place in 9 x 12-inch casserole dish in layers:
chicken, Doritos, onion and cheese. Pour sauce over all.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: four layer dessert
directions: Melt 1 stick margarine, mix with nuts and flour.
Put evenly in pan and bake.
Let cool.

title: meat macaroni
directions: In skillet, melt butter or margarine.
Saute chopped onions in butter until tender, but not brown.
Stir in soup, tomatoes, thyme and pepper.
Add macaroni and meat.
Add cheese.
Bake uncovered at 350° for 35 to 40 minutes.

title: chili verde
directions: In large pot heat bacon fat; saute onions until soft.
Add pork cubes.
Cook for 5 minutes.
Sprinkle flour over pork and onions, cook until the pork is browned and onions are golden.
Stir in the cumin, garlic and chilies, mixing well.
Add the chicken stock and stir.
Add salt and pepper.
Lower heat and simmer, uncovered, until meat is tender (about 1 1/2 to 2 hours).
Serve with warm tortillas.

title: scampi-style shrimp
directions: In skillet, cook onions and garlic in oil and butter mixture. Add shrimp and cook until shrimp are pink.
Add lemon juice and salt. Serve over wild or white rice.

title: chocolate delight
directions: Mix all ingredients together, then spread in a 9 x 12-inch pan.
Bake at 350° for 15 minutes.
Cool.

title: crab lasagna
directions: Cook lasagna noodles according to package directions.
While the noodles cook, mix the cream cheese (room temperature), cottage cheese, soup, shrimp, beaten eggs, basil, onion and salt and pepper.
Place half the noodles in greased 9 x 13-inch pan.
Cover with half the cheese mixture, then the crab.
Cover with remaining noodles; then the rest of cheese mixture.
Bake at 350° for 15 to 20 minutes.
Sprinkle with Cheddar cheese to cover top.
Bake 30 minutes more.
Let rest 10 to 15 minutes before serving.

title: pickled yellow squash
directions: Combine squash, onions, pepper and salt.
Let stand for 1 hour, then drain.
Combine vinegar, celery seed, sugar and mustard seed, the bring to a boil.
Put squash mixture in clean hot jars and pour liquid over mixture.
Seal jars.

title: hello dolly's
directions: Melt butter in a 9 x 13-inch pan.
Pour crackers in pan with butter and spread crackers out in pan.
Pour chocolate chips over crackers.
Then pour nuts and coconut over chocolate chips.
Spread it out in pan.
Pour milk over the whole pan.
Bake at 350° until brown.

title: no bake chocolate cookies
directions: Combine butter, sugar, cocoa and milk; bring to a boil.
Boil 1 minute and remove from heat.
Add remaining ingredients and mix well.
Drop by teaspoon onto waxed paper.
Let cool and serve.

title: golden empire torte
directions: Place a 16 x 11-inch sheet of aluminum foil on baking sheet. Fold sides up to make a 15 x 10 x 1/2-inch pan.
Make a second pan. Sift together flour, baking powder and 3/4 cup sugar in small mixing bowl.
Beat egg whites, salt and cream of tartar in large bowl until soft mounds form.
Add 1/3 cup sugar, a tablespoon at a time, beating until stiff, straight peaks form.
Do not underbeat!

title: banana bread
directions: Cream together sugar, and soft butter.
Add the egg and mashed bananas.
Mix.
Add dry ingredients.
Mix again.
Add nuts.
Bake at 350° for about 1 hour.
Store a day before slicing.

title: broccoli tex-mex
directions: Brown meat in margarine.
Add garlic and tomatoes with liquid. Add broccoli and onion.
Simmer, covered, for 10 minutes.
Serve with tortillas or pita bread.

title: kosher pickles
directions: Wash cucumbers and pack in jars, leaving 1-inch headspace. To each jar, add 1 head of dill, 1 button garlic and a pinch of alum, the size of a pea.
Mix water, vinegar and pickling salt; bring to a boil.
Pour over pickles and seal.

title: apple crisp
directions: Mix first 3 ingredients and sprinkle with cinnamon.
Place in oven (350°) in 9-inch pie plate.
Mix remaining ingredients and spread over apples.
Bake 1/2 hour at 375°.

title: tossed fresh mushroom salad
directions: Combine ingredients.
Marinate and chill at least 1 hour. Serve.

title: sausage cheese balls
directions: All ingredients should be at room temperature.
Mix all together and form little balls.
Bake on ungreased cookie sheet for 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
May be stored in freezer up to 2 months.

title: cookie bars
directions: Pour melted margarine into 9 x 13-inch pan.
Sprinkle crumbs onto margarine.
Add nuts and chocolate chips, then coconut.
Pour 1 can of Eagle Brand milk over the mixture.
Bake in preheated oven at 350° for 25 minutes until golden brown.
Cool 15 minutes before cutting.

title: brocomole
directions: Cook broccoli according to package directions, but without salt.
Drain.
Place 3/4 of the broccoli (including all stalks) into your food processor or blender.
Add remaining ingredients and puree until smooth.
(Add reserved broccoli florets and process briefly for a slightly chunky texture.)
Makes 3 guilt-free servings.

title: latija(heritage:  guam)
directions: Slice sponge cake into 1/3-inch slices.
Place on platter and set aside.
In a thick 1-quart saucepan, bring 1 1/3 cups water to boiling point and add milk and sugar.
Mix 1/3 cup water with cornstarch and vanilla. Gradually add this to milk mixture. Continue cooking, stirring constantly, until mixture bubbles. Remove from heat and add butter.
Pour the well beaten eggs into the pudding in 4 additions, stirring vigorously after each addition.
Pour over sponge cake slices.
Sprinkle with cinnamon. Serves 8.

title: ginger chicken
directions: Marinate chicken for 1/2 hour in 1 teaspoon potato flour, 2 teaspoons thin soy sauce, 1/4 teaspoon ginger powder, 1/2 teaspoon sugar and 1 teaspoon oil.
Stir-fry chicken with 1 tablespoon oil for 1 minute; remove from wok.
Combine 1 tablespoon oil, onion, bamboo shoots and mushrooms in wok.
Season with 1 teaspoon soy sauce, 1 teaspoon sugar, lemon grass, water and salt.
Cover and cook over low heat for 3 to 5 minutes.
Add chicken and thicken with potato flour.

title: three bean casserole
directions: Cook sausage, celery, onion and garlic in skillet over medium heat approximately 10 minutes, stirring occasionally until sausage is no longer pink.
Drain.
Mix sausage mixture and remaining ingredients in ungreased 3-quart casserole dish.
Bake, uncovered, at 400° for approximately 45 minutes until hot and bubbly.
Stir mixture once during baking.

title: lemon squares
directions: Combine butter, powdered sugar, 2 cups flour and dash of salt. Mix together; it will be stiff.
Spread in 8 x 13-inch pan and bake at 350° for 20 minutes.
Do not overcook.
It should not turn brown, but just begin to brown in a spot or two.

title: cream corn casserole
directions: Saute onion, pepper and flour in butter.
Add other ingredients and heat.
Pour into casserole dish and bake at 350° for approximately 20 minutes (longer if necessary).

title: spinach salad
directions: Combine the first 5 ingredients and let stand.
Toss remaining ingredients together except cheese.
Top with cheese.
Pour on dressing before serving.

title: pot roast with cranberries
directions: Sprinkle meat with a little flour.
Brown on all sides in the fat.
Add water, cranberries (picked over then washed) and all other ingredients except the salt.
Cover and bring to boiling point, then simmer very gently until the meat is tender.
When 1/2 done, turn meat over and add salt.
Total cooking time: approximately 2 1/2 hours.
If necessary, thicken gravy with additional flour.

title: pasta salad
directions: Prepare the garlic sauce:
Crush the garlic, salt and cilantro with a mortar and pestle to a paste; mix in the lemon juice and olive oil.

title: eggs seymour
directions: Lay 8 slices bread flat in buttered 9 x 13-inch baking pan. On top of each slice, put Canadian bacon and 1 slice of sharp Cheddar cheese.
Place remaining 8 slices of bread over cheese. Beat ingredients 4 to 10 together and pour this mixture over bread; let stand overnight covered in refrigerator.
Melt 1/4 pound margarine and drizzle over top; cover with 1 cup crushed potato chips.
Bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: deep, dark chocolate cake
directions: Combine dry ingredients in a large mixing bowl.
Add remaining ingredients, except boiling water.
Beat at medium speed for 2 minutes.
Stir in boiling water (batter will be thin).
Pour into two greased and floured 9-inch or three 8-inch layer pans.
Bake at 350° for 30 to 35 minutes.
(Cook 35 to 40 minutes if using a 13 x 9-inch pan.)
Cool 10 minutes on rack.
Remove from pans. Cool completely before frosting.

title: pecan pie
directions: Cream shortening and sugar.
Add remaining ingredients and mix.
Pour into unbaked 9-inch pie shell.
Bake in a 425° oven for 10 minutes, then reduce heat to 350° and bake 25 more minutes.

title: easy date nut bread(mix by hand)
directions: Pour hot water over dates.
Add soda and butter; cool.
Add sugar and egg.
Sift together dry ingredients.
Gradually stir into date mixture.
Add nuts and vanilla.
Mix.
Pour into loaf pan and bake at 350° for 1 hour.

title: cranberry nut bread
directions: Preheat oven to 350°.
Grease and line a loaf pan, approximately 9 x 5 x 3-inches.
Sift flour, baking powder, baking soda and salt.
Cut in butter and add sugar.
Mix the orange rind and orange juice with the beaten egg.
Stir into the dry ingredients and mix well.
Fold in the nuts and cranberries.
Turn into the pan and bake for about 1 hour or until golden brown and firm to the touch.
Turn out and allow to cool before storing.

title: toll house cupcakes
directions: Cream butter, sugar, brown sugar and vanilla.
Add egg and beat well.
Add flour and baking soda.
Spoon by teaspoons into foil cupcake papers.
Bake at 375° for 10 to 12 minutes.
Take from oven and top with topping.

title: apple cake
directions: Mix apples and sugar.
Let stand 10 minutes.
Add the rest of the ingredients and mix well.
Bake at 350° about 50 minutes in loaf pan.
Can double recipe.
Cake keeps good.

title: cottage cheese salad
directions: Put cottage cheese in bowl; sprinkle on jello and mix.
Fold in fruit and Cool Whip.

title: sausage balls(appetizer)
directions: Grate cheese and allow to soften.
Mix all ingredients well with hands.
Shape into small balls.
Bake 15 to 20 minutes at 350°.
Bake in a cast-iron skillet that has been greased and sprinkled with flour.
(It will not stick.) Makes 60 to 90 balls. Can be frozen until ready to use.
May take a few more minutes baking time.

title: chili
directions: In a large kettle, brown ground beef.
Drain and set aside. In the same kettle, heat oil; saute garlic and onions over low heat until onions are tender.
Stir in green pepper, salt, chili powder, cayenne pepper, cinnamon, cumin, and oregano.
Cook for 2 minutes, stirring until well mixed.
Add beef and tomatoes with liquid.
Dissolve bouillon in water
and add to soup.
Simmer, covered, for about 1 hour.
Yield 8-10 servings.

title: mini sausage pizza
directions: Melt cheese and brown sausage. Mix all ingredients. Spread on top of bread and broil to melt spread. Serve hot.

title: breakfast egg casserole(serves 15)
directions: Mix eggs, milk and onion together.
Grease a 9 x 13-inch pan. Melt margarine in pan, then add bread cubes.
Pour egg mixture over cubes and cover with grated cheese.
Cover and refrigerate overnight.
Uncover and bake in a 325° oven for 1 hour, or until golden brown and firm.

title: tea cakes
directions: Cream melted shortening with sugar.
Blend in eggs, orange rind, extract and milk.
Mix well, then add self-rising flour until hard and firm.
Continue to knead in dry flour until real firm, then roll out.
Bake in a 400° oven for 10 to 12 minutes on an ungreased cookie sheet.

title: broccoli cheese soup
directions: Cook broccoli and onion.
Melt cheese and cream together.
In small box, mix cornstarch with milk.
Add cheese and cooked broccoli.
Stir in milk with cornstarch.
Add salt, garlic and pepper to taste.
Cook 30 minutes.

title: meat loaf
directions: Mix all but tomato sauce together; make loaf in pan.
Pour sauce over loaf and 4 cans water.
Bake at 325° one hour.

title: creamed chicken
directions: Cook onion in margarine until soft.
Blend in flour.
Slowly stir in broth, milk and canned milk.
Add salt.
Cook and stir over medium heat until mixture thickens.
Stir small amount of hot mixture into egg yolks.
Return to hot mixture.
Cook and stir over low heat about a minute.
Add diced chicken and heat just until hot through.
Serve over hot biscuits.
May also be served in patty shells.

title: seafood with fresh tagliatelle
directions: In a large frying pan heat, oil and add garlic.
Saute briefly and add seafood.
Cook, stirring until well coated with garlic oil. Add tomatoes, pimientos, paprika, saffron and salt to taste.
Pour in stock and bring to boil.
Add tagliatelle, stir and simmer until al dente (1 to 3 minutes).
If it looks as though there will be excess juice, increase the heat for the last half minute to reduce liquid.
The dish is ready when the pasta is cooked.

title: spaghetti sauce and meatballs
directions: In a very large pot, combine tomato sauce, tomato paste, water, spaghetti sauce and canned tomatoes; start simmering.

title: pig picken cake
directions: Mix all these together and bake in 3 layer pans or in a 9 x 13-inch pan for 20 minutes or until done by testing.

title: date nut balls
directions: Chop dates.
Combine
dates, sugar and butter in medium saucepan; bring to a
boil.
Cook, stirring constantly for one minute.
Stir in cereal
and
pecans.
Cool
mixture to touch; shape into 1 inch balls and roll in coconut or sugar.

title: squash casserole
directions: Cook squash and onion until tender.
Mix all ingredients together and pour in Pyrex dish; bake for 25 minutes at 350°.

title: cranberry salad
directions: Grind cranberries.
Mix gelatin and dissolve sugar.
Add ground orange, pineapple, cranberries and nuts.
Place in refrigerator until set.

title: irresistible peanut butter cookies
directions: Heat oven to 375°. Combine peanut butter, Crisco, light brown sugar, milk and vanilla in large bowl. Beat just until blended. Combine flour, salt and baking soda. Add to creamed mixture at low speed. Mix just until blended. Drop by heaping teaspoonfuls 2-inches apart onto ungreased baking sheet.

title: e-z pizza
directions: On a cookie sheet, lay crescent rolls out as 1 oblong crust. Bake at 375° for 7 to 10 minutes.
Heat sauce on top of the stove while the crust is baking.
After crust has baked, spread sauce on top. Turn oven to broil.
Sprinkle pizza with cheese on top of sauce and return to oven until cheese is melted.
Pepperoni and mushrooms can be added at the same time as the cheese is added.

title: baked beans
directions: Combine all ingredients in a crock-pot and cook for about 1 to 1 1/2 hours.

title: pineapple orange sunshine cake
directions: Combine top 4 ingredients to make cake.
Stir by hand for 2 minutes.
Bake at 350° oven in 13 X 9 inch pan for 30 minutes.

title: magic fruit cake
directions: Mix all ingredients, place in greased brown paper lined (bottom) pan (tube).
Bake at 250° for 2 to 2 1/2 hours.

title: pork chops in stewed tomatoes
directions: Fry pork chops on both sides.
Remove chops; pour off grease. Put 1/2 cup water in frypan.
Bring to boil; add tomatoes, vegetables and pork chops.
Bring to boil; turn heat down to simmer for 1 hour.
Thicken sauce with flour or cornstarch. Serve with mashed potatoes.

title: husband's delight casserole
directions: Brown beef and onions.
Add seasonings and tomato sauce, simmer 15 minutes.
Cook egg noodles as directed on package. Layer in dish with 1/2 noodles and 1/2 meat mixture.
Add cream cheese and sour cream, then remainder of noodles and meat mixture. Top with Cheddar cheese.
Bake 25 minutes at 350°.
Yields 10 to 12 servings.

title: milk chocolate cake
directions: Combine Spry, salt, vanilla and sugar.
Gradually cream until light and fluffy.
Add eggs one at a time, beating thoroughly after each addition.
Add melted chocolate.
Mix well.
Add flour and baking powder slowly with milk; mix until smooth.
Bake in 2 (8 or 9-inch) round greased and floured cake pans at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: texas caviar
directions: Boil peas in salted water for about 30 to 40 minutes.
Rinse with cold water.
While they're warm, mix peas in with remaining ingredients.
Refrigerate for at least 24 hours, because the longer it sits, the better it gets.
Serve with crackers; saltines are the best.

title: charlie bread
directions: Mix all of the ingredients.
Cook 30 minutes at 400° in a greased iron skillet.

title: peanut brittle
directions: Cook sugar, water and corn syrup until hard ball forms in cold water, then add unroasted peanuts and butter.
Cook until golden brown.
Take from heat and add soda and vanilla.
Pour in buttered pan and as soon as it is cold, break in pieces.

title: peach jello salad
directions: Heat pineapple and juice.
Add	dry
jello (remove from heat). Add buttermilk and mix
well.
Blend
in Cool Whip and put in refrigerator.
Can be cut in squares.

title: broccoli and rice casserole
directions: Cream together in saucepan the soup, cheese, butter and milk. Put rice and broccoli in baking dish; pour soup mixture over and mix.
Bake at 350° for 20 to 30 minutes.

title: chewy chip cake
directions: Mix and bake at 350° for 30 minutes (chewy).

title: 5 minute reese's pie
directions: Mix in a bowl Cool Whip, sugar and cream cheese.
Beat 2 minutes.
Add Reese's peanut butter cups, crushed.
Fold in, pour in pie crust.
Refrigerate and serve.

title: cheese cake
directions: Press firmly in greased 9-inch pie pan.
Chill about 45 minutes.

title: barbecue hamburger(used at legion ball games)
directions: Brown and drain hamburger, onions, salt and pepper.
Add remaining ingredients.

title: toffee squares
directions: Heat oven to 350°.
Melt margarine in microwave.
Mix all except chocolate bits and spread thin on cookie sheet.
Bake 10 to 12 minutes until edges start to brown.
Melt chocolate bits; spread over warm crust.
Sprinkle on chopped pecans or walnuts. Cut into squares.
Makes 5 dozen.

title: pie crust
directions: Mix and pat in pan.
Bake at 425° until golden brown, 10 to 15 minutes.

title: 24 hour vegetable salad
directions: In bottom of large bowl place 1/2 of vegetables.
Sprinkle sugar, salt and pepper over all.
Layer 1/2 of eggs over vegetables.
Place remaining vegetables over eggs.
Sprinkle sugar, salt and pepper over vegetables.
Add cheese and bacon and layer eggs on top.
Spread mayonnaise or salad dressing over top, sealing to edge of bowl.
Cover and refrigerate 24 hours or overnight.
Garnish with sliced green onions and paprika if desired.
Toss before serving.
Makes 12 to 15 servings.

title: pasghetti pizza
directions: Break spaghetti into 2-inch pieces.
In large sauce pot, cook according to package directions.
Drain and cool.
Preheat oven to 400°.
In large bowl, beat eggs lightly; stir in milk and add one cup Mozzarella cheese, onion, garlic powder and salt.
Add cooled spaghetti and stir until thoroughly combined.
Grease a 10 1/2 x 15 1/2-inch jelly roll pan and spread the spaghetti in the pan.
Bake for 15 minutes; remove from oven and reduce temperature to 350°.
Add toppings.

title: apple oat muffin
directions: In one bowl mix oats and allspice.
In small bowl mix honey, milk, oil and egg.
Pour liquid into oat and flour mixture.
Stir in apples and raisins, if desired.
Spoon into cupcake tin and bake in preheated 400° oven for 25 minutes.

title: finger jello
directions: Dissolve Knox gelatine in cold water.
Dissolve flavored jello in boiling water; add Knox and stir until dissolved.
Pour into a 9 x 13-inch pan until set, about 30 minutes.
Cut into squares or shapes with cookie cutter.
Serves 12.

title: grandma's donuts, refrigerator rolls or cinnamon rolls
directions: For donuts, add some vanilla.

title: scalloped potatoes
directions: Pare potatoes; slice thin.
Put half the potatoes in a greased 2-quart casserole.
Cover with half the sauce, seasonings and onion.
Add remaining potatoes, seasonings and onion, then remaining sauce.
Cover and bake in moderate oven (350°) for about 1 hour.
Uncover and continue baking until top is browned.
Grated cheese may be added to white sauce.
Makes 4 to 6 servings.

title: harvard beets
directions: Mix sugar, cornstarch and salt.
Stir into brown vinegar. Blend.
Add 1/3 cup hot water.
Cook on medium heat and stir constantly, approximately 3 minutes or until thick.
Pour over diced or cut beets and butter.
Let stand in syrup 30 minutes. Serve hot.

title: rotini salad
directions: Cook rotini and drain. In bowl, combine all ingredients. Mix well and chill.

title: sweet and sour meatballs
directions: Combine all ingredients, except jelly and chili sauce.
Roll into 1-inch balls.
Dredge in flour and brown in 2 to 3 tablespoons of oil in skillet.
Remove and set aside.

title: chewy bread
directions: Combine sugar and butter; add eggs one at a time, beating well after each.
Add flour and blend.
Add nuts and bake in 13 x 9 x 2-inch greased pan for 35 to 40 minutes at 350°.
Yield:
3 dozen squares.

title: miniature pecan pies
directions: Combine cream cheese and margarine in a large bowl.
Cut in flour and salt with pastry blender until blended.
Shape into 1-inch balls.
Place into miniature muffin cups, pressing to cover bottom and side.
Chill for 1 hour. Beat eggs in bowl until foamy. Add cooled, melted margarine and vanilla.
Mix well. Add brown sugar and pecans.
Mix well.
Spoon into prepared muffin cups, filling 3/4 full.
Bake at 325° for 25 minutes or until filling is set. Cool and remove from pans. Yields 48 servings.

title: pasta primavera
directions: In a large saucepan over high heat, bring 3 quarts of water to a boil.
Add rotelle; cook 10 minutes.
Add broccoli and red peppers.
Cook 3 to 4 minutes longer or until pasta and vegetables are just tender; drain and set aside.
In a medium size saucepan over medium heat, heat butter until hot.
Add garlic.
Cook 2 to 3 minutes or until golden.
Remove from heat.
Stir in Ricotta and Parmesan cheeses, milk, basil, salt and ground pepper.
Return pasta and vegetables to large saucepan.
Add Ricotta mixture.
Toss to coat thoroughly.
Serve hot or cover and refrigerate 2 hours to serve as a salad.

title: hamburg cabbage casserole
directions: Cook rice.
While it is standing, brown the ground beef with salt, pepper and onion.
Simmer until onion is tender.
Add tomato soup and heat.

title: fruit salad
directions: Mix well; chill and serve.

title: chicken enchiladas
directions: Cook onion in oleo and add chilies.
Cook until clear (5 minutes).
Add milk and soup.
Bring to boil.
Pour over 1 layer tortillas, layer cheese, layer chicken, several layers.
Top with cheese.
Bake 30 minutes at 350°.

title: creamy squash casserole
directions: Cook squash until tender; drain well.
Add chicken soup, sour cream, pimento, water chestnuts and onions.
Melt 3/4 stick of butter in a large skillet.
Add stuffing.
Mix well.
Pack stuffing into bottom of a 3-quart baking dish, reserving some to top casserole.
Pour squash mix over stuffing and sprinkle remaining stuffing over top.
Dot the rest of the butter on top of casserole and bake at 350° for 30 minutes.

title: mandarin orange cake
directions: Mix ingredients together and beat until combined using medium speed of electric mixer.
Pour into two 8-inch pans and bake at 350° for 25 or 30 minutes.

title: killer bread(aka "killer breath")
directions: Spread items on top of Boboli crust in order given, sprinkling Parmesan on top.
Bake at 425°
for 8 to 10 minutes.
Slice in hors d'oeuvre size pieces.

title: hot dog chili
directions: Brown ground beef; drain.
Add all other ingredients to beef. Simmer and serve.

title: ground beef 'n tater casserole
directions: Brown beef in skillet; drain.
Combine beef, green beans, soup, water, salt and pepper.
Pour into 1 1/2-quart casserole.
Combine mashed potatoes and 1/2 can French fried onions.
Spoon potato mixture in a mounded ring around top outer edge of casserole. Bake, uncovered, at 350° for 25 minutes.
Top potatoes with cheese and remaining onions and bake 5 minutes longer.
Makes 6 servings.

title: mile high pie (strawberry or raspberry)
directions: Beat egg whites, sugar, lemon juice, and berries for 15 minutes.
Fold in whipped cream.
Pour into crumb crust and freeze.

title: microwave divinity
directions: Beat egg whites until stiff.
Set aside.
In a large glass bowl, cook sugar water and syrup on High 7 to 9 minutes or until 236°, stirring 1 or 2 times.
Remove 1/3 cup and slowly add to egg whites, beating at medium speed.
Cook remaining syrup on High 3 to 5 minutes to 264° (soft crack), stirring 1 or 2 times.
Slowly add to egg whites, beating on medium speed.
Beat 12 to 15 minutes or until dull.
Add nuts.
Drop on wax paper by spoonful to cool. For freshness keep in airtight container.
